title: buttermilk rolls
directions: Mix dry yeast with 1/4 cup warm water. Heat buttermilk, shortening and sugar to lukewarm. In mixing bowl, combine flour, salt and soda. Fold in all ingredients. Let stand for 1 hour. Roll out like biscuits, dip in melted butter and fold. Place in pans. Cover and let stand for 1 hour. Bake at 475° for 8 - 10 minutes.

title: chocolate crinkle cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
It will be hard at first but don't add any water.
Roll into small balls and then roll in powdered sugar.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes.
Don't overbake. Cool on a cookie sheet for a minute before removing to a wire rack to cool.

title: garlic cheese spread
directions: Put margarine and Cheddar cheese in processor; mix until blended and fluffy.
Add garlic and Parmesan cheese and beat until very smooth and fluffy.
Refrigerate in screw-top jar.
Spread on sourdough a generous 1/4-inch.
Broil 5 to 6-inches below broiler until bubbly and lightly golden.
Don't overcook!

title: pineapple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together with spoon, no mixer.
Bake in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: holiday ham slices tutti-frutti
directions: Combine crushed pineapple with mixed chopped fruits and half the brown sugar.
Spread half the mixture over one ham steak and top with the other, sandwich fashion.
Place ham steaks on a large sheet of heavy-duty Reynold's Wrap.
Wrap loosely and place in a shallow pan.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes.
Remove from oven; spoon out fat.
Top with remaining fruit mixture, pineapple chunks, pecans, orange sections, cherries and remaining brown sugar. Return to oven for 20 minutes to glaze, basting occasionally with liquid in foil.

title: cream pie
directions: Heat milk.
Mix sugar, egg yolks, flour, salt and vanilla together.
Add to milk.
Heat until it begins to thicken.
Pour into cooked pie crust.

title: cheesy potato dish
directions: Combine all ingredients except cornflake crumbs.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with cornflake crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: easy baked chicken
directions: Arrange pieces of chicken in a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish. Sprinkle with pepper.
Place slices of cheese to cover chicken. Spread cream of mushroom soup to completely cover the cheese slices.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
The melted cheese and soup make a good gravy over rice.

title: strawberry nut bread
directions: Combine berries and their juice with eggs, lemon juice and oil in a large bowl.
Combine dry ingredients, except nuts, and gradually stir into berry mixture.
Add nuts.
Pour batter into a greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: lancaster county party mix
directions: In a very large bowl, combine the first 5 ingredients.
Melt the white chocolate.
Pour on dried ingredients and toss it to coat everything.
Then spread the mixture on cookie sheets so the chocolate will harden.
Usually takes about 10 to 15 minutes to cool.
Once it hardens, break it up and store in a sealed container.

title: beef with cauliflower and snow peas
directions: In oil, brown garlic and remove.
Add beef, cut in small, thin slices and saute until brown.
Add onions, salt and pepper; cook a few seconds.
Add bouillon, cauliflower and snow peas.
Cook about 5 minutes or until cauliflower and peas are thoroughly heated but not soft.
Add mixture of cornstarch, soy sauce and water.
Cook a few minutes longer to thicken, stirring slowly.
Serve hot on rice.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: granny's light bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/4 cup of warm water for 5 minutes. Combine all ingredients.
Let rise until double in bulk.
Punch down.
Roll into balls and let rise again, approximately 45 minutes.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: sore throat gargle
directions: Stir salt, baking soda and aspirin tablets in warm water until dissolved.

title: chicken tortillas
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Line pan with 4 tortillas and spread with mushroom soup, 2 cups of the chicken, half of the peppers and onions and half of the cheese.
Layer 4 more tortillas and spread with the chicken soup and the rest of the chicken, peppers, onions and cheese.
Pour the tomatoes with chili peppers over the top.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix until all ingredients are well mixed up; chill.
Use as dip for your favorite diced or sliced fruits.

title: pigeon pie
directions: Line a deep casserole dish with pastry.
Fry squabs until brown and place in dish with pastry.
Blend flour into bacon fat in saucepan; add stock and milk slowly, stirring together.
Add salt and pepper.
Cook, stirring until thickened.
Pour over squabs.
Sprinkle buttered crumbs on top and bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 375° and cook 10 minutes more until crumbs and edge of crust are browned.
Serves 4.
May substitute fryer chicken or 4 and 20 blackbirds.

title: brandied fruit
directions: To start culture, mix all of the ingredients together and allow to stand for 2 weeks.
Add 1 cup sugar and 1 cup fruit. This sugar and fruit mixture may be added every 2 weeks.
Fruit is ready to eat in 2 weeks.
Any assortment of canned fruits may be used.
Stir mixture occasionally to mix sugar in well.
Good over ice cream or angel food cake with whipped cream.

title: soda cracker cake
directions: Gradually add sugar to beaten egg whites.
Fold in crackers and pecans.
Spoon into a buttered deep pie pan.
Bake in a 325° oven until golden brown.
Cool.
Top with Cool Whip.
Spoon drained crushed pineapple on Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with coconut (optional).

title: bloody eight
directions: In pitcher, combine V-8 juice, horseradish, Worcestershire sauce and hot pepper sauce.
Pour over ice.
Garnish with celery stick.

title: gooey butter cake
directions: Mix together cake mix, melted butter and 2 eggs.
Press into well-greased and floured cake pan.
Next, mix 2 eggs, powdered sugar and cream cheese together.
Pour on top of other mixture and bake 40 to 55 minutes at 300°.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Slice stem ends from peppers and scoop out seeds.
Blanch peppers in boiling water for 2 to 3 minutes.
Drain well.
Season inside of peppers with salt and pepper.
Combine beef and next 6 ingredients.
Stuff peppers with meat mixture and place in a buttered 2 quart casserole dish.
Cover and bake in 350° oven for 55 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Top peppers with cheese and chili sauce.
Bake uncovered for 5 minutes longer.

title: guilt free orange balls
directions: Combine
all ingredients, except extra coconut or pecans. Form into balls. Roll balls in coconut or pecans. Refrigerate to set.

title: buttermilk glaze
directions: Mix in a saucepan and bring to a boil.
Pour over baked cake.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix together; put in dish.
Cover with crushed potato chips. Bake at 350° for approximately 25 minutes.

title: clam chowder
directions: Heat clams and juice on medium heat and add butter.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
Add vegetables and cook until potatoes are tender. Mix together milk, can milk and cornstarch and pour into clam mixture.
Ready to serve when chowder has thickened.

title: broccoli-cauliflower salad
directions: Cook bacon over medium heat.
Crumble and set aside.
In a medium sized salad bowl, layer in order broccoli, cauliflower, eggs, cheese and bacon.
Prepare the dressing by whisking together the sugar, mayo and vinegar.
Drizzle over top and serve.

title: banana muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Spray muffin tins with vegetable cooking spray.
In a large bowl, combine first 5 ingredients.
In separate bowl, combine bananas, applesauce, egg and orange juice; add to dry ingredients and stir until moistened.
Spoon batter into muffin tin and bake 25 to 30 minutes or until lightly browned.
One muffin contains 118 calories.

title: grilled shrimp and scallops
directions: Place scallops and shrimp in a plastic bag. Set bag in a bowl. Mix the oil, parsley, lemon juice, garlic, salt and pepper. Add to bag.
Seal the bag and marinate for 4 to 6 hours, turning bag occasionally.
Drain and reserve marinade.

title: stove-top roast
directions: Cover roast with water, Kitchen Bouquet and salt.
Boil on high for 1 hour, adding water as necessary.
Add baby carrots, potatoes and onion making sure water still covers the roast.
Turn on medium and cook for 30 minutes, or until carrots are tender. When done, mix gravy packet with 1/4 cup of water and slowly add to roast, stirring well.
Simmer for 20 minutes, or until gravy is thick.
Season to suit taste.

title: plains special cheese ring
directions: Mix. Mold in ring.
Place in refrigerator until chilled. Unmold on plate and fill center with strawberry preserves.
Serve with crackers.
This is Rosalynn Carter's recipe in Plains cookbook.

title: red banquet punch
directions: Mix the punch, sugar and pineapple juice.
Fill pineapple juice can with water 3 times.
Add orange juice.
Freeze in 2-gallon ice cream buckets.
When ready to serve, set out frozen bucket for a short time, then add 1 bottle of ginger ale.

title: canning spaghetti sauce
directions: Combine
all
ingredients
and	cook in large container until thick.
Add
a
little cornstarch and cook until it has thickened. Put in hot jars.
Seal.
Boil for 15 minutes.

title: bisquick mix
directions: In large bowl, mix
flour, baking powder and salt.
Cut in shortening.
Store in covered container, needs no refrigeration, and use when Bisquick is called for in recipes.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream first 3 ingredients real good.
Add eggs and flour alternately.
Add vanilla and lemon juice last.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 325° to 350°.

title: mom's sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into baking dish.

title: gardeners' delight
directions: Make sure all vegetables are diced to bite size proportions. Saute vegetables and onions in butter.
Season with garlic or seasoning of your choice.
In another pan, brown the sausage (sliced).
Combine sausage and vegetables.
Be sure to drain meat. Pour in gravy that's made following directions on package.
Cover and let simmer about 15 minutes on low flame.
Boil rice.
To serve, serve mixture over the rice.
Goes great with kid and Kool-Aid.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: cream cheese coffee cake
directions: Then you put another can of crescent rolls on the above.

title: hominy casserole
directions: Mix ingredients together except Mexican Velveeta cheese. Sprinkle it on top of mixture.
Bake 1 hour at 350°, covered.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Cream oil, sugar and eggs.
Add apples, flour, soda, baking powder, salt and cinnamon.	Stir well.
Pour into lightly greased 9 x 13 pan.
Sprinkle nuts and morsels on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: quick candied popcorn
directions: Bring syrup, sugar and salt to boil over medium heat; boil 2 minutes, stirring constantly. Gradually pour over popped corn; toss until coated. Shape in the shape you want them and add the food coloring as you want to.

title: mom's chocolate pie
directions: Beat egg yolks.
Add milk gradually and mix well.
Gradually stir into dry ingredients.
Cook in medium size saucepan, on medium heat, until thick, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add vanilla and butter; stir well.

title: banana boat
directions: Fix pudding according to directions on box.
Cut up bananas in bottom of large container and spread wafers in with bananas.
Pour pudding over that.
Spread Cool Whip on top and chill.

title: onion roasted potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Blend everything, except the potatoes. Add potatoes and coat thoroughly, stirring occasionally.
Bake for 40 to 50 minutes or until potatoes are tender and golden brown.
Garnish with chopped parsley, if desired.

title: red cherry pie filling
directions: Drain cherries and save juice.
Combine cornstarch, sugar and salt.
Stir in 3/4 cup cherry juice.
Cook until thick and clear. Add almond extract.
Pour over cherries in a 9-inch pastry lined pie pan. Dot with butter.
Cover with top pastry (pie dough). Trim edges and bake in hot 425° oven for about 40 minutes.

title: french vanilla coffee
directions: Add vanilla, creamer and sugar to 1 (8 ounce) cup of hot coffee.

title: granny jo's raisin cake
directions: *Use some to flour raisins "good."

title: layered banana pudding
directions: In saucepan combine flour and brown sugar; stir in milk.
Cook and stir over medium heat until thickened; then cook 1 minute more. Remove from heat.
Stir 1 cup mixture into egg yolks.
Return all to saucepan.
Bring to a boil, cook and stir 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in margarine and vanilla.
Cool to room temperature; stir occasionally.
Fold in whipped cream.
Layer a third of the pudding in a 2-quart glass bowl; top with half of the bananas.
Repeat layers.
Top with pudding.
Sprinkle with nuts. Cover and chill at least 1 hour before serving.

title: chocolate peanut butter ritz crackers
directions: Melt Hershey bars in double boiler; cook slowly.
Add paraffin and stir well.
Do not let it get too thick.
If it becomes too thick, add more paraffin.
Dip Ritz cracker with peanut butter that has been prepared before preparing chocolate.
There should be 2 crackers with peanut butter between before dipping.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar well; add eggs and beat thoroughly. Sift soda, salt and flour together 3 times.
Add to egg and sugar mixture.
Mix well; add sour cream and flavorings.
Preheat oven to 325°.
Bake 1 1/2 hours in tube pan.
Batter may be divided and cooked in loaf pans.

title: country chicken casserole
directions: Combine milk, salad dressing and cheese.
Stir and cook over low heat until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into a 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Can be divided and frozen before baking.

title: spiced apple slices
directions: Arrange apple slices in a lightly greased 1-quart baking dish. Combine remaining ingredients and pour over apple slices.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Makes 2 servings.

title: hot spiced punch
directions: Put apple cider and cranberry juice in large coffeepot. Combine sugar, salt, cinnamon sticks and cloves in coffeepot basket.
Perk!

title: foolproof fudge
directions: Heat chips with Eagle Brand on stove. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Put wax paper in pan.
Pour in.
Put in refrigerator to cool. Cut up.

title: old fashion potato chips
directions: Peel potatoes.	Rinse
in
cold water.	Slice crosswise into rounds, thin and
uniform,	by
hand
or
use a vegetable slicer that
works
by hand or attaches to an electric mixer. Soak sliced potatoes in several changes of very cold water for 2
hours, adding ice cubes to the last change of water.
Turn potato	slices into
a towel and dry thoroughly.	Fill a deep fat
fryer	with 3
inches
of oil and heat to 375°.
Using a frying
basket
or large
spatula, fry only a few slices at a time, shaking the basket to prevent sticking.
Chips should be golden
in
4	to
5 minutes.
Drain chips on paper towels or brown paper bag.
Salt just before serving.

title: apricot bars
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Stir in oats and sugar.
Cut in butter until crumbly.
Pat 2/3 crumbs in 11 x 7-inch pan.
Spread with preserves.
Top with remaining crumbs.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes; cool and cut in bars.
Yields 2 1/2 dozen.

title: butterscotch brownies
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into lightly-greased 9 x 13-inch Pyrex.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 325°.
Cool; cut into squares.

title: bacon wrapped smokies
directions: Wrap each smokie with 1/2 to 1/3 slice of raw bacon.
Roll in brown sugar and insert toothpick to hold.
Place all smokies in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with remaining brown sugar and pat down gently.
Leave out on the counter for 24 hours (don't worry, it won't spoil).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Watch carefully after 45 minutes so the bacon doesn't burn.
You might want to place smokies on a paper towel before you transfer to a serving dish.

title: eight layer overnight salad
directions: Make in layers as listed.
Cover with Saran Wrap and refrigerate overnight.
Can be made in deep bowl or baking dish, not so deep.
Very good!
Serves 10 to 12.

title: fruit punch
directions: Mix well and chill.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: almond roca
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle bottom of pan with 1/4 cup chopped nuts.
In a heavy saucepan, melt the butter.
Add sugar.
Stir continually and cook over medium heat.
When the toffee comes to a vigorous boil, continue to cook for another 4 to 5 minutes.
It will start to change to a slightly darker brown and will not be as frothy.
When it reaches the hard ball stage, quickly pour the mixture into the baking dish.
Spread it to cover.
Layer chocolate bars on top of toffee.
As it melts, spread it to cover the toffee.
Sprinkle with remaining nuts. When cool, break into pieces.
If you want to refrigerate the candy, do it after the pieces are broken up.

title: secret cake
directions: Sift flour, sugar and salt together.
Bring margarine, water and cocoa to a boil; pour over sugar mixture and blend well.
Add buttermilk, eggs, vanilla and soda; mix well.
Batter will be thin. Pour into greased and floured 11 x 16 x 1-inch pan.
Bake in 400° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: jessie's pie crust
directions: In a bowl, mix together flour, baking powder and lard.
Mix until crumbly.
In second bowl, combine egg, vinegar and water. Add to dry ingredients.
Makes 4 crusts.
Can be frozen for future use.

title: baked trout
directions: Place fish fillets skin down in baking dish.
Top each fillet with 2 pats of margarine.
Sprinkle with onion and garlic powder, top with lemon pepper.
Bake uncovered at 400° for about 20 minutes.
Serve with fresh lemon juice.
Very low calories.
Real good.

title: ham-rice casserole
directions: Reserve 1/3 can of cheese soup or grated cheese to spread over top. Cook onion and green pepper with rice. Mix with remaining ingredients. Bake for 45 minutes at 375°.

title: raisin bran muffins
directions: Mix together.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Sift all dry ingredients together.
Drain juice and add fruit cocktail.
Mix well.
Add fruit last.
Cook at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: zucchini sausage pie
directions: Mix all together and put in greased pie plate.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: southern fried chicken
directions: Combine flour, seasoning salt and pepper to desired taste. Rinse chicken thoroughly.
Leave chicken wet.
Flour chicken pieces thoroughly.
Place in hot skillet of shortening.
Cook chicken on medium heat until golden brown, 30 to 40 minutes. Drain on paper towel.

title: quick and easy beef stroganoff
directions: Mix flour and salt; coat meat with flour.
Cook and stir onion and garlic in shortening in 10-inch skillet until onion is tender; remove from skillet.
Cook and stir beef in same skillet until brown.
Stir in onion, garlic, water, tomato sauce, salt and pepper.
Heat to boiling, reduce heat.
Cover and simmer until liquid thickens.
Stir in sour cream and serve over noodles. Serves 6.

title: dinner rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour mixture into a greased muffin pan.
Bake 10 minutes at 400°.
Makes 12 rolls.

title: * hamburger soup *
directions: Bring the 4 cups of water to a boil.
Add all ingredients, except allspice.
Cook until nearly tender, then add allspice. Simmer until vegetables are tender.
Add more water if needed. Serves 4.

title: mom's meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Shape into loaves and bake at 350° in a greased loaf pan for 1 1/2 hours.
Put ketchup over top before baking.

title: corn bread
directions: Add the milk to the meal and mix thoroughly.
Add the oil and stir.
Spoon into a greased and preheated 8 x 4-inch pan or a similar pan or fill muffin tin cups half full.
Bake at 450° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: springtime garden pilaf
directions: In 2-quart saucepan, bring water, butter, chicken, salt, pepper and garlic to a full boil (5 to 7 minutes).
Add rice and carrots; return to a full boil.
Reduce heat to low.
Simmer until rice is tender (25 to 30 minutes).
Stir in remaining ingredients.

title: prune cake
directions: Combine flour, soda, cinnamon, nutmeg, allspice and salt thoroughly with a wire whisk in a large mixing bowl.
Add sugar, oil, buttermilk, eggs, prunes and vanilla, mixing well with electric mixer.
Pour into 2 greased and floured 9-inch round cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: mom's best oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Drop onto cookie tray by teaspoonfuls.
Bake at 350°.

title: beer bread
directions: Melt butter in loaf pan.
Mix flour and sugar.
Add beer; stir.
Pour into pan that has melted butter in it.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Cook fryer in pressure cooker until tender.
Tear meat from bones.
Place in long casserole dish.
Pour soups and sour cream over chicken.
Sprinkle 1 1/2 cups cracker crumbs over top.
Dot with 1/2 stick butter. Sprinkle with poppy seed and bake until hot.

title: lemon delight
directions: Beat first 3 ingredients and pour over cooled crust. Mix pudding with milk. Beat together. Pour over second layer. Spread remaining Cool Whip on top. Pecans (chopped) may be sprinkled on top.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix ginger, cinnamon, flour, sugar and salt.
Beat eggs until light, add dry ingredients, then pumpkin.
Mix well.
Add milk and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour into two 10-inch pie shells.
Bake 10 minutes at 450° then 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: oatmeal muffins
directions: Place oatmeal in blender.
Blend until a fine powder.
Measure and add enough flour to make 2 cups.
Mix oatmeal-flour mixture with baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Break egg into cup.
Add enough buttermilk until cup is full.
Place this mixture, oil and honey in blender.
Blend.
Add flour mixture.
Blend again.

title: easy red velvet cake
directions: Mix cake mix with next 3 ingredients.
Add cocoa; mix well. Add food coloring; mix well.
Pour in greased, floured pan and bake 25 to 30 minutes in 350° oven.
Use Cream Cheese icing listed in icing section.

title: easy ice cream sandwich
directions: Combine softened ice cream, peanut butter and vanilla thoroughly.
Spoon onto grahams and cover.
Seal each sandwich tightly in plastic wrap and freeze until firm.
Enjoy.

title: cracker bacon wrap
directions: Wrap crackers with a slice of bacon. Place on a cookie sheet. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Bake at 200° for approximately 2 hours.

title: delicious strawberry pie
directions: Mix and press into a 9-inch pie plate.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes, checking to make sure it doesn't get too brown, every 10 minutes.
Cool.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add all other ingredients; mix well. Pour into baking dish.

title: denver omelet
directions: Cook onion, pepper in pan.
Beat eggs; add milk and salt. Stir in cheese and onion mixture.

title: rice and artichoke salad
directions: Cook rice; omit browning.
Cool.
Combine remaining ingredients and add to rice.
Serve on a bed of lettuce as a luncheon entree or as a side dish.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Line a pan with foil.
Place butter in pan and place in the oven at 400° until butter melts, evenly coating the bottom of the pan.
In a bag, place the flour, salt, paprika, seasoning and pepper.
Place chicken in and shake until it is well coated. Place the coated chicken, skin side down, in the pan.
Bake for 25 minutes at 400°.
Cook the rice. Take the chicken out of the pan. Place the rice on the bottom of the pan. Add the onions and green pepper.
Place the chicken, skin side up, in the pan.
Pour the soup over all and bake, uncovered, 45 minutes at 400°.
Use a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Serves 4.

title: barbecue steak sauce
directions: Melt butter; add lemon juice and Worcestershire sauce.
Baste meat with this sauce.
Pour over barbecued meat.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each.
Sift flour three times.
Add one cup to mixture and mix well.
Add water and vanilla, then remaining cup of flour with the baking powder.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes, then at 325° for 15 minutes.
(All ingredients should be room temperature for best results.)

title: wicked garlic dip
directions: Boil potatoes until soft and drain well.
Transfer to bowl of food processor fitted with steel blade.
Without waiting for potatoes to cool, add the remaining ingredients and whip until very smooth.
Cover tightly and chill until serving.

title: confetti cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a small bowl, combine flour, baking soda and salt; set aside.
In a large mixer bowl, beat butter and sugar until creamy; beat in eggs and vanilla extract.
Gradually beat in flour mixture.
Stir in Nestle morsels.
Drop by rounded measuring tablespoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake 11 to 12 minutes until edges are lightly browned.
Let stand 2 minutes. Remove from cookie sheets.
Cool.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: frosty sours
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in container of electric blender; process until smooth. Gradually add ice, processing until mixture reaches desired consistency.
Yield:
about 4 cups.

title: world's best cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add egg and mix well.
Add oil and beat.
Add all other ingredients and stir in pecans.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Yields: 7 to 8 dozen.

title: scalloped potatoes and ham
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt oleo in large saucepan over low heat.
Blend in flour, salt and pepper.
Cook and stir in milk. Return to heat and cook until thickened and bubbly.
Fold in ham, onion, green pepper and cheese.
Pour over potatoes in large bowl. Pour into buttered 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Cover with foil. Bake 30 minutes at 350°, covered.
Uncover and bake for 1 hour or until brown and bubbly.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving. Serves 6.

title: 4 layer dip
directions: Mix together; spread in bottom of 8 x 10-inch dish.

title: glazed carrots
directions: Boil carrots for 10 minutes.
Drain all of the water.
Add the onion, margarine, brown sugar and nutmeg.
Simmer, stirring occasionally, for 15 minutes or until tender.

title: ground turkey meat loaf
directions: Soak bread in milk and eggs.
Stir in carrots, onion, cheese and meat.
Press into loaf pan.
Stir together the brown sugar, catsup and prepared mustard.
Pour over top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: french toast
directions: Dip loaf bread in batter; fry in butter until brown.

title: crab salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate overnight to absorb flavor.

title: mashed potato donuts
directions: Mix in order given.
Roll out and cut.
Deep fat fry at 375° until golden brown.

title: lime gelatin salad
directions: Heat pineapple slowly to boil; add Jell-O and stir until dissolved. Add buttermilk and coconut. Fold in Cool Whip. Chopped nuts are optional.

title: ham delights
directions: Split rolls.
Mix margarine, mustard, poppy seed, Worcestershire and onions in saucepan over low heat.
Heat until mixed.
Spread ham and cheese on rolls.
Spread butter mixture on inside and top of rolls.
Replace rolls in tray.
Top with foil. Bake 10 to 15 minutes at 400°.
Freezes well.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Cook spaghetti according to pkg. directions, drain. Melt cheese in microwave according to package directions. In a large bowl combine cheese, undrained tomatoes and soups. Stir in spaghetti and chicken. Place in a 2-quart baking dish and bake for 15-20 minutes or until heated through. May cook on stove top also, stir frequently.

title: buckeyes(makes 6 pounds)
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large bowl.
Mix until well blended.
Break off small amounts and knead until smooth.
Make soft balls, size of quarter.
Place on cookie sheet lined with Handi-Wrap.
Place a toothpick in each ball.
Place candy in refrigerator to chill.

title: salted peanut chews
directions: Combine all the ingredients, except for marshmallows.
Press into greased 9 x 13-inch pan and bake 12 to 15 minutes at 350°. Remove from oven and top with the marshmallows.
Return to oven 1 or 2 minutes, just until they are fluffy.
Cool.

title: aunt tina's blondies
directions: In double boiler, melt butter.
Stir in light brown sugar. Cook until melted.
Remove from heat and cover.
In mixing bowl, crack 6 eggs.
Stir in sugar mixture.
Add flour and vanilla.
Mix well.
Stir in nuts.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Fills a 9 x 13-inch and a 12 x 18-inch pan.

title: peanut butter squares
directions: Mix together peanut butter and crushed corn flakes.
Heat Karo and sugar until bubbly.
Do not boil.
Pour over peanut butter and corn flakes mixture.
Mix well.
Press into 8 x 12-inch pan. Cool.
Melt almond bark in microwave.
Spread over pressed mixture in pan.
When firm, cut into squares.

title: broccoli cauliflower salad
directions: Cut up vegetables into small pieces. Mix other ingredients into a shaker. Add dressing just before serving.

title: sesame chicken with honey dip
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients; set aside.
Mix crumbs and sesame seed.
Coat chicken with real mayonnaise mixture, then crumb mixture.
Place on baking sheet.
Bake in 425° oven 12 minutes or until lightly browned.
Serve hot with dip.
Serves 6.

title: jello punch
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in water. Mix all ingredients together and finish out with water to make 1 gallon of punch.
Mix your favorite sherbet with the punch which has been chilled when you are ready to serve.

title: no-cook custard
directions: Mix together the milk, pudding, vanilla and sugar; add dry whipped topping mix and mix until desired thickness.
Let chill. (If this gets too thick, add a little milk to thin.)

title: hot chicken
directions: Stew chicken and debone.
Cook until mixed: cream of chicken soup, chicken broth and jalapeno peppers.
Layer 1/2 of Fritos in an 8 x 10-inch baking dish.
Add chicken layer, then layer with rest of Fritos.
Pour sauce over mixture.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
Top with cheese and bake for 10 minutes.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Grease a 1-quart casserole.
Combine first 6 ingredients until well blended.
Pour into casserole; top with Provolone.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes or until brown on top.

title: sausage cheese balls
directions: Mix all ingredients and roll into balls about 1-inch in diameter.
Place on cookie sheet and bake at 325° for 20 minutes, turning balls over after first 10 minutes.

title: taco casserole
directions: Mix hamburger with taco seasoning (according to directions). Cover with Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 or 30 minutes or microwave on High for 10 minutes.

title: white cake
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt three times or more. Cream shortening.
Add sugar and cream until fluffy.
Add dry ingredients alternately with liquid, lastly fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Bake at 350° in three 9-inch layers.
Wonderful for fresh coconut, using 7 minute icing.

title: creamy orange dip
directions: Combine all ingredients in a small bowl.
Stir until smooth. Cover and chill thoroughly.
Serve with fresh fruit or unsalted crackers.

title: chicken tarragon
directions: Cut chicken into strips.
Add oil and butter in frypan with shallots, garlic, salt and pepper and tarragon.
Cook until golden. Remove chicken.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix thoroughly and store.
Put 2 or 3 teaspoons in a cup and pour in hot water.

title: peggy's creation
directions: Mix all ingredients except Cool Whip; put it in last.
Cover with chopped nuts and refrigerate.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt margarine in oven in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Remove from oven; sprinkle crumbs over margarine, pressing down with a fork.
Sprinkle coconut over crumbs; add a layer of chips and one of pecans.
Drizzle condensed milk evenly over the top.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes, or until golden brown. Cool and cut into bars.
Makes 3 dozen cookies.

title: corned beef sandwiches(so good and easy)
directions: Simmer slowly for 1 hour.
Serve on toasted buns.
Makes 4 sandwiches.

title: cut-out cookies
directions: Beat margarine and sugar until light and fluffy.
Blend in eggs and vanilla.
Add combined dry ingredients; mix well.
Chill several hours or overnight.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Cream sugar and butter.
Add flour and eggs alternately.
Add vanilla and coconut extract and buttermilk. Pour into pie shell.
Set oven to 350°.
Cook about 1 hour or until pie is done.

title: apricot chicken breasts
directions: Mix together the first 3 ingredients; pour over the chicken breasts.
Bake, covered, at 300° for 1 hour.
Remove cover; bake 30 minutes longer.
Baste with the sauce.

title: no bake chocolate cookies
directions: In a large pan melt together cocoa, butter and sugar.
Bring to a boil, boil 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add syrup, peanut butter and marshmallow cream, blend until smooth.
Add oats.
Put in freezer for 1 to 2 hours and serve.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine ground chuck with onion, tomato sauce, egg, oatmeal, seasoning and salt.
Mix together well.
Place into 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Shape into loaf.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours. Serves 8 to 10.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Beat together sugar, pumpkin, eggs and oil.
Sift dry ingredients together and add alternately with the water and soda mixture, to the first mixture.
Bake in 3 loaf pans (sprayed with nonstick spray and lightly floured) for 1 hour at 350°.

title: french pork pie
directions: Cook over medium heat the meat, onion and cold water for 1 1/2 hours, stirring often. Drain fat.
In a separate pan, boil the potatoes, then mash without milk or butter.
Add mashed potatoes to meat mixture, a little at a time. Add poultry seasoning.
Place in an uncooked pastry shell.
Add a top crust.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes or until brown.

title: super easy ice cream
directions: Mix together and pour into freezer.
Makes 1 gallon.
Can use strawberry pop and add frozen strawberries before freezing.

title: blonde toffee brownies
directions: Mix flour, baking powder and salt together with a fork.
Set aside.
Cream butter.
Add both sugars and cream well.
Add eggs and vanilla. Beat until fluffy.
Blend in dry ingredients.
Stir in crushed candy.
Spread in well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.
Cool and cut into bars.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Bring to a boil in pan margarine, water and cocoa.
In a large bowl mix sugar, flour, salt, vanilla, soda, eggs and sour cream. Pour pan mixture in with dry ingredients and mix.
Pour into a jelly roll pan and bake for 20 minutes.

title: corn casserole
directions: Grease a 1 1/2-quart casserole with cooking spray.
Mix all ingredients together and place in casserole.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.

title: boiled chocolate cookies
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Bring to a boil for 1 minute. Remove from heat.
Add next 3 ingredients; mix.
Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper.

title: grandma's drop fried cakes
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Drop by rounded teaspoonful into hot fat until golden brown.
Makes about 50.

title: sausage balls
directions: Form sausage into 100 (1-inch) balls and place on cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Drain on paper towels. Combine 1 pound sharp Cheddar cheese (softened or grated), margarine or butter, flour, salt and paprika. Wrap 2 tablespoons (No. 70 dipper) of dough around each sausage ball. Freeze at this point, if desired. Place on ungreased baking sheet. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: carrot cake(the best there is)
directions: Mix and sift the dry ingredients.
Add oil and stir well.
Add eggs, one at a time; beat well after each additional egg.
Stir in carrots.

title: cream cheese salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in water.
Cool.
Whip cream, add cream cheese, pineapple and nuts.
Stir in Jell-O.
Chill until firm.

title: punch with a holiday ring
directions: The day before your party, make the ring.
Cut 1 lemon and 1 lime into thin slices.
Remove seeds.
Arrange alternating slices of fruit in bottom of 3 1/2-cup ring mold.
Pour in enough crantastic or cran-orange to barely cover fruit.
Freeze until just set.
Now, add enough Ocean Spray to fill mold.
Freeze overnight. Refrigerate remainder of crantastic or cran-orange.

title: bobby's waffles
directions: Mix flour, baking soda and baking powder and set aside.
Beat egg whites until foamy and set aside.
Mix egg yolks, oil, vanilla and milk.
Gradually add flour mixture to egg mixture and beat for 3 minutes.
Gently fold in egg whites.
Pour 3/4 c. batter into prepared waffle iron.
Makes about 48 waffles.

title: crackling corn bread
directions: Add flour, corn meal, sugar, salt, baking powder, egg and milk.
Add cracklings.
Beat thoroughly.
Bake in well-oiled shallow pan in hot oven at 450° about 20 minutes or drop by teaspoonfuls on a hot well-oiled griddle.
Fry until golden brown. Makes 6 servings.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Mix thoroughly the bread crumbs, thyme, oregano, parsley, butter and wine.
Wash mushrooms, remove stems and chop them up fine.
Saute stems and caps in butter for 10 minutes.
Cool; set aside caps and mix stems with spices, crumbs and wine.
Fill the caps with the mixture and place on baking tin.
Broil until hot.

title: squash puppies
directions: Trim squash ends; slice and cover with water.
Cook 20 minutes over medium heat until tender.
Drain well.
Mash and drain again. Combine squash and next 5 ingredients.
Drop by scant tablespoon into 350° oil.
Fry 5 minutes.
This mixture can be refrigerated until next day if it makes too much.

title: meaty macaroni
directions: Cook hamburger in frying pan over medium heat for 10 minutes. Drain well. Add tomato sauce; mix well. Lower heat to simmer and cook 15 minutes. Cook macaroni following directions on package; drain well.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add molasses and egg.
Beat well. Stir in dry ingredients.
Rol into small balls.
Dip each ball in sugar and bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: homemade chili
directions: Brown and drain meat and onion.
Add flour, package of chili mix and chili powder.
Add all other ingredients.
Cook slowly for 1 hour.
Add beans in last 15 minutes.
Cook 1 1/2 hours total.

title: shoofly pie
directions: Mix molasses, water, baking soda, and salt together. In a separate bowl, mix flour, butter, and brown sugar; mix well.

You may need to use your hands. Pour 1/3 molasses mixture into pie crust; pour 1/3 flour mixture on top. Continue to alternate layer, ending with flour mixture on top. Bake the pie at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: champagne punch
directions: Combine.
Float pineapple sherbet scoops to decorate.
Makes approximately 20 servings.

title: mexican chef's salad
directions: Chop onion, tomatoes and lettuce.
Toss with cheese, dressing and hot sauce.
Crunch and add Doritos.
Slice and add avocado. Brown ground beef.
Add kidney beans and salt.
Simmer for 10 minutes and mix into cold salad.
Decorate with tortilla chips, avocado and tomato slices.

title: pork chops dijon
directions: Trim excess fat from chops.
In a bowl, combine salad dressing, Dijon mustard and pepper.
Brush both sides of chops with mixture.
In a 12-inch skillet, cook chops, covered, over medium-low heat for 20 minutes.
Turn chops.
Cook covered for 5 to 10 minutes more.
Makes 4 servings.

title: banana bread
directions: Beat eggs, mash bananas and mix all ingredients thoroughly. Pour into greased and floured loaf pan and bake 1 hour (or until toothpick in center comes out clean).
If using a glass pan, bake in 325° preheated oven. If using a metal pan, bake at 350° (preheated).
Makes 1 loaf.

title: spinach balls
directions: Drain moisture from frozen spinach.
Mix other ingredients together, then fold in spinach.
Roll into balls and freeze on cookie sheet.
When needed, bake frozen balls at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: corn scallop
directions: Saute onion, celery and carrots in butter.
Add remaining ingredients except cheese.	Spread in
an
x 8 x 2-inch pan. Bake in a 350° oven for about 40 minutes, or until light golden and set.
Top with	cheese	during	last
minutes of baking time.

title: fried bologna sandwich
directions: Put butter in frypan.
Fry bologna until curls up around edges.
Make toast.
Add cheese, mayo or butter.
Enjoy!

title: chewie bread
directions: In a large bowl, mix all ingredients with a spoon. Spread in a baking dish (greased). Cook at 325° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares. They get better when they are 2 or 3 days old; a great snack.

title: cheese popcorn
directions: Spread the popped corn in a flat pan, keeping it hot and crisp in the oven.
Melt the butter with the grated cheese in a pan, then add the salt.
Pour this mixture over the corn; stir until every corn is cheese-flavored.

title: chicken-n-rice casserole
directions: Mix soup, water, rice and dry onion soup mix together in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Lay chicken pieces on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: lo-fat fettuccine with fresh zucchini
directions: In large heavy saucepan, melt butter over low-medium heat. Add onion and cook 2 or 3 minutes.
Add milk and bring to boil for 2 or 3 minutes to thicken, stirring occasionally to avoid burning and boiling over.
Add thinly sliced zucchini and mushrooms; boil 3 or 4 minutes.

title: stuffed tomatoes
directions: Mix and stuff in hollowed tomatoes.

title: escalloped onions
directions: Cook onions in salted water until tender.
Drain and put in a buttered baking dish.
Make a white sauce with the butter, flour and salt.
Sprinkle with crumbs and melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes in preheated oven.

title: impossible quiche
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Lightly grease a 10-inch pie plate. Sprinkle bacon, onion and cheese in plate.
Beat milk, Bisquick, eggs, salt and pepper in medium bowl until smooth, about 1 minute. Pour into pie plate.
Bake in hot oven for 35 minutes or until top is golden brown.
Let stand 15 minutes.

title: baked chicken and artichokes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Put chicken in a baking dish.
Top with artichokes, mushrooms and onions.
Add artichoke liquid and white wine.
Bake for 45 minutes.

title: squash or eggplant dressing
directions: Boil squash or eggplant until tender.
Drain.
Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° until brown.

title: grandma's apple fritters
directions: Combine all ingredients into hot oil from tablespoon.
Cook for 2 minutes on each side.
Drain on paper towels.
Sprinkle with sugar.

title: sweet potato cream cheese cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream potatoes and sugar together.
Add milk, cinnamon, salt, whole eggs and egg yolks to mixture.
Stir well.
Add cream cheese and mix again.
Beat egg whites in a separate bowl and then fold into potato mixture.
Pour into crust and top with marshmallows.
Cook 30 to 40 minutes.

title: cherry delight
directions: Mix and chill.
Also may use peach pie filling, strawberry or blueberry pie filling.

title: chicken crescent casserole
directions: Mix first
8 ingredients together and place in a baking dish. Lay crescent roll on top (rolled out flat to form rectangle). Cover with grated cheese.
Drizzle with butter.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: potatoes crock-pot perfect
directions: Line crock-pot with foil, leaving enough to overlap potatoes while cooking.
Layer the ingredients in order listed.
Cook on low 10 to 12 hours or on high for 3 to 4 hours.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: crab stuffed sole
directions: Saute green onions, green pepper and mushrooms in wine. Drain.
Add crab.
Lay sole flat. Spread crab filling over each fillet. Roll and secure with toothpicks.
Pour lemon juice and 1/4 of the chicken broth over fish.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until fish flakes easily when tested with a fork. Transfer to a serving plate to keep warm.

title: grandma's potato salad
directions: Stir everything together in a large bowl and garnish with 1 sliced egg.

title: venison oven stew
directions: Mix raw meat and raw vegetables together and place into a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Blend seasoned salt and pepper into the tomato juice and pour over the meat/vegetable mixture.
Cover tightly with tinfoil and bake at 250° for 4 hours.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together until smooth and fluffy. Do not add any liquid to the pudding. Refrigerate. This will be light green.

title: hot tuna salad
directions: Mix together cooked noodles, cottage cheese, tuna, milk, onion, salt and pepper and place in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Top with crumbs and cheese.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: low-fat cavatini
directions: Cook ground turkey and bell pepper; drain.
Slice sausage like pepperoni.
Add sauce and sausage.
Simmer while cooking macaroni per package directions.
Pour sauce into large baking dish.
Drain macaroni; add to baking dish.
Add Mozzarella and stir; reserve some Mozzarella for the top.
Bake, uncovered, at 400° until bubbly, about 20 minutes.

title: buttermilk cake
directions: Sift the dry ingredients together, then add the Crisco, buttermilk, vanilla and eggs.
Bake in large loaf pan or large square pan at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: exotic chicken salad
directions: Brush chicken with butter, salt and pepper. Wrap and bake at 350° for 1 hour or you can boil the chicken. Cut into bite-sized pieces (should be about 2-quart). Coat almonds with butter. Put on cookie sheet and bake about 30 minutes (slightly brown). Spread on paper towels. Sprinkle with salt and set aside until just before serving. Mix mayonnaise, curry powder and soy sauce with 2 tablespoons of lemon juice. Combine with chicken, celery, chestnuts, grapes and pineapple chunks. Chill. Arrange lettuce leaves on plate. Put chicken on lettuce and sprinkle with almonds. Serve with any crackers you like.
(I have never used 2 cups of mayonnaise. Use ingredients according to your taste. More of one and less of another.)

title: broccoli and cheese casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix in broccoli.
Pour in casserole dish and cover.
Cook 30 minutes at 350°.
Remove cover and top with dried onions.
Cook 15 minutes uncovered.

title: puppy chow
directions: Pour Crispix in a large bowl.
Melt chips and peanut butter together.
Pour over the cereal and mix well.
Then coat all this with powdered sugar.

title: grandma's pound cake(makes 20 servings)
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour a 10-inch tube pan.
In large bowl of electric mixer, beat butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs 2 at a time, beating until very light and fluffy.
Add flour and flavorings all at once.
Stir in gently just until well combined.
Turn into prepare pan.
Bake until a toothpick inserted in the center comes out clean, 80 to 90 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes in pan.
Remove from pan and cool on a wire rack.

title: barbecue and biscuit cups
directions: Brown hamburger; add barbecue sauce, brown sugar and onion. Place 1 biscuit in a muffin tin; press out to form cup. Spoon meat mixture into cups. Top with cheese. Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes. Makes 10 to 12.

title: french bread
directions: Soften active dry yeast in 1/4 cup warm water.
To remaining water, add sugar, shortening and salt.
Add 1 cup flour; beat well.
Add yeast mixture and egg whites; mix.
Add remaining flour to make soft dough.
Knead until smooth and satiny.
Place in greased bowl, turning once to grease surface.
Cover and let rise until double in bulk.
Punch down.
When again doubled, divide in half.
Shape into loaves.
Let sit 10 minutes.
Place on greased cookie sheet sprinkled with white corn meal.
Cover; let double. Brush with egg yolk diluted with water.
Bake in hot (400°) oven for 30 minutes.
Place large flat pan of boiling water on floor of oven to give crustiness.

title: chili cheese appetizers
directions: Melt butter in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Beat eggs slightly.
Add flour, salt and baking powder. Blend.
Add melted butter, chilies and cheeses.
Mix only until blended.
Return to baking pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 400°. Reduce heat to 350° and bake 35 minutes longer.
Cool and slice into bite size squares.

title: layered mexican dip
directions: Peel and mash avocados until creamy; mix with a little lemon juice.
Spread layers in the order listed in a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts and all layers have been heated.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: green bean pilaf
directions: Finely chop onion.
Melt butter in a pan.
Add onion; cook until translucent, stirring as needed.

title: cheater's chili
directions: Brown hamburger and onions; drain.
Add onion, kidney beans, tomatoes and chili seasoning mix (1/2 package) or more if you want spicy.
Simmer 1 hour and serve with Jiffy corn bread!

title: leek and zucchini flan
directions: Preparation time: 25 minutes.
Cooking time: 40 minutes.

title: strawberry divinity
directions: Combine sugar, syrup and water in saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring until sugar dissolves.
Cook to hard ball stage.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Cut heads of broccoli into bite size pieces.
Add crumbled bacon, onions and raisins.
Mix together mayonnaise, vinegar and sugar.
Pour over salad.
Toss well and refrigerate for several hours or overnight.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.
Chill 6 hours or overnight.

title: mexican wedding cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add all other ingredients in the order given.
Make into small balls.
Place on cookie sheet; chill in refrigerator for 15 minutes.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Roll in powdered sugar while hot, then again when cooled.

title: pink velvet pie
directions: Mix graham crackers with butter and line deep 9-inch pie plate, saving 1/4 cup of mixture for topping.
Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Add lemon juice and sugar and let stand while whipping Carnation milk to a stiff froth.
Add gelatin mixture to whipped milk and continue whipping until stiff peak forms.
Stir in lemon rind.
Pour in crust.
Top with remaining crumbs.
Chill 4 hours or until firm.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: lemon coconut danties
directions: Cream the butter and sugar until light and fluffy. Beat in egg, vanilla and lemon extract.
Blend in flour and coconut. Shape into walnut size balls.
Place on baking sheet. Flatten with fork. Bake in moderate 350° oven for 8 minutes until edges are brown. Remove cookies to cooling rack. When cool, frost with lemon butter frosting.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: pork chops in sour cream
directions: Brown chops in oil. Mix bouillon cubes in 1 cup hot water. Mix bouillon broth, mushrooms, mustard, parsley, paprika, salt and pepper.
Separate onion into rings.
Place on top of chops.
Pour mixture over this.
Simmer on low for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Add sour cream and simmer 15 more minutes.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: jumbles
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat butter and sugars until light and fluffy.
Add egg. Combine flour and soda.
Blend into creamed mixture.
Stir in M&M's, raisins and nuts. Drop rounded tablespoonfuls onto greased baking sheet, about 2-inches apart. Bake 13 to 15 minutes. Cool 2 to 3 minutes on baking sheet.
Store in tight containers.
Yields approximately 32 cookies.

title: shrimp seashell macaroni
directions: Combine mayonnaise, sour cream, sauce, salt and pepper.
Add macaroni and shrimp.
Best if chilled 24 hours before serving.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Combine shrimp and rest of ingredients; add mayonnaise (Hellmann's is best), salt and pepper.
Mix all together and refrigerate.

title: cheese straws
directions: Sift flour and baking powder into bowl.
Cut in cheese, butter and pepper.
Add water and mix well.
Work out on floured board. Shape or cut into straws.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: phyllis' cheese bread
directions: Mix together the flour, yeast, salt, sugar and Crisco; mix well.
Add water to make a dough; knead well.
Let rise 1 hour. Knead again; make 2 balls with dough.
Sprinkle with flour; let stand for 1/2 hour.
Roll out on floured board 1 inch thick; spread butter all over.
Add grated cheese all over and fold in dough, making sure the ends are tucked in.
Place on a greased baking sheet; bake at 375° until light brown.

title: party mix
directions: Mix last 3 ingredients.
Heat but do not boil mix.
Pour over cereal mix and toss well.

title: snow kisses
directions: Beat egg whites until almost stiff.
Add sugar very slowly, beating until very stiff peaks are formed.
Carefully fold in ground nuts, then chocolate chips.
Drop by teaspoon onto slightly greased cookie sheet.
Put into a 350° oven.
Turn heat off at once.
Do not open oven door for at least 4 hours; better still, next morning.
Makes about 40 cookies.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Make a well and beat in eggs. Add bananas, sour cream, lemon juice.
Stir together with dry ingredients.
Fold in nuts.
Grease two bread loaf pans, put in waxed paper cut to fit bottom and grease paper also.
Bake at 350° F. for 40 minutes.
Can be frozen.

title: hawaiian bread
directions: Combine all ingredients in order given.
Bake 1 hour at 325° in 2 greased loaf pans.
Half of recipe fills two (7 x 3 x 2-inch) pans.
Spread.
Bread freezes well.

title: delores' favorite apple pie
directions: Roll out 1/2 of pastry; fit into 9-inch pie pan.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Pour into pie shell.
Roll out other 1/2 of pastry and put over filling.
Flute edges.
Cut several slits near center. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until golden and juices bubble up through slits.

title: darrell's stir-fried asparagus
directions: Wash and trim asparagus; cut into bite size pieces. Heat butter or oil in skillet. Add asparagus, stirring constantly until all pieces are well coated. Add water and cook 3 to 5 minutes. Season and serve immediately. Delicious sprinkled with olive oil and balsamic vinegar.

title: fruity sundaes
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add cold water and chill in bowl until set.
Alternately spoon ice cream and jello into 4 tall sundae glasses, ending with jello, filling to within 1/2-inch of top.
Top with sauce, Cool Whip, nuts and cherries.
Serve at once.

title: buttermilk salad
directions: Combine buttermilk, Cool Whip and pudding together.
Add all ingredients together; refrigerator until ready to serve.
Chill well.
Crumble chocolate striped cookies (1 pound) and add just before serving.
Very good.

title: mock apple pie
directions: Bring first 3 ingredients to boil.
Drop in about 25 Ritz crackers.
Simmer 2 minutes.
Do not stir.
Add cinnamon to taste and slice of butter.
Pour into pie shell and add top crust.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: cantaloupe meringue pie
directions: Scoop out cantaloupe.
Mash in double boiler.
Add sugar, cornstarch and slightly beaten egg yolks.
Cook over boiling water, stirring constantly.
Cool; pour into pie shell.
Beat egg whites until frothy; add the 6 tablespoons sugar and lemon juice gradually, beating until stiff peak consistency.
Spread meringue over pie.
Bake at 350° until meringue is browned.

title: jeff davis pie
directions: Pour in unbaked crust (8-inch) and bake at 450° for 10 minutes, then 325° for 30 minutes.

title: cucumber soup
directions: Cook cucumbers, onion and seasoning together until tender. Add oleo and milk.
Heat to serve.

title: out-of-this-world nut cake
directions: Cream the margarine and sugar together. Add eggs; beat well. Add cracker crumbs, nuts and coconut.
Stir in baking powder, then add milk; mix well. Butter and flour four 9-inch cake pans. Divide batter among them.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.

title: crme-de-menthe brownies
directions: Bake brownies as directed. Beat room temperature butter with confectioners sugar and crme-de-menthe in a large bowl with an electric mixer until smooth. Spread over brownies.

title: caramel pie
directions: Combine sugar and flour. Add milk and egg yolks. Cook until thick. Remove from heat; add caramelized sugar. Beat as you add the hot sugar. Cook until mixture is smooth. Add butter and vanilla. Pour into baked pie shell. Put meringue on top and brown lightly.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Mix together sugar, Karo syrup and salt.
Cook on high 5 minutes.
Add peanuts and cook 4 minutes more, stirring halfway through.
Take from microwave and add vanilla, butter and soda. Stir until fluffy.
Pour onto a greased baking sheet.
Spread and work out as smooth as possible.
Use only a glass bowl.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Soften cream cheese; add all the other ingredients, except shrimp.
Mix well, then add shrimp.
Chill well.

title: hors d'oeuvre meatballs
directions: Mix beef, sausage, breadcrumbs, egg and milk and make into small meatballs.
Bake on cookie sheet at 325° for 15 minutes. Remove from cookie sheet and drain on paper towels.
Mix chili sauce, grape jelly and lemon juice and bring to boil in saucepan. Pour over meatballs and simmer 1 hour.
Can be put in crock-pot on low for several hours.

title: grandma cole's tea cakes
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and extracts; beat well.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Chill for 1/2 hour.
Shape into 1 1/4-inch balls.
Place 2 1/2 inches apart on lightly greased baking sheets.
Bake at 375° for 11 to 13 minutes or until lightly browned (do not overbake).
Cool 1 minute on pan before removing to a wire rack.
Makes 5 1/2 dozen. Cookies can be frozen in heavy-duty bags or airtight containers.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Melt oleo; cool.
Add sugar and mix well.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Sift
together
flour, salt, baking powder and soda. Add to sugar
and oleo.
Mix well and pour into a buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle
chocolate
chips on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Beat sugar and eggs.
Add pumpkin and spices.
Mix, add milk, stir thoroughly.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes to 1 hour or until set.

title: sunshine salad
directions: Mix jello by directions on the box.
Add pineapple, sliced bananas and marshmallows.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: asparagus and chicken bundles
directions: With a kitchen scissors, cut up the chicken breasts into about 6-inch strips.
Count the number of asparagus you have; for example, if you have 24 asparagus and 12 strips of chicken breast, you will use 2 asparagus for each strip of chicken.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Butter a casserole dish.
Mix all together and bake at 425° for 40 minutes.

title: karl's potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients except 1/2 cube of margarine and corn flakes.
Pour mixture into rectangular pan.
Pour 1/2 cube margarine (melted) over the corn flakes.
Place the corn flake mixture over the potatoes.
Bake at 350° for one hour, uncovered.

title: texas salad
directions: Shred lettuce. Chop the tomatoes and onion. Combine everything and serve.

title: cousin ruby's easy sweet potato pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into a pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes, until done.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: First, melt one tablespoon butter in bottom of casserole dish. Salt and pepper chops.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Melt oleo, then cook oleo, milk, sugar and cocoa for about 1 minute.
Then add peanut butter, vanilla and oatmeal.
Remove from heat; mix well.
Then drop on wax paper or greased cookie sheets.

title: mafe(ma-fa)
directions: Chop onion and mix peanut butter with water until fluffy, dilute tomato paste until same volume as peanut butter.
Brown meat quickly in hot oil in large skillet.
Add onions and stir until they are partly cooked not browned.
Add diluted tomato paste and peanut butter and spices.
Stir.
Taste for seasoning.
Cook over low heat approximately 45 minutes or until meat is tender, stirring frequently.
Serve immediately over plain rice.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: escarole and beans soup
directions: Bring water, broth and salt to boil.
Add greens, garlic and pepper.
Boil and simmer for 45 minutes.
Add beans.
Simmer another 10 minutes.
Serve with grated cheese and Italian bread.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt chocolate chips and margarine, then melt in peanut butter well.
Pour mixture over cereal in a very large bowl.
Stir gently to coat cereal.
In a large bag, toss coated cereal with confectioners sugar.
(You'll make a mess, but it's worth it!)

title: ham and herb vegetable dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and beat until smooth and creamy. Refrigerate 1 to 2 hours before serving.
Makes 1 2/3 cups.

title: fluffy bakeshop icing
directions: Mix milk with cornstarch.
Cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Set aside to cool.
Cream vegetable shortening, oleo and sugar.
Beat with electric mixer for 10 full minutes.
Combine second mixture with first.
Add vanilla and beat both together until creamy.
It will look like whipped cream.
Put on cooled cake.

title: chicken piccata
directions: Cut chicken into 1 1/2 x 1/2-inch strips.
Toss chicken in combined flour, salt and pepper.
Add oil and margarine to hot wok.
Stir-fry chicken in very hot oil for 3 to 4 minutes, until done.
Drain oil.
Add wine and lemon juice to wok.
Cook down slightly and pour over chicken.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix by hand.
Do not use electric mixer.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add apples and nuts.
Combine eggs, oil and vanilla; add to apple mixture.
Pour into greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: almond tea
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Stir until sugar dissolves.
Serve over ice.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix ingredients and layer in buttered pan (rice, chicken, rice).
Bake at 300° for 2 hours.

title: dumplins
directions: Sift the flour, baking powder and salt together.
Combine egg and milk and add to dry ingredients.
Stir together lightly.
Drop by spoonfuls on top of boilings stews, meats, vegetables or sauerkraut.
Cover utensil tightly and steam 15 to 20 minutes on top of burner without lifting cover, or cover and bake in the oven at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: fruited cabbage salad
directions: Combine cabbage, pineapple,
pear,
apple and grapes in bowl; toss to mix.
Mix yogurt, vinegar, honey and celery seed in small bowl.
Pour
over
cabbage	mixture;
toss	to
coat. Chill. Cover for 1 hour or longer.
Add banana; toss lightly. Enjoy.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix and form into balls.
Melt chocolate almond bark and roll balls
into melted chocolate.

title: creamy seafood chowder
directions: In a heavy saucepan saut onion, celery, ham, carrots and thyme in butter until vegetables are tender. Add water, pasta and contents of seasoning packet; bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer 12 minutes, stirring often. Add clams and simmer 2 to 3 minutes longer. Season to taste with salt and pepper.

title: sourdough bread starter
directions: Let set out for 8 hours every time you feed it.
Take out 1 cup of starter even if you are not baking bread.

title: molded salad(sugar-free)
directions: Mix Jell-Os in large bowl and let set until "soft set" in refrigerator.
Whip until "frothy".
Add pineapple last and stir well.
Pour into mold or 9 x 13-inch pan.
Refrigerate until set. Unmold or cut into 3 x 3-inch servings.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut biscuits in half.
Roll
into
ball
can
at
a time). Roll ball in
melted
margarine
and then in sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Stack in a greased tube pan.
Put pecans on top of each layer.
Bake at 375° for about 1 hour.

title: homemade donuts
directions: Open biscuits and put your thumb in the center.
Have a very hot pan of Crisco shortening. Carefully put your biscuits in the Crisco. Turn over as soon as they brown slightly. Take out immediately with fork or spoon.
Put in glaze; spoon all over. Take out and place on a plate, then eat!!

title: mama's pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco.
Blend in baking powder, vanilla, lemon and milk.
Add eggs and flour.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours in a greased and floured Bundt pan.

title: reuben casserole
directions: In large bowl, put croutons and melted oleo; toss gently. Add hot water, sauerkraut and caraway seeds.
Set aside 1 cup of the mixture for later.
Grease casserole dish; layer crouton mixture, corned beef slices and cheese slices.
End up with the crouton mixture which was set aside.
Cover; bake in a 350° oven for 20 minutes.
Top with the 2 slices of cheese, then bake, uncovered, 10 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: clam, corn casserole
directions: Drain liquid from clams into a cup and fill with milk. Combine with beaten eggs.
Combine with rest of ingredients and pour into greased casserole.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until firm.
Serves 6.

title: pumpkin squares
directions: Grease a 13 x 9-inch pan; reserve 1 cup cake mix.
Combine remaining cake mix with melted butter and egg; mix well.
Dough will be dry and crumbly; press into bottom of pan.
In another bowl, mix pumpkin pie mix, 2 eggs and milk.
Pour over crust, combine reserve cake mix, sugar, cinnamon and butter.
Mixture should be crumbly.
If not, mix a small amount of flour.
Layer over pumpkin mixture.
Put in preheated 375° oven for 50 minutes. To serve, cut into squares.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: chewy bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 8 x 8-inch pan.
In small bowl, blend all ingredients well.
Spread in prepared pan.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool and cut into bars.

title: dairy cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and egg until light and fluffy. Sift dry
ingredients
and add alternately with buttermilk or sour milk.
Add	the chopped nuts.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes in a 375° oven.

title: irish cream
directions: Blend all of the ingredients in a blender until smooth.
Pour into bottles.
Will keep in refrigerator for 1 month.

title: bubble recipe
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Allow foam to subside before using.
Tends to produce longer lasting bubbles as the mixture ages.
Enjoy.

title: hot apple punch
directions: Heat red hots in apple juice to dissolve.
Add pineapple juice.
Serve hot.
Yields 40 servings.

title: shish kabob
directions: Cut listed ingredients and put into 9 x 13-inch baking pan. Melt 2 cubes butter on low heat in saucepan.
Pour over veggies and meat.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Broil for 30 minutes.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown onion and meat. Drain fat if necessary.
Mix in rest of ingredients except tortillas and cheese.
Layer half of the tortillas in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with half of the meat mixture.
Make second layer. Cover with cheese. Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken and spaghetti
directions: Boil fryer with garlic salt, pepper, onion, bell pepper and celery.
Remove from broth when done and debone.
Add spaghetti to broth; cook until nearly all broth is absorbed.
Add chicken pieces, Velveeta cheese and about 1/2 can or jar jalapeno Cheez Whiz, if desired.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Thez ugly ole varmits iz gud but you gotta cook az much fat az you kin outta them 'r yo' mouth will be kivered in fever blisters!

title: jo's carrot cake
directions: Mix together flour, sugar and salad oil in a large bowl (mixing by hand).
Add the beaten eggs and mix well.
Add all the other ingredients and mix well after each addition.
Pour batter into a well-greased 10-inch tube pan and bake in a preheated oven at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
About 15 minutes before the cake is ready to come out of the oven, start putting together the Buttermilk Topping. Pour the topping over the cake as soon as you take it out of the oven.
Allow the cake to stand in the pan for 3 to 4 hours.
Remove from pan and serve.

title: crisco pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening well.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Gradually add flour, milk and flavoring.
After mixing well, bake at 325° in a 10-inch tube pan for 1 1/2 hours.

title: pear and apple crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 425°. In shallow, 2-quart baking dish, combine pear slices and pie filling. In medium bowl, with fork, stir together oats, flour, sugar and cinnamon. With fingertips, mix in butter until mixture resembles coarse crumbs. Crumble topping over fruit. Place baking dish on cookie sheet and bake 30 to 35 minutes or until topping is lightly browned and filling is hot and bubbling. Cool crisp slightly on wire rack to serve warm. Serve with whipped cream or ice cream if you like.

title: kahlua pecan brie
directions: In medium skillet, combine brown sugar and Kahlua. Heat, stirring constantly until blended. Add pecans, simmer until hot, but not runny. Remove from heat. Place brie on microwave safe serving plate and spoon warm pecan mixture over top. Microwave on high 1-2 minutes, or until cheese softens.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix the peanut butter, 10x sugar and vanilla together.
Roll into balls.
Put bar wax and chocolate chips in double boiler. Roll each ball, one at a time, then put on wax paper.
Put in refrigerator.

title: squash casserole
directions: Saute squash, bell pepper, onion and butter until tender.
Mix together sour cream, cream of mushroom soup, Cheddar cheese, pimento and cornbread stuffing.
Add to squash mixture.
Top with remaining stuffing.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes.

title: easy cinnamon buns
directions: Combine hot water, yeast and 1 teaspoon sugar.
Mix until dissolved; set aside.
Combine 3 1/2 c. hot water, margarine, 1 cup sugar and salt.
Mix until melted.
Cool to lukewarm and add to yeast mixture.
Beat in enough flour to make a thick, but still sticky dough, not stiff enough to knead.
Place in greased bowl, grease top, and let rise until double in size.
Sprinkle flour on counter and roll dough into a rectangle 8 x 42-inches, 1/2-inch thick.
Spread 1/3 cup melted butter over dough.
Mix 2 1/2 cups brown sugar, 1 1/2 tablespoon ground cinnamon and 3/4 cup chopped nuts (optional) and sprinkle over dough.
Roll up like a jelly roll and cut into 1-inch slices.
Place in 6 (8 or 9-inch) cake pans. Let rise until double again.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes until lightly browned.
Do not overbake.

title: seven layer cookies
directions: Melt oleo in an oblong cake pan; layer ingredients in order given.
Spoon milk over top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: pat's pound cake
directions: Combine butter and oil.
Add sugar, then eggs.
Add all flavorings and milk.
Combine flour and baking powder.
Stir into butter, sugar and egg mixture.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt or angel food cake pan.
Cook at 300° for 1 hour to 1 1/2 hours.
Check after 1 hour.
Cake is done when toothpick comes out clean.

title: green pepper jelly
directions: Combine all ingredients, except Certo, in saucepan; bring to a boil.
Continue boiling for 5 minutes.
Take off stove and add Certo.
Pour into sterilized jars and seal.

title: carob balls
directions: Cook carob powder and honey in top of double boiler; stir 10 minutes.
Mix next 5 ingredients together.
Stir both mixtures together in a bowl.
If too stiff, add water.
Form into little balls.
Roll balls in coconut or cracked nuts.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl.
Stir until just blended.
Pour into a nonstick 12-cup fluted tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center of cake comes out clean.
Cool 10 minutes.
Invert onto a wire rack or serving platter.

title: apple fritters
directions: Mix together dry ingredients and combine with egg, vanilla and white sugar, stirred together.
Add enough milk to make it the thinness of thick pancake batter.
Drop into hot (375° to 400°) oil or fat with tablespoon dipped into oil to avoid sticking to the spoon.
Turn fritters over in oil repeatedly to brown evenly, about 9 or 10 minutes frying time or until browned.
Roll in powdered sugar.
Oven frying causes toughness.
Makes several dozen.

title: grits casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large saucepan, bring the water to a boil.
Add garlic powder, salt and pepper.
Gradually stir in grits.
Lower heat and simmer, stirring occasionally, for 5 minutes.
Remove pan from heat.
Stir in butter and 1 cup cheese until melted.
Mix eggs with milk; stir into grits.

title: island chicken and rice
directions: Sprinkle chicken with salt, pepper and 1 tablespoon cornstarch.
Brown chicken and onions in oil until lightly brown. Blend peach juice, soy sauce, vinegar and remaining cornstarch; pour over chicken.
Cook, stirring constantly, until clear and thickened.
Add peaches, green pepper and tomatoes.
Simmer until green pepper is tender.
Serve over rice; sprinkle almonds on top. Makes 6 servings.

title: light and fruity pie
directions: Dissolve gelatin completely in boiling water, stirring 3 minutes.
Add ice cubes and stir constantly until gelatin is thickened (2 to 3 minutes).
Remove any unmelted ice.
Using a wire whip, blend in whipped topping, then whip until smooth. Chill until mixture is stiff.
Put in pie shell; chill for 2 hours or freeze until firm.

title: apple bites
directions: Cut apples into chunks.
Roll in mayonnaise, then roll in crisp chopped bacon or chopped nuts or grated cheese.
Serve with toothpick.

title: sausage and egg brunch
directions: Mix eggs, milk, salt and dry mustard.
Pour over bread.
Top with cheese.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake in morning for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: fabulous turkey sandwich roll
directions: Roll out pizza crust to an 11 x 10-inch rectangle.
Combine mustard, 1/2 teaspoon caraway seed and garlic powder.
Spread on dough. Top with turkey and cheese.
Roll dough up from short end (jelly roll style).
Pinch ends together to seal.
Fold ends under.
Brush top of dough with water and sprinkle with remaining caraway seed.
Cut 3 small steam vents on top.
Place on a greased baking sheet.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 30 minutes or until golden brown. Cut into slices to serve.

title: barbecue shrimp
directions: Melt butter.
Mix all ingredients together in a ziploc bag, add peeled shrimp, seal and shake. Let shrimp stay in bag until ready to place on grill (about an hour or more)
Then put shrimp on skewers and grill.
Usually a big hit!!!

title: seafood and grapefruit salad
directions: Cook shrimp in boiling salt water until pink, 2 to 4 minutes. Drain, cool, peel and devein.
Chill.
Peel grapefruit with paring knife, cutting right down to flesh to remove all white pith. Working over a bowl to catch all juice, cut the sections away from the membrane, to leave pure fruit.
Arrange lettuce leaves on plate.
Put a mound of crab meat on one side, slightly off center, then arrange shrimp and grapefruit sections alternately placed around crab meat on one side of plate.
(Divide number of shrimp up evenly to accommodate 4 servings.)

title: fruit crunch
directions: Mix together first three ingredients; press into sheet pan. Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: oven chicken salad
directions: Mix preceding ingredients and place in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: cinnamon-sour cream cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour Bundt cake pan.

title: roasted pecans
directions: Roast pecan halves in a
shallow
pan
40 minutes.
Stir every 10 minutes.
Add mixture
dissolved
on pecans.
Stir and mix well.
Put back in oven for 20 minutes.
Stir 2 times, then add a dash of salt.
Stir
well.
Back
in oven for 20 minutes. Leave oven door cracked open
for 20 minutes with oven temperature at 130° at all times.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Combine sugar, syrup, water and salt in a heavy saucepan. Bring to a full boil (soft ball stage, 238°) and add peanuts. Cook until nuts snap and syrup begins to turn color.
Add butter and vanilla.
Cook until amber color and continue cooking slowly to 300°, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat and add baking soda, stirring well.
Pour immediately onto buttered hard surface.

title: zeppoli
directions: Mix all together to a dumpling-like consistency.
Drop by tablespoons into oil; turn once.
Test inside for doneness.

title: strawberry whip
directions: Soften cream cheese and beat with beaters. Slowly add the milk, then the sugar. While still beating, add the lemon juice.

title: ice cream oranges
directions: Cut oranges in half.
Scoop out the insides with a spoon. Discard stringy bits and seeds; save juice and pulp.
Melt 4 large scoops of vanilla ice cream.
Mix pulp and juice together with the melted ice cream.
Pour back into orange halves.
Freeze 2 to 3 hours.

title: sloppy joes(yields 4 servings)
directions: Saute onion and celery in oil until tender and transparent. Add beef and brown; drain excess oil.
Add remaining ingredients except water and mix.
Simmer uncovered about 1 1/2 hours.
Add water, as needed.
Freezes well!
Enjoy!

title: sugarless apple pie
directions: Combine juice, cornstarch, cinnamon and salt.
Heat in saucepan until thickened.
Add sliced apples and simmer until apples are tender.
Be very careful not to burn.
Pour into an unbaked crust and cover with top crust.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pralines
directions: Mix
and
stir over low heat, stirring constantly until sugar is	dissolved.
Continue
cooking
over low heat to soft ball stage.
Add
pecans and beat with a wooden spoon until it begins to	thicken,
then	drop
rapidly
by teaspoonfuls on a sheet of foil or wax paper.

title: steak supper in foil
directions: Place foil in 9 x 13-inch pan or baking dish.
Place round steak on foil.
Mix soup and soup mix.
Spread on steak.
Top with vegetables.
Sprinkle water on vegetables.
Close foil.
Bake at 450° until tender, about 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: vanessa's punch
directions: Mix sugar and Jell-O with 2 cups boiling water.
Add pineapple juice,
cold water, orange juice and lemonade.
Slice strawberries in a plastic mold.
Add part of the punch mixture into mold and freeze.
To serve place frozen mold in punch bowl; fill punch bowl 1/2 to 3/4 full of punch mixture then add ginger ale.
This makes a dark pink color.
Use a different color Jell-O to change the color.

title: spaghetti  supreme
directions: Melt butter in fry pan, add mushroom and tomato soup and milk. Season with salt and pepper and mix with.
Pour in casserole. Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: holiday wreath
directions: Combine marshmallows, butter, vanilla and food color; heat (double boiler is best) until melted.
Stir in corn flakes.
Drop onto waxed paper.
Shape into wreath(s).
Decorate with small red candies (for large wreath use candied cherries and silver dragees).

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook and drain macaroni.
Melt margarine and add flour.
Cook over low heat until thick.
Slowly add milk.
Bring to boil; take off heat and cool.
Add cheese; stir until blended.
Layer macaroni and cheese sauce.
Bake at 350° until browned on top.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Cream together peanut butter and margarine; add powdered sugar.
Roll into balls.
Mother tells me to always wash my hands; dip in chocolate mixture.

title: banana applesauce-nut bread
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar and mix.
Add applesauce, banana and nuts; stir.
Add flour and soda; mix well.
Bake in greased bread pan for 50 to 60 minutes.
Bake at 325°.

title: "fried" turkey
directions: Put turkey in dish and cover with enough soy mixture so there isn't any turkey sticking out.
Allow to soak in refrigerator at least 18 hours.
When ready to eat, heat pan and spray with Pam. Brown each side for 2 to 3 minutes.
Serve.

title: cream of chicken bisque
directions: Mix butter and flour in skillet over low heat.
Stir until smooth and bubbling.
Add broth, salt, onion and celery.
Stir until creamy.
