Cover; cook over low heat for 15 minutes.
Stir to prevent lumping.
Strain liquid into pot.
Add milk, chicken and garlic powder; cook until creamy.
Stir in sherry.
Do not boil after egg and wine have been added.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or longer until juice is cooked low or mostly gone.

title: microwave caramel corn
directions: Combine brown sugar, oleo, syrup and salt in 1-quart bowl. Microwave on Full power for 30 seconds; stir and microwave for 1 minute; stir and microwave for 2 1/2 minutes then stir in soda. Put popped corn in large bowl.
Pour sauce over corn and stir until well mixed.
Microwave for 2 minutes and 20 seconds, stirring every 30 seconds.
Cool, stirring occasionally and break apart.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown ground meat and season with pepper, garlic and taco seasoning.
Drain and cool.
Chop fine lettuce, onion, carrot and olives.
Add cheese.
Mix salad dressing and mayonnaise.
Add just before serving.
Also add tomatoes.
Toss lightly.
Add 1 bag of taco Doritos (crushed).
Serve.

title: chicken stew
directions: Boil chicken; debone and put back into stock.
Add onion to chicken broth and cook until tender.
Add salt, pepper and soup; bring to a boil.
Add milk and heat until warm; do not boil. Serve with saltine crackers.

title: black bottom frozen dessert
directions: Combine cookie crumbs and oleo; press into bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan and freeze.
Soften the ice cream and spread on frozen crust and freeze.
Combine milk, sugar and chocolate.
Microwave until thick (at least 15 minutes).
On stove, cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until a thick sauce is formed (about 20 minutes).
Cool mixture.

title: fudge scotch squares
directions: Blend together the graham cracker crumbs and milk.
Add chocolate and butterscotch chips and walnuts.
Press into well-greased, 9 x 9 x 2-inch square pan.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Spray 9x11 dish with pam. Mix all ingredients and pour into pan. Bake 400° until brown.

title: hard teething biscuits
directions: Break eggs into a bowl and stir until creamy.
Add sugar and continue to stir.
Gradually add enough flour to make a stiff dough.
Roll out between two sheets of lightly floured wax paper to about 3/4-inch thickness.
Cut into shapes with metal type cookie cutters.
Place on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Let it stand overnight (10 to 12 hours).
Bake at 325° until browned and hard.
This will make approximately 12 durable and almost crumb-free teething biscuits.

title: potato turbet
directions: Brown ground meat and season with salt and pepper to taste. Drain.
Add onion and green pepper to meat and cook tender.
Boil and mash potatoes.
Make layer of ground meat in bottom of ungreased casserole dish.
Pour 1 can creamed corn over meat. Spoon mashed potatoes on top of corn.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes until potatoes are browned.
Serves 5.

title: red lobster cheese rolls
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Mix Bisquick, water and cheese.
Drop by large spoonfuls on greased baking sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes. Combine melted butter with garlic salt and seasonings to taste. While hot brush tops with butter mixture.

title: cucumber relish
directions: Grind cucumbers and onions.
Mix 1/2 cup salt to 3 quarts water and let stand overnight.
Next day, drain off water.
Cook 10 minutes.
Place in jars and seal.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix flour, baking powder, baking soda, cinnamon, salt and sugar together; blend well.
Add salad oil, eggs and pumpkin.
Bake in a 10 x 16-inch pan for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: creamy vanilla ice cream
directions: When ice cream maker is finished, remove mixer blades but leave container in ice for 20 minutes, then serve.

title: teriyaki sauce
directions: Combine ingredients and marinate meat overnight, or marinate 2 to 3 hours before cooking.
Broil or stove-top grill or use on outdoor grill.
Turn once.
This sauce is good for 1 to 1 1/2 pounds of meat.
This sauce may be used for marinating steaks, chicken, pork or fish.

title: sweet and sour slaw
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients in bowl, set aside.
In another bowl, mix remaining ingredients.
Pour over slaw mix.
Chill 2 hours before serving.
Will keep in refrigerator 1 week.

title: chocolate no bake cookies
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa and milk in a 2 quart saucepan.
Add butter and heat over medium high heat to a boil.
Boil and stir for 3 to 4 minutes.
Remove from heat, stir in vanilla.
Add oatmeal and mix.
Drop small blobs onto waxed paper and let cool.
Takes about 1 hour to fully set.

title: first-time fried rabbit
directions: To do this you must not know how to cut up a rabbit.

title: crock-pot potato soup(club member: amanda speed)
directions: In crock-pot, pour in diluted soup. Spread evenly sliced cheese and layer on top. Cover and start cooking on high.

Peel potatoes and dice. Put in large pan on stove top. Dice onion; add to potatoes and cover with water. Cook until potatoes are soft. Pour potatoes, onions and water into crock-pot. Stir and cover. Cook for 1 1/2 hours.

title: buckeye candy
directions: Melt oleo.
Add sugar and peanut butter.
Mix and form into balls.
Chill.
Melt chocolate bits and paraffin.
Dunk balls into chocolate, using a toothpick or corsage pin, leaving 1/2 of the ball bare to look like a buckeye.
Chill on wax paper.

title: potato soup
directions: In a 3-quart saucepan, combine first 9 ingredients.
Bring to boiling, reduce heat, cover and simmer until vegetables are tender, about 15 to 20 minutes.
Add 3 1/2 cups milk; heat soup just until milk is hot.
Blend flour with the 1/2 cup of milk. Stir into soup.
Cook, stirring constantly until thick and bubbly. Add butter or oleo.
Very good.

title: corn casserole
directions: Saute onion, bell pepper and celery in the butter until the onion begins to become transparent.
Add rest of ingredients and mix well.
Pour into greased baking dish and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: aunt elizabeth's casserole
directions: In a large skillet, brown ground beef and onion.
Drain off excess
liquid
and
add
remaining
ingredients,
except cheese. Pour
into a 2-quart casserole and bake 30 minutes at 350°. Remove
from oven and top with cheese.
Allow cheese to melt before serving.

title: pork chop stew
directions: In skillet, brown pork chops.
In large pot, layer vegetables, starting with potatoes, peppers, onions and celery.
Repeat until all vegetables are in the pot.
Place browned pork chops on the top.
Pour in tomato juice.
Add salt and Tabasco sauce.
Cover and cook over low heat until vegetables are tender, about 2 1/2 hours.

title: dried beef dip
directions: Mix cream cheese and sour cream until smooth.
Add milk, parsley, onion and beef.
Chill.
Serve with crackers.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter and Crisco.
Add sugar, one cup at a time, followed by two eggs at the time, and mix well on #7 (mixer speed) after each addition.
Reduce speed to #4.
Add flour and milk alternately (4 parts) and mix well after each addition.
Add flavoring.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Test for doneness.

title: hot bacon dressing
directions: Mix to paste.
Then gradually add 3/4 cup milk.
Brown bacon (cut bacon into small pieces before browning).
Add water and let boil.
Add first mixture to second mixture, gradually, and mix like making gravy.

title: el dorado casserole
directions: Brown meat, onions and garlic salt.
Mix with tomato sauce and olives.
Blend cottage cheese, sour cream and chilies.

title: cream of zucchini soup
directions: Cook all but cream and butter until tender over medium heat for 45 minutes.
Puree cooked ingredients.
Stir in cream and butter and serve.
Adjust seasoning.

title: jalapeno corn muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 12 or 36 (2 1/2-inch) miniature muffin cups.
In large bowl, combine cornmeal, flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
In small bowl, combine sour cream, eggs and jalapeno peppers until blended.
Stir into flour mixture just until moistened.
Spoon into muffin cups.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes for regular-size muffins, 12 to 15 minutes for miniature muffins or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Remove from pan.

title: blueberry soup
directions: Set aside 1 1/2 cups blueberries to put in the bottom of soup bowls.
Blend 3 cups of blueberries with 1 1/2 cups pineapple juice, lemon and vanilla.
Refrigerate.
Place blueberries in bottom of bowls.
Serve with dollops of vanilla yogurt.

title: alma's barbecue ribs
directions: Precook ribs in a pressure cooker for 15 minutes on high. While the ribs are cooking, mix the rest of the ingredients in a saucepan and bring to a boil.
Place drained ribs in a single layer in a glass or enamel baking dish.
Cover the ribs with the barbecue sauce and cover with foil.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours.
Remove the foil for the last 15 minutes to brown.

title: mandarin delight cake(once assembled, keep refrigerated.)
directions: Combine ingredients; mix for 2 minutes at medium speed.
Pour into sprayed 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake in preheated 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes. Cool. Frost with topping.

title: baked grits
directions: Cook grits in salt water according to directions on box.
Add chopped garlic, cheese and butter.
Remove from stove and fold in eggs, beaten.
Pour into greased dish.
Sprinkle with caraway seed and bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: saucepan fudge brownies
directions: In saucepan, melt 1/2 cup butter or margarine.
Add cocoa and oil.
Stir well.
Remove from heat.
Stir in sugar.
Blend in eggs, one at a time.
Add vanilla, flour and nuts; mix well.
Spread in greased and floured 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool.
Cut into squares.
Makes 16.
I used canned icing on these.

title: cornbread
directions: Heat oven to 425°. Put shortening in pan and let heat in oven. Mix cornmeal, flour, sugar, baking powder, salt, egg and milk. After mixing well, pour in heated pan. Spoon melted shortening over top of mix. Bake for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: christmas wreath
directions: Heat marshmallows and butter over medium-low heat until marshmallows are melted. Stir frequently. Stir in food coloring. Remove pan from heat. Add cereal, stirring until cereal is well coated.

Let stand until cool enough to handle. Divide cereal mixture into 8 equal mounds on greased cookie sheet, using greased fingers to shape into wreaths about 3-inches in diameter. Decorate with red M&M's.
Let stand until firm.
Store in single layer in airtight container.

title: marbled pound cake
directions: In large mixer bowl, pour cake mix; add water, oil and eggs. Blend at low speed just to moisten, then beat 3 minutes at medium speed.
Pour 2/3 of batter into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Stir gelatin into remaining batter.
Spoon over plain batter and zigzag a spatula through to marble.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes or until cake springs back when lightly pressed.
Cool in pan 15 minutes.
Remove from pan and finish cooling on rack.

title: cucumber pickles
directions: Mix ice in cucumbers. Let stand 1 hour.
Wash several times. Make sure all salt is rinsed out. Drain on towel, then heat vinegar, sugar and spices.
Pour over cucumbers.
Let come to boiling point.
Do not boil.
Makes 4 quarts.
Put in jars and seal.

title: crab dip
directions: Beat cream cheese until creamy. Combine all ingredients; mix well. Serve with wheat crackers.

title: jerry woodard's moist and creamy coconut cake
directions: Note:
I like to use French vanilla in Duncan Hines.

title: zucchini orange salad
directions: In large bowl, combine zucchini, onion and celery.
Pour boiling water over to cover; let stand 1 hour.
Drain and add green beans, water chestnuts, wax beans and mandarin oranges.

title: ron's peach melba cobbler
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients. Stir; let set while making enough pie crust for two 9-inch pies. Put half crust in bottom of pan (9 x 13) and preheat oven to 325°.

title: garden patch pasta salad
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions; drain.
In large bowl, combine cooked macaroni, zucchini, red peppers, bacon, eggs and seasonings.
Mix lightly.
Meanwhile, in medium saucepan, combine the cheese, mayonnaise (or salad dressing), milk and mustard.
Stir over low heat until cheese is melted.
Combine with macaroni mixture; toss together lightly.
Chill 3 to 4 hours, stirring occasionally, before serving.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: sue goff chicken casserole
directions: Mix and let stand overnight in fridge.
Take out 1 hour before baking.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
A delicious easy meal that can be made the day before.

title: sweet and sour steak stir-fry
directions: Cook rice; set aside.
Drain pineapple, reserving juice.
Add 1/2 cup reserved juice to 1 cup liquid measure.
Stir in vinegar, soy sauce, cornstarch and brown sugar.
Set aside.

title: snowball cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar thoroughly.
Add all other ingredients (except powdered sugar); mix well.
Form into tiny balls and bake 15 minutes in 450°
oven.
Cool slightly and roll in powdered sugar.
When cool, roll again in powdered sugar.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Drain beans.
Layer beans in soup, water chestnuts, pimentos and onion rings.
Sprinkle season over first layer, then repeat with another layer.
Let onion be the last layer this time.
Cover and cook in round 2-quart casserole for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: broccoli-cauliflower salad
directions: Combine vegetables in a large bowl.
Blend remaining ingredients in bowl.
Pour over vegetables, tossing lightly. Chill, covered.

title: mom's homemade ice cream
directions: Beat sugar and eggs together until blended.
Add evaporated milk, salt and vanilla.
Mix well.
Slowly add half and half and whipping cream.
Pour into ice cream container.
Add whole milk if necessary to fill to line.
Best if chilled a few hours or overnight.
Put in ice cream mixer (hand turned like the one I used as a kid or electric if you don't want to have as much fun).

title: chicken curry
directions: Saute onion and celery in oil.
Add flour and curry powder and stir well.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer 30 minutes. Serve as stew or over bread or biscuits.
Great for leftover turkey.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine chicken, celery, salt, mayonnaise, lemon juice, almonds, onion
and water chestnuts and put in buttered baking dish; top
with
potato
chips and cheese.
Bake in oven until heated through
and
bubbly.
Bake
at
for
20 minutes. Serves 6.

title: artichoke pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake pie shell for 5 to 10 minutes. Mix all ingredients together.
Fill pie shell and bake approximately 1 hour.

title: banana split cake
directions: Blend 1 1/2 sticks melted margarine and vanilla wafer crumbs. Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix powdered sugar, 1 1/2 sticks soft margarine, eggs and vanilla.
Beat 5 minutes, then pour on crust.
Split bananas lengthwise.
Roll them in lemon juice to preserve the color.
Lay slices on top of cream mixture.
Drain pineapple and spread over bananas.
Beat the Cool Whip and spread over top.
Sprinkle cake with chopped nuts.
Place a cherry in the middle of each anticipated serving.
Refrigerate at least an hour before serving.

title: hot dog relish
directions: Grind vegetables, using coarse blade. Sprinkle with 1/2 cup salt. Let stand overnight. Rinse and drain. Combine remaining ingredients; pour over vegetable mixture. Heat to boiling. Simmer 30 minutes. Seal in hot sterilized jars.
Process 8 minutes in hot water bath. Makes 8 pints.

title: quick caramel rolls
directions: Place butter in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Heat in a 375° oven until melted. Sprinkle with pecans. Add ice cream topping and mix well.
Remove dough from tubes (do not unroll); cut each section of dough into six rolls. Arrange rolls in prepared pan with cut side down.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden. Immediately invert onto a serving plate.
Serve warm. Yield: 2 dozen.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Cook fryer in pressure cooker for 20 minutes.
Remove all bones.
Add enough water to chicken broth to make 3 quarts.
Add base or bouillon.
Add chicken to broth.
Bring to boil.
Add dumplings.
Let boil 10 minutes.
Turn down to simmer for 45 minutes.

title: chicken on a diet
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Wash and skin chicken and dry on paper towel.
Salt and pepper and place in a foil-lined broiler pan.
Mix together orange soda and soy sauce.
Pour over chicken.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until chicken is tender.
Spoon sauce over chicken a couple of times while cooking.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Mix peanut butter and margarine in large bowl.
Stir in cereal.
Mix in powdered sugar, 1/3 at a time.
Press mixture firmly in ungreased square pan (9 x 9 x 2-inch).
Heat shortening in 1-quart saucepan over low heat until melted.
Add the chocolate chips.
Heat over very low heat, stirring constantly, until the chocolate chips are melted and the mixture is smooth.
Spread chocolate over mixture in pan.
Cover and refrigerate about 1 hour or until chilled.

title: crabmeat hors d'oeuvres
directions: Mix all ingredients, then spread onto English muffin halves (each half cut into 4).
Refrigerate for 1 to 2 hours.
Broil 3 to 5 minutes.

title: antipasto salad
directions: Sprinkle with oregano to taste.
Drizzle generously with virgin olive oil, amount is personal to taste.

title: mexican bread
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: baby foods
directions: Liquefy in blender (until smooth).
Add full amount of liquid for very young babies, decrease amount as child grows older.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients in bowl.
Pour into greased casserole. Crumble potato chips on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: italian zucchini pie
directions: Cook and stir zucchini in margarine for 10 minutes.
Stir in parsley or parsley flakes, salt, pepper, garlic powder, basil and oregano leaves.
Combine beaten eggs and Mozzarella.
Stir in zucchini mixture.
Place crescent rolls in ungreased 10-inch pie pan.
Pour mixture in crust.
Bake at 375° for 18 to 20 minutes. Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: banana surprise
directions: Layer vanilla wafers and sliced bananas in 48 ounce bowl.
Pour pudding over top layer.
Pudding will seep down between layers. Refrigerate at least 2 hours.
Serves 8.

title: cherry squares
directions: Beat together butter, sugar and eggs.
Add flour, nutmeg, vanilla, nutmeats and baking powder. Put 3/4 of mixture into a greased 7 x 11-inch pan.
Spread with pie filling.
Dot with the rest of the batter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes (until top batter browns).

title: grand prize double chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a small bowl, combine flour and soda.
In a large bowl, cream together until fluffy the butter, sugars and vanilla.
Whisk in egg.
Stir in cocoa and milk.
Fold in flour mixture, walnuts and chocolate chips.
Drop batter by rounded teaspoonfuls onto a nonstick baking sheet.
Bake about 12 minutes.
Cool for 5 minutes before removing from cookie sheets. Also delicious with milk chocolate chips!

title: fresh glazed peach pie
directions: Sprinkle the lemon juice over the peaches.
Add 1/4 cup sugar and mix.
Set aside for 1 hour.
Drain the peaches, but save the juice.
Add enough water to juice to make 1 cup.
Mix together in a pan 1/2 cup sugar and the cornstarch.
Cook until thick and clear.
Remove from heat and cool.
Add the salt, almond flavoring and the butter.
Add the peaches.
Turn into baked crust and cool. Serve with whipped topping.

title: tangy hush puppies
directions: Sift dry ingredients in
a
bowl.
Chop onion and tomatoes in a blender.	Add eggs
and blend.
Stir into dry ingredients.
Drop by
spoonfuls
into
hot grease, deep enough to submerge the hush puppies.
Fry until golden.
Serves 8.

title: cinnamon biscuit bites
directions: Separate biscuits and cut each into fourths.
Dip in melted butter; then roll in cinnamon-sugar mixture.
Bake at 400° about 10 minutes.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage and onion.
Drain.
Mix remaining ingredients and add to the sausage.
Place in 2-quart casserole dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: apricot rice
directions: Cook rice according to directions on box.
Pour boiling water over apricots and let stand 20 minutes to soften.
Drain.
Saute onions, mushrooms and green peppers in butter until tender.
Add to the cooked rice, then add apricots, pecans, parsley and seasonings.
Mix well.

title: beet salad
directions: Combine pineapple juice and beet juice to make one cup.
Mix gelatin and sugar.
Boil beet and pineapple juice and pour over gelatin and sugar, stirring until dissolved.
Cool and add beets, pineapple and nuts.
Mix well and chill.

title: pepper jelly
directions: Bring to a boil the sugar and vinegar.
After sugar is dissolved, add the chopped green pepper and the hot peppers and boil for 5 minutes more.
Add 1 bottle of Certo and a 1/2 bottle of red food coloring.
Pour into sterilized jars.

title: beef and cheese ball
directions: Mix ingredients and form into a ball.
Serve with crackers or chips.
Keeps in the refrigerator for several weeks.

title: barbecue
directions: Brown hamburger; drain.
Add rest of ingredients.
Simmer for 10 minutes.

title: crock-pot spaghetti
directions: Cook and stir well beef, onion and pepper.
Cook until meats brown and onion is tender.
Pour off fat.
Place in crock-pot. Add remaining ingredients except spaghetti.
Simmer 8 hours or longer.
Cook spaghetti and add Parmesan cheese.
Serves 12.

title: chocolate chip bars
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix shortening, margarine, sugars, egg and vanilla. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Spread on ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until light brown.
Cool and cut into bars, about 3 x 1-inch.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: apple dessert
directions: Peel and slice apples into baking dish.
Mix 1/2 cup sugar and cinnamon.
Sprinkle over apples.
Mix flour, 1/2 cup sugar, baking powder, salt, egg, oil and milk.
Pour batter over apples.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until apples are tender.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Mix together mayonnaise, sour cream, sugar, salt and garlic salt.
Add mixture to raw vegetables and refrigerate (or you can serve immediately).

title: bran muffins
directions: Stir together the first 4 ingredients.
Let stand for about 5 minutes.
Add flour, baking powder, salt and sugar, stirring only until combined.
Pour into greased muffin pan cups.
Bake at 400° about 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: clam casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake in buttered casserole dish at 400° about 20 minutes.
Will be golden brown and firm.

title: pancakes
directions: Beat the egg in a mixing bowl.
Add the remaining ingredients in the order they are listed.
Stir.
Bake on hot, lightly greased griddle.

title: sour cream avocado dip
directions: Peel and pit avocados.
Cut into pieces and place in food processor with sour cream, tomato, green onions, lemon juice and red pepper seasoning.
Cover; whirl until smooth.
Refrigerate 1 hour.

title: raspberry rhubarb crisp
directions: Place 9 crackers on bottom of 8 x 8-inch pan.
In saucepan over medium heat, add rhubarb, raspberries, 1/2 cup sugar and cornstarch until boiling.
Spoon into pan and set aside.
Coarsely crush remaining crackers.
Stir in flour, margarine and remaining sugar.
Sprinkle mixture evenly over fruit.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: ambrosia
directions: Drain pineapple and oranges.
In large bowl, combine grapes, marshmallows, pineapple, banana, coconut, oranges and nuts. Combine sour cream and brown sugar.
Stir into fruit mixture. Refrigerate, covered, 1 hour or overnight.
Makes 4 servings.

title: japanese pie
directions: Mix sugar and butter.
Add eggs, raisins, coconut and pecans and beat.
Add vanilla and vinegar.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 325° in uncooked pie crust.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs and oil together.
Add sugar.
Stir in zucchini and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: refrigerator muffins
directions: Pour boiling water over all-bran cereal and let stand while mixing. Cream salad oil, white sugar and brown sugar. Add eggs, buttermilk and bran. Mix well. Add flour, baking soda and salt. Mix and add raisins. This recipe keeps in the refrigerator up to 8 weeks. Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes as needed.

title: glazed carrots(microwave recipe)
directions: Cook carrots in water and salt until tender.
Meanwhile, combine brown sugar, corn syrup, margarine, orange peel and cornstarch.
Cook until clear, thickened and bubbly.
Drain carrots.
Pour glaze over carrots and toss to coat.

title: pasta salad with tuna sauce
directions: Cook the pasta 10 to 20 minutes and drain.
Blend the oil, ketchup, cayenne pepper, white wine vinegar and the paprika.
Toss with the pasta.
Stir in the tuna, dill and scallions. Refrigerate and chill thoroughly.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Add all ingredients in a 2-quart saucepan; bring to a boil. Add 2 cups of rice.
Let mixture come to a boil.
Stir and lower heat.
Cook until rice is tender, about 20 minutes.

title: shoo-fly pie
directions: Mix all together until like a coarse meal.
Set aside.

title: turkey ham roll-ups
directions: Combine.
Cook cabbage and 1/2 cup cheese.
Spoon about 3 tablespoons onto each ham piece and roll up.
Place, seams side down, in a baking dish.
Saute in 2 tablespoons butter or margarine.
Blend in flour.
Add milk and mustard; gently bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Add 1/2 cup cheese and parsley. Pour over turkey rolls.

title: butterscotch brownies
directions: Melt together the butter, sugar, eggs, vanilla and pecans.
Mix well and add flour and baking powder to mixture.
Combine all ingredients.
Bake in a well-greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: lasagne
directions: Boil noodles until almost done.
Set aside in cold water. Make hamburger meat into small balls and cook until done.
Drain and set aside in large pan.
Make sausage into small ball and cook until done.
Drain and add to hamburger balls.
Slice hot links into small pieces and fry, drain and add to other meat.
Saute onions and bell peppers until done.
Add to meat and mix tomato sauce with it.
Heat until almost boiling and simmer.
Grate all cheeses into separate bowls.

title: ham pie
directions: Cube ham.
Cook potatoes.
Layer potatoes, cubed ham and cheese until the pan is full.
Pour white sauce over.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Top with pie crust.
Bake according to instructions on box or until golden brown, approximately 45 minutes.

title: brown edge vanilla wafers
directions: Sift flour and salt together.
Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add egg and vanilla.
Beat until light.
Stir in dry ingredients.
Drop by teaspoon about 2 inches apart on well-greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until edges are brown. Can be decorated before baking.

title: zesty pasta salad
directions: Cook linguine according to box instructions.
Cool and add vegetables and seasonings.

title: tuna burgers
directions: Mix ingredients and baste tops of buns with butter.
Spoon mixture on buns.
Place on cookie sheet.
Place in preheated oven at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: french silk chocolate pie
directions: Cream butter and white sugar.
Add melted chocolate and vanilla.
Add 1 egg; beat for 5 minutes at minimum speed.
Add other egg; beat for 5 minutes at medium speed.
Place in baked pie crust.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Brown ground beef; drain and add onion and cut up zucchini. Cook until barely tender.
Add tomato sauce, tomato soup and seasonings.
Mix well.
Immediately pour into casserole dish. Place tomato slices on top of casserole.
Sprinkle grated cheese over tomatoes.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Sprinkle with French fried onions and return to oven for 5 minutes.

title: golden banana bread*
directions: Sift together 3 cups flour, baking powder and salt.
Cream shortening and sugar, add egg; beat well.
Beat in bananas and milk.
Gradually add dry ingredients; mix just until moistened. Combine nuts and 1 tablespoon flour.
Stir into batter.
Pour into greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes, or until tests done.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: pecan pie(different)
directions: Beat sugar and baking
powder
into egg whites; stir in cracker crumbs and nuts.
Pour
into
greased pie pan and bake in 350° oven for 30
minutes.
Top with whipped cream.
Serves six.

title: hot buffalo wings
directions: Drain oil from fried wings.
Heat Texas Pete.
Melt butter in Texas Pete.
Stir thoroughly.
Dip each drummette in mixture. Serve.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Cook rice, don't drain.
Stir in other ingredients.
Cook over medium heat until vegetables are tender.
Makes a complete meal served with crackers or bread.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown beef with the chopped onions.
Add the ketchup, brown sugar, Worcestershire sauce, chili powder, water and crumbled corned beef.
Simmer about 2 hours. Serve on buns.
Serves 16.

title: gingerbread(makes 1 loaf)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Blend eggs and brown sugar well.
Add shortening and molasses and stir until creamy.
Stir in the boiling water until well blended. Separately mix remaining ingredients together.
Add to sugar mixture, blending well.
Pour batter into a well-greased 9 x 5 1/2 x 4-inch loaf pan and bake until a knife inserted in the center comes out clean (about 1 hour).

title: impossible coconut pie
directions: Blend flour and sugar.
Add to beaten eggs.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into greased pans and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until firm.
Makes two 9-inch pies.

title: peanut-oatmeal drops
directions: Cream shortening, peanut butter and sugars.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add milk and vanilla.
Stir in flour, baking soda and salt.
Stir in oats and chopped nuts.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: beef brisket
directions: Place brisket in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour red wine over it and onion, sliced.
Cook about 6 to 7 hours at 300°, covered, until tender.
Cool overnight.
Slice thinly.
Reserve juice.

title: rice casserole
directions: Melt butter.
Add rice and soups.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: barbecue shrimp
directions: Melt margarine in large baking pan.
Mix in seasonings; add shrimp.
Add water to almost cover shrimp.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes until done.
Be sure to include French bread with this meal; dip it in the butter sauce and enjoy!

title: oatmeal honey bread
directions: In
large
mixer
bowl,
combine
cup
oats, butter, boiling
water, honey and salt.
Cool to warm.
Stir in yeast. Add eggs and 2 1/2 cups flour.	Beat at medium speed, scraping bowl often until smooth, 1 to 2 minutes.
Stir in enough flour to
make dough
easy
to
handle.
Turn
dough out on lightly floured surface.
Knead
until
smooth
and elastic, about 10 minutes. Add
more
flour
as
needed
until
dough no longer sticks. Place
in greased bowl.
Turn greased side up.
Cover and let rise in warm place until double in size, about 1 hour.

title: mrs. fields cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugars together.
Add eggs, vanilla, flour, oatmeal, baking soda, salt and baking powder.
Mix all ingredients. Make out in golf size balls.
Place on cookie sheet 2 inches apart. Bake for 6 minutes at 375°.

title: brownies
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add the well beaten eggs.
Sift the dry ingredients and add the vanilla.
Blend the entire mixture.
Spread thin in a greased paper-lined pan.
Bake in a hot oven (400°) about 15 to 20 minutes.

title: mira's chicken pot pie
directions: Drain vegetables and chicken in a colander in the sink.
Turn the oven to 400°.
Pour 2 cups of the milk and bouillon into a pot. Pour the rest of the milk into a jar and add flour.
Close and shake until there are no lumps.
Add to pot and cook over medium heat until boiling (about 6 to 8 minutes).
Stir 2 minutes more. Stir in vegetables and chicken, parsley and 1/2 teaspoon sage. Cook until hot and then turn off burner.
Put 6 casserole cups onto a baking sheet and split mixture between the dishes.
Cut each biscuit into 4 pieces.
Place 4 pieces on each casserole.
Bake 15 minutes and remove from oven.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Mix together flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Combine milk, egg and oil and add to flour mixture.
Add blueberries and put in greased muffin pans.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Makes 12.

title: nutritious peanut granola cups
directions: Place foil liners in 8 to 12 muffin tin cups.
Mix all ingredients well and spoon into cups.
Healthy snacking!

title: zucchini with eggs(zucchini con uova)
directions: Heat
oil
in medium saucepan.
Add the onion and saute until transparent.
Add
cut
zucchini
and
saute
for a few minutes. Add salt, pepper, parsley and water.
Cover and cook on medium-low
heat
until
zucchini is tender to fork.
Make indentions
in
zucchini and place raw egg (out of shell) onto squash.
Cover
pan
and
cook 5 minutes.
Close heat and keep covered until ready to serve.
Makes 6 servings.

title: goulash
directions: Brown meat; add tomatoes, salt and pepper. In a casserole dish, layer 1/3 potatoes, 1/2 meat mixture, 1/3 potatoes, onions and carrots. Top with remaining meat and 1/3 potatoes on top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hot wing dip
directions: Smear cream cheese in bottom of 9 1/2 x 11 baking dish.
Mix drained chicken with hot wing sauce in a separate bowl.
Pour over cream cheese. Cover with Ranch dressing, then cheese layer. Bake at 350° until cheese is melted.
Serve with celery or tortilla chips.

title: fruit trifle
directions: Cut cake in half. You may freeze one part for future use. Tear the other half into pieces.
Mix pineapple and oranges together.
Prepare pudding as directed on the box (except use skim milk).
Layer half each of the cake, fruit and pudding in a 2-quart serving bowl.
Repeat.
Prepare topping mix as directed on the box (except use skim milk).
Spread over pudding.
Sprinkle with nuts and garnish with cherries.
Refrigerate 2 hours.
Serves about eight people.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Mix together browned ground beef, salt, pepper, milk and catsup. Put in bottom of pan (13 x 9). Add remaining ingredients, placing the Tater Tots on top. Bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: cranberry jello mold
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Stir in whole cranberries and crushed pineapple with juice.
Stir and pour into 6 cup mold. Refrigerate overnight or 4 to 6 hours until set.

title: oatmeal cookies(uncooked)
directions: Put in saucepan and heat until dissolved. Mix thoroughly and beat.
Add oatmeal, peanut butter and vanilla.
Spoon out and flatten to shape.
Put on cookie sheet and refrigerate until well set.

title: apple crumb pie
directions: Pare apples (Pippin is good).
Cut in 1/8-inch pieces and arrange in an unbaked pie shell.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup sugar and cinnamon.
Sift remaining sugar with flour; cut in butter or oleo until crumbly.
Sprinkle over apples.
Bake in a hot oven at 450° for 10 minutes, then in a moderate oven at 350° for about 40 minutes or until apples are tender.

title: broccoli-cauliflower bake
directions: In 1 1/2 qt casserole, combine soup, milk, soy sauce and pepper. Stir in broccoli and cauliflower and 1/2 of the onions.
tags: Campbell's condensed cream of broccoli soup

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Combine shortening, granulated sugar, brown sugar, vanilla, and water.
Beat with an electric mixer.
Add eggs and continue to beat.
The mixture will be very creamy and light.
Add sifted dry ingredients and mix well.
Stir in chocolate chips according to taste and nuts if desired.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Don't let them brown.
(They may even not look quite done but will be awesome.)

title: mexican bean soup(frijoles charros)
directions: Clean and soak beans overnight.
Saute bacon, onion, garlic and pepper until tender.
Add this mixture plus tomatoes, cilantro and salt to beans that have been covered with water.
Simmer for 45 minutes.
Garnish with white cheese, if desired.
Serve with warm corn tortillas and hot sauce.

title: e-z yeast rolls
directions: Place yeast in 2 cups warm water.
Melt butter; add to sugar in large bowl.
Add beaten egg and dissolved yeast.
Add flour and stir until thoroughly mixed.

title: easy chocolate cherry torte
directions: Beat the 3 ingredients together until well blended.
Pour into greased Bundt pan or a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° until done.
When cooled, place in freezer until frozen.
This makes the cake very moist.
Remove from freezer.
Thaw and serve.
May sprinkle with confectioners sugar, if desired.

title: calico beans
directions: Brown beef, bacon and onion and drain.
Stir in beans (total of 4 cans).
Add the rest of ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or do in crock-pot.

title: chocolate cheese cake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Spoon into crust.
Refrigerate 3 hours or overnight.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and mix peppers, chicken soup, mushroom soup, onion, salt and pepper all together.
In 9 x 12-inch baking dish, put a layer of Doritos, meat mixture and a layer of grated cheese.
Continue in layers until all is used.
Bake in 350° oven about 30 minutes.

title: buckeyes
directions: Put all ingredients in large bowl and mix well with hands. Form in small balls.
Place on cookie sheets.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: parmesan sesame sticks
directions: Cut each slice of bread into 4 sticks and place in ungreased cookie sheet.
Brush with butter, then sprinkle evenly with cheese and sesame seed.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix these ingredients and place over potato mixture.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: pepperoni pizza chili
directions: Cook the beef and drain. Stir in the beans, pizza sauce, tomatoes, tomato sauce, water, pepperoni, pepper and salt. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat; simmer, uncovered, for 30 minutes. Serve over Fritos chips. Garnish with cheese.

title: seafood gumbo(serves 8 to 10)
directions: In Dutch oven saute garlic, onions and bell pepper in oil. Add okra, tomatoes, water, salt, pepper, Tabasco sauce, bay leaf and rice; bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer for 10 minutes.
Add shrimp (chopped) to Dutch oven; stir.
Return to boil, cover and simmer for 3 minutes.
Add crabmeat and parsley to shrimp mixture. Simmer for 2 minutes.
Stir in file powder.
Ladle gumbo into bowls; stir gently to mix all ingredients.
Serve with extra boiled rice.

title: orange salad
directions: Mix thoroughly and chill before serving.

title: holiday cole slaw
directions: Shred one head of cabbage.
Add mayonnaise to taste.
Drain pineapple and add to cabbage and mayonnaise.
Mix well.
Top with cherries.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Quick and easy!

title: amish friendship bread
directions: Mix well.
Pour into 2 well-greased and floured loaf pans. Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon on top.
Dates, raisins or nuts may be added.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: low calorie angel's food
directions: Prepare pudding according to package directions.
Add Cool Whip to pudding and mix together.
Tear angel food cake into small pieces in bottom of large bowl.
Slice 3 bananas and 1/2 of strawberries.
Top with 1/2 of pudding.
Make another layer of cake, bananas and strawberries.
Finish with pudding.
Top with a few sliced strawberries and nuts, if desired.
Chill and serve.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: Place graham cracker crumbs into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour melted oleo over crumbs.
Mix together all other ingredients and spread over graham crackers.
Bake 25 minutes at 350° or until slightly brown on top.

title: amazin' raisin cake
directions: Grease and flour 8 x 10-inch baking pan.
In a large bowl with mixer, beat first 10 ingredients for 2 minutes.
Batter will be thick.
Stir in apples, raisins and nuts.
Spoon batter into pan and bake at 350° for 45 minutes, or until silver knife comes out clean.
Cool in pan at least 10 minutes.
Frost if desired or serve plain with whipped cream.

title: whiskey sour punch
directions: Combine lemonade concentrate and orange juice; chill.
At serving time, place in punch bowl.
Add whiskey; stir lightly. Pour soda down sides to preserve bubbles.
Add ice and orange slices.
Yields 5 1/2 quarts.

title: ground beef deluxe
directions: Put beef in frying pan.
Add salt, pepper, onion and green pepper.
Cook on medium heat about 3 minutes.
Stir often.
Add catsup, A.1. sauce and Worcestershire sauce.
Continue to cook, stirring often, until beef is browned.

title: dip for fruit
directions: Whip all the ingredients together with an electric mixer until very smooth.	Refrigerate until cool.
Serve with fruit such as strawberries, banana slices, cantaloupe, pears and apples. This keeps well in the refrigerator.

title: mock "morel" mushrooms
directions: Mix together and let set overnight.
Drop spoon size patties in small amount of oil or butter.
Fry until brown.

title: pork chops on scalloped potatoes
directions: Arrange layers of potatoes, oleo, flour, cheese and salt and pepper in a 2-quart casserole.
Pour milk over layers.
Arrange pork chops on top of potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Break spaghetti in half.
Cook and drain.
While warm, combine with Parmesan cheese and eggs.
Pat into a well-greased 10-inch pie plate.
Melt butter and saute onion, then mix with Ricotta and spoon over spaghetti.
Saute meat and drain.
Add tomato paste, water and oregano.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Pour over pie.
Top with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: fresh broccoli casserole
directions: Cut up broccoli to make 6 cups.
In saucepan, cook broccoli in small amount of boiling salted water for 10 minutes; drain well. Mix broccoli with all ingredients except crackers.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Top with crushed crackers.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix together sour cream, cream cheese and bean dip.
Cover cookie sheet with foil; spread sour cream mixture over cookie sheet.
Spread olives over sour cream mixture.
Spread onions, cheese, taco sauce, lettuce and tomatoes over the top.
Serve with taco chips.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Bring milk to a boil.
Add butter and brown sugar.
Mix flour with warm water to make a paste.
Add eggs and salt to flour mixture.
When milk is almost boiling, stir in flour mixture, continuing to stir until blended.
Pour into 1 baked pie shell. Bake in preheated 350° oven for 40-45 minutes.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: In skillet, cook sausage until browned.
Drain off excess fat. Separate crescent roll dough into 8 triangles.
Place triangles in ungreased 12-inch pizza pan with points toward center.
Press over bottom and up sides of pan to form crust and seal perforations.
Spoon sausage over crust, then potatoes and cheese. Beat eggs, milk, salt and pepper.
Pour into crust.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: carol's apple crisp
directions: Mix together oatmeal, flour and sugar.
Cut in butter and add cinnamon.
Pare and slice apples and then put half of the flour/sugar mixture in an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Cover with the apples and place rest of mixture on top.
Bake 45 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: wine cake
directions: Dump cake mix into large mixer bowl.
Measure 1 cup of wine and drink to test for taste.
If it tastes good, have another. Then add pudding mix.
Measure another cup of wine and sip while getting eggs from refrigerator.
Measure 1 teaspoon of nutmeg and add to mixer bowl contents.

title: frankfurter skillet barbecues
directions: Cook onion and frankfurters in butter until onions are cooked and frankfurters are brown.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Stir often.
May be served in hot dog buns.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: german sweet chocolate cake
directions: Melt chocolate in boiling water; cool. Cream oleo and sugar. Beat in egg yolks. Stir in vanilla and chocolate. Set aside.

title: molded vegetable salad
directions: Sprinkle salt over vegetables and let stand a few minutes. Drain.

title: burritos
directions: Cook beef and drain.
Mix with beans and taco seasoning; warm. Place mixture on tortillas.
Add cheese on top.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes to melt the cheese.

title: dijon vinaigrette salad dressing
directions: Blend thoroughly and chill.
Keeps well in refrigerator. Makes one cup.

title: chocolate chip cookie
directions: Mix shortening, butter, eggs and vanilla. Stir in remaining ingredients. Bake in 350° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: divinity
directions: Make 1 batch of fudge and spread on wax paper or buttered tin. Make 1 batch divinity and spread on top.
Make another batch of fudge and put on top.
Cut into squares.
Store in tins.

title: angel yeast biscuits
directions: Dissolve
yeast in warm water.	Set aside.
Stir flour, Sweet 'N Low or sugar and soda.
Cut in shortening until size of	peas. Mix
buttermilk
with
yeast
water.
Add
to flour mixture.
Stir with fork until moistened.	(May be covered and refrigerated overnight to be shaped and baked later.) Turn out onto
floured surface.
Sprinkle	with
flour,
knead
4 or 5 times.

title: bowle's baked beans
directions: Mix together first 4 ingredients.
Put in bean pot or other baking pan.
Place bacon strips across top.
Bake at 300° for 3 hours.
Add water as necessary to prevent becoming too dry.

title: mother's salad dressing
directions: Bring to a boil vinegar, water, sugar, margarine and flour. Beat egg.
Pour mixture over egg and beat.
Add salt and pepper. Put a layer of leaf lettuce on platter and dip some of mixture over lettuce and continue with a layer of lettuce and mixture.
It sure is good.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Grease a casserole dish.
Line with tortillas.
Layer ground beef, onion, beans, dash of salt, cheese (in pieces), tortillas and mixture of soup and Ro-Tel tomatoes.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: two flavor fudge
directions: Combine in saucepan the brown sugar, granulated sugar, evaporated milk and butter.
Bring to full boil over moderate heat, stirring frequently.
Boil for 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat.
Add marshmallow cream, butterscotch and chocolate morsels; stir until morsels are melted and mixture is smooth.
Blend in walnuts and vanilla.
Pour into greased 9-inch square pan.
Chill until firm.
Yields about 2 1/2 pounds.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spread pecan and coconut mixture into well-greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Mix German chocolate cake mix as directed.
Pour cake batter over pecan mixture; set aside.

title: turkey tetrazzini(total time is 45 minutes)
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Cook pasta according to package directions omitting salt and fat.
Drain.
Heat oil in a large nonstick skillet over medium high heat.
Sprinkle turkey with 1/2 teaspoon onion powder, 1/4 teaspoon salt and 1/8 teaspoon pepper. Add turkey to pan, cook 2 minutes on each side or until done. Remove turkey from pan.
Add 1/4 teaspoon onion powder, sherry, and mushrooms to pan.
Cover and cook about 4 minutes or until mushrooms are tender.
Combine peas and next 4 ingredient in a large bowl.
Chop turkey.
Add 1/8 teaspoon pepper, pasta, turkey and mushroom mixture to soup, tossing gently to combine.
Spoon mixture into a 13 x 9 inch baking dish that is coated with cooking spray.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Boil until it forms a soft ball in cold water.
Remove from fire.
Add vanilla and peanut butter.
Beat until thickens.
Pour into a buttered pan.
When cool, cut in squares.

title: fiesta tamale pie
directions: Saute onion in 3 tablespoons butter and 3 tablespoons oil until soft.
Add beef and brown.
Add tomatoes, corn and seasonings. Pour into 13 x 9-inch dish.
Press olives into mixture.
Mix corn meal, milk and eggs.
Spread over meat mixture and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: broiled sesame fish
directions: Thaw frozen fish in refrigerator overnight,
or defrost briefly in a microwave oven.
Cut fish into 4 portions.
Place fish on a broiler pan lined with aluminum
foil.
Brush margarine over fish.	Mix lemon juice, tarragon
leaves,
salt
and pepper; pour over fish.
Sprinkle sesame
seed
evenly
over fish.
Broil until fish flakes easily when tested with a fork, about 12 minutes.
Garnish each serving with parsley.
Makes 4 servings.

title: "sugar's" oven-baked butter bread
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Put shortening in a 9-inch cast-iron skillet and put in the oven to melt shortening and to heat skillet.
Mix the dry ingredients.
Beat buttermilk and egg together.
Stir them into the dry ingredients, mixing thoroughly but do not beat.
The batter is best when left as a slightly lumpy mixture.
Pout hot shortening from skillet into batter.
Stir briefly.
Pour batter into hot skillet.
Bake 18 to 20 minutes. Serve hot with butter and jelly.

title: praline cookies
directions: Bring sugar, butter and margarine to boil and boil 1 minute. Break graham crackers into sections and place on a cookie sheet. Then place the finely chopped pecans on top of crackers.
Drip boiled mixture over crackers and pecans.
Place in 350° oven for 10 minutes.

title: barbecue shrimp
directions: Melt butter and add olive oil in a 9 x 12-inch pan. Mix the remaining ingredients. Add mixture to olive oil and butter mixture and cook for 7 minutes over medium heat. Let cool for 30 minutes. Warm mixture and add 1 1/2 pounds of shrimp. Cook on stove top for 6 minutes or until shrimp are pink, stirring frequently. Place in 450° oven for 8 to 10 minutes, stirring often. Serve with warm bread.

title: veal parmesan
directions: Pan-fry veal patties in small amount of butter.
Place in baking dish. Cover with spaghetti sauce.
Cover with grated Mozzarella cheese. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Bake at 350° until brown and bubbly.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Cream peanut butter, oleo and vanilla (easier to mix with hands).
Add powdered sugar, a little at a time.
In double broiler, melt 1 large bag chocolate chips and 1 stick paraffin. Make dough into balls.
Dip in chocolate.
Place on waxed paper and put into refrigerator.
Makes 80 to 135 balls.

title: cold broccoli salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill and serve.

title: mex chiquito cheese dip
directions: Mix first 2 ingredients into paste.
Add remaining ingredients.
Combine all and bring to boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat.

title: pineapple meringue cake
directions: Sift 2 more tablespoons flour with 1 teaspoon baking powder and 1/4 teaspoon salt into batter.
Stir vigorously.
Put into 2 greased and floured cake pans and cover with meringue.

title: hopping john
directions: Place peas and ham in a large saucepan and cover with water. Add salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil and reduce heat.
Simmer for about 1 1/2 hours.
Add water as needed to keep peas covered. Remove ham hock; lay it aside to cool.
Add rice.
Bring back to a boil.
Remove from heat and cover.
Let it stand for 15 minutes.

title: peanut butter squares
directions: Melt margarine
and
mix
with first 2 ingredients, add peanut butter and vanilla.
Spread in ungreased cookie pan and refrigerate.
Slice into squares and return to refrigerator.

title: pineapple cream pie
directions: Combine first five ingredients and cook until thick.
Cool and put into pie shell.
Top with Cool Whip or Meringue.

title: potato salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together in large mixing bowl. Add pepper to taste.
Place in a large bowl.
Sprinkle with paprika.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Mix sugar and butter.
Add eggs and flour.
Add spices.
Mix soda with applesauce, then add to flour mixture.
Add raisins and nuts.
Bake in tube or loaf pan at 225°.

title: risen biscuits
directions: Sift the dry ingredients into a bowl.
Mix with shortening. Add yeast and milk.
Mix like biscuits.
Knead, then place in greased bowl in refrigerator for at least two hours to chill. Roll like biscuits.
Grease the top of each and place one on top of another and crimp.
Let rise and bake in 425° oven.
These can be made up the night before if you wish.

title: perfect pie crust
directions: Put first 3 ingredients in large bowl and mix well with table fork.
Add shortening and mix with fork until crumbly.
In small bowl beat together with fork 1/2 cup water, vinegar and egg. Combine the two mixtures, stirring with fork until all ingredients are moistened.
Divide into 5 portions with hands.
Shape into flat round patty ready for rolling.
Wrap each in plastic or waxed paper and chill at least 1/2 hour.
When ready to roll pie crust, lightly flour both sides of patty, put on lightly floured board.

title: candied dill sticks
directions: Drain and wash pickles.
Cut in chunks and place in crocks. Mix sugar and vinegar and pour over pickles.
Stir frequently over a period of 6 hours.
Return to jar and pour liquid over pickles.

title: broccoli supreme
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Blend together soup and flour.
Add sour cream, carrots and onion.
Mix well. Stir in broccoli.
Put in a 2-quart casserole.
Combine stuffing mix with melted margarine and sprinkle evenly over top of broccoli mixture. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until hot and bubbly and top is golden brown. Serves 4 to 6.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar and milk well, then add the Cool Whip and mix real good and set aside.
Mix pudding mix according to box directions and set aside.
Layer bottom of pan with graham crackers.
Put in pudding, then Cool Whip filling and keep alternating crackers, pudding and Cool Whip.
Can also be topped with Cool Whip.

title: safe play dough
directions: Mix and heat slowly all but food coloring until it lumps together.
Remove from heat.
Stir in food coloring.
Can also be scented with extracts.
Mix with hands.

title: spanish rice
directions: Cook ground beef and drain fat.
Add minced onion and continue cooking for 5 minutes.
Spray a small baking dish with nonstick cooking spray (or lightly grease dish).
Mix all ingredients in the dish, except save 1/2 the cheese to sprinkle on top.
Sprinkle cheese on top and cover the dish with aluminum foil.
Bake it in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: artichoke salad with oregano dressing
directions: Wash and dry spinach and lettuce.
Mix the lettuce and spinach with the olives, artichoke hearts and their liquid.
Pour the desired amount of dressing over and mix well.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions.
Drain and add lemon juice, then add next 4 ingredients.
Mix. Let marinate in refrigerator for 3 hours or overnight, then add remaining ingredients.

title: best blueberry muffins
directions: Position rack in the middle of oven. Preheat oven to 375 degrees. Spray the top of a muffin pan with non-stick coating., and line with paper liners. In a large bowl, cream together the butter, 1 1/4 c. sugar and salt until light and fluffy. Beat in the eggs one at a time. Mix together 1 3/4 c. of the flour and baking powder. Beat in the flour mixture alternately with the buttermilk, mixing just until incorporated. Crush 1/4 of the blueberries, and stir into the batter. Mix the rest of the whole blueberries with the remaining 1/4 c. of the flour, and fold into the batter. Scoop into muffin cups. Sprinkle tops lightly with sugar. Bake in preheated oven for 30 minutes, or until golden brown, and tops spring back when lightly tapped.

title: szechuan shrimp
directions: Combine scallions, bamboo shoots, ginger, garlic and pepper sauce in a small bowl.
In a second bowl, combine sugar, catsup, sherry, soy sauce and sesame oil (or seed).
In 3rd bowl, mix cornstarch and water.
Heat oil in wok or large skillet to 400°. Have ready a large strainer with bowl underneath.
Add shrimp to hot oil, stirring until done, about 2 minutes.
Pour oil and shrimp into strainer to drain.
Heat 2 tablespoons of strained oil in same wok over high heat.
Add scallions.
Mix and stir-fry 1 minute. Add drained shrimp and stir-fry 30 seconds.
Add cornstarch mixture to wok.
Cook and stir until slightly thickened.
Serve over rice. Add pea pods and baby corn if desired to wok with scallion mixture.

title: coconut pecan cake
directions: Mix together. Cook in a tube pan. Bake at 350° about 1 hour.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Boil sliced strawberries and 2/3 cup water for 3 minutes.
Mix together sugar, cornstarch and 1/3 cup water.
Add to strawberries and bring to a boil again.
Boil 1 minute.
Set aside.
Fill pie shell with halved or quartered strawberries.
Pour filling over berries.
Cool in refrigerator 1 hour.
Top with whipped cream or whipped topping.
Serve.

title: fresh raw apple cake
directions: Cream shortening; add sugar and eggs.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add apples and nuts and mix well.
Bake in 9-inch square pan in a 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.
(Batter will be very stiff.)

title: calico beans
directions: Brown bacon, drain and crumble.
Saute onions in bacon drippings; drain onion.
Mix beans; add bacon and onions.
Put into 2 1/2 to 3-quart casserole.
Mix together the brown sugar, garlic salt, dry mustard and vinegar.
Pour over top of mixture in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, uncovered.

title: old fashioned rice pudding
directions: Heat milk and add cooked rice.
Beat eggs, and add sugar, vanilla and raisins.
Combine with rice and milk mixture.
Pour in baking dish and dot with margarine.
Set dish in pan of hot water.
Bake at 450° for 20 minutes.
Lower heat to 300° and bake until custard is firm (about 15 to 20 minutes).
Sprinkle with nutmeg and cinnamon.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: cin-apple buns(positively fat free!  fantastic!)
directions: In food processor, mix flour, yeast, sugar and salt (the first 4 ingredients).
While processor is running, then add egg whites and 1 cup warm water.
If dough seems too dry, add a bit more water; if too wet, a bit more flour.
Process until smooth ball forms (about 4 minutes).
Cover with damp cloth and leave on floured surface to rise, about 1/2 hour.
When dough has risen, roll into large rectangle.
Spread with applesauce, then top with 1 cup brown sugar, raisins and cinnamon.

title: sunburst chicken
directions: Stir-fry chicken and ginger until chicken is done.
Remove from pan and keep warm.
Add to pan a bit of oil, carrots and green pepper.
Stir-fry until tender.

title: cottage potatoes
directions: In small roaster layer all ingredients.
Melt butter and pour over top.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chocolate chip brownies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: fruit kuchen
directions: Mix together oleo, 1/2 cup sugar, eggs, flour, salt and flavoring.
Pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cut plums and prunes in half.
If using apples, slice.
Put in rows.
Mix sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg; cover fruit.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: lemon sauce for pie or over desserts
directions: Chop cherries, nuts, chocolate, etc.
Gradually add boiling water to sugar or NutraSweet, lemon or lime juice and egg yolks. Cook until thick.
Pour into baked pie shell or graham cracker shell and whip "egg whites".
Spread on top and bake until egg white browns.
Sprinkle on chopped cherries or etc.
Refrigerate until set and serve.

title: spam potato bake
directions: Layer potatoes, celery, onion, pepper and Spam in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix soup with milk (instead of water).
Pour over layers.
Bake 45 to 60 minutes at 350° or until done.

title: glazed ribs
directions: Place spareribs, meaty side up, in open, shallow roasting pan. Heat remaining ingredients to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir for 3 minutes.
Pour sauce over meat.
Roast in 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours or until done, basting 4 to 5 times.
Makes 4 servings.

title: three bean casserole
directions: Brown hamburger, chopped onions and bacon.
Add remaining ingredients and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Bake at 425° for 1 hour.

title: peaches and cream cheesecake
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, salt, butter, egg, milk and pudding and beat for 2 minutes.
Pour into a 9-inch greased pie plate. Drain peaches, reserving 2 tablespoons juice.
Place fruit on batter.
Mix cream cheese, sugar and 2 tablespoons peach juice. Beat for 2 minutes.
Spoon over fruit to within 1 inch of edge of batter.
Sprinkle on top a mixture of 2 tablespoons sugar and 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Filling will appear soft but will set as it cools.
Chill well.

title: no cook fudge
directions: Cream softened cheese and oleo.
Leave cheese and oleo out of refrigerator 2 hours or more to soften. Add peanut butter and cream until smooth.
Add milk and mix well.
Sift in powdered sugar until fudge consistency is reached.
Spread in buttered pan and refrigerate.

title: hot french onion dip
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a 1 qt. casserole combine soup mix, sour cream, 1-3/4 c. swiss cheese and mayonnaise. Bake uncovered 20 minutes or until heated through.
Sprinkle with remaining 1/4 c. of cheese.
Serve with sliced French bread or your favorite chip.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Use enough butter to moisten flakes.
Mix all ingredients as listed.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: caramel torte
directions: Beat egg yolks until lemon colored and thick.
Add sugar and continue to beat.
Add Rusk crumbs, nuts, baking powder and vanilla; mixing well.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold egg whites into yolk mixture.
Pour into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Bake at 350° about 30 minutes or until cake tests done.
Cool. Spread whipped cream over cooled cake.
Spread Sanders fudge topping over whipped cream.
Chill before serving.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt together chocolate chips, peanut butter and oleo.
In a large pan, pour melted mixture over cereal.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour sugar in a large paper bag.
Pour in coated cereal and shake well. Store in an airtight container.

title: dog food(chuck wagon beans)
directions: Brown ground beef; drain well. Add pork and beans; heat well, stirring often.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Drain off fat.
Add sour cream and creamed soup.
Cook on low heat.
Boil until thick.
Pour over cooked noodles.
Serve immediately.
Cook noodles while sauce is cooking.
Follow directions on package.

title: old fashion pepper sauce
directions: Wipe peppers off with paper towel.
Pack in jar of choice. Pour cold vinegar until peppers are covered.
Let set a few days. Serve on vegetables.

title: pasta and beans
directions: Wash beans and put in 6-quart pot, then bring to a boil.
Turn stove off and let beans stand; set.
Soak for 1 hour.
Then turn stove back on and add salt, pepper, oregano, tomatoes and oil. Put on slow, cooking until tender, about 3 to 4 hours.
Cover pot with a tight lid to keep the liquid from evaporating while you are cooking the beans.
About 1 hour before they are eaten, cook ditalini for about 5 minutes in separate pot.
Then drain macaroni and put it in the pot with beans, mixing well.
Turn stove off under beans.
The macaroni will finish cooking without heat from the stove when mixed with bean liquid.
Serve with cheese.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Line pie shell with bacon and cheese slices overlapping to cover bottom of crust.
Combine eggs, cream, flour, pinch of nutmeg, cayenne and black pepper.
Beat well.
Strain and pour over bacon and cheese slices.
Bake in hot oven, 450°, for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 325° and bake for 30 minutes.

title: cherry crunch
directions: Spread	cherry pie filling, then pineapple in bottom of 9 x 11-inch oblong baking dish.
Sprinkle nuts, then dry cake mix on top.
Melt oleo and pour over top of cake mix.
Cook at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: beef porcupines
directions: Shape ingredients into small meatballs.
Brown on all sides in skillet.
Combine contents of beef seasoning with 2 1/2 cups hot water.
Pour over meat.
Lower heat and simmer 30 minutes. Thicken gravy, if desired.

title: banana, zucchini and carrot bread
directions: Beat egg and add sugar; beat until creamy. Add melted margarine/butter and bananas, carrots and zucchini. Add nuts mixed with dry ingredients. Bake 70 minutes in regular loaf pan or in 3 small loaves for 45-50 minutes at 350°.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Mix bread, eggs, 1 1/2 cups milk, Cheddar cheese, dry mustard, pepper and onion and let set overnight.
In morning, add ham, celery soup and 1/2 can milk.
Bake in 9 x 12-inch pan uncovered 1 hour at 350° or until knife comes out clean.

title: arthritis
directions: Pour raisins into a glass container.
Pour gin on the raisins until it covers them.
Let stand on countertop for 7 days.
(Do not refrigerate.)
After one week, take 1 teaspoon with 9 raisins every day.
It will help your arthritis and make you feel happy. (Use any brand of gin.)

title: lemon filling or frosting by irene lee dixon
directions: Cook over low heat until thick. Spread on your favorite cake recipes, white or yellow cake.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Cover well with mayonnaise.
Refrigerate.
Mix or toss when ready to serve.

title: dressing
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Cut onion and celery into bite-size pieces; simmer in melted butter.
Cut some turkey fat and turkey. Add to onion and celery along with salt, pepper and sage and simmer.
Mix with bread.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Stuff into turkey.

title: the bread thing
directions: Saute mushrooms, onions and almonds in butter.
Add soup and Old English.
Heat through.
Add cooked broccoli.
Hollow out bread, ripping pieces into large dipping size.
Pour sauce into bread.
(We often buy 2 different loaves of bread for more of a variety of dippers.)

title: crazy chocolate cake
directions: Mix in order given.
Don't mix or beat until last thing is added.
Bake in loaf or layer pan in moderate oven (350°) for approximately 80 minutes.

title: peach jello salad
directions: Combine Jell-O, pineapple and sugar in saucepan.
Cook over low heat until Jell-O and sugar are dissolved.
Remove from heat. Blend in buttermilk.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish which has been greased with mayonnaise.

title: tri-tip roast
directions: Place Tri-Tip in large baking dish with lid.
Cover meat with onion soup mix.
Top with mushroom soup, undiluted.
Cover and bake 1 1/2 to 2 hours at 350°.

title: corn bread dressing
directions: Mix corn bread with bread. Add remaining ingredients and blend well. May stuff turkey or chicken or bake in well-greased 8 x 8-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: wednesday's chili
directions: In a skillet, add ground round, oil, onion soup and chili powder and brown.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer for 1 hour over low heat, stirring often.

title: oatmeal-raisin cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Dough will be very stiff but will come out okay.
Bake at 350° for about 10 to 12 minutes.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar together.
Pour over mixture of broccoli, sunflower seeds, bacon, onion and raisins.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain fruit, set aside.
Beat sour cream, add marshmallows and fruit.
Beat Dream Whip by directions on package, add to other mixture.
Chill serveral hours or overnight.

title: fifth wheel cannelloni
directions: Cooking Meat:
Place meat in preheated olive oil and start to cook.
As it starts to brown, add the Italian seasoning and cook at low heat slowly until thoroughly cooked.

title: rye boat dip
directions: Chop dried beef to shreds. Mix all ingredients.
Let flavors blend several hours, refrigerated.
Cut out center of bread leaving "boat" of bread.
Fill with dip just before serving.
Cut center of bread into bite-sized chunks.
Place around bread boat for dipping.

title: pork chop 'n stuffing
directions: Heat a small amount of oil in a skillet.
Add chops and cook until browned on both sides.
Place chops in a shallow baking dish.
Lightly mix together the next 5 ingredients.
Place a mound of stuffing mixture on each chop.
Stir together soup and water; pour over chops.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Yield: 4 servings.

title: chicken broccoli cheese casserole
directions: Parboil broccoli cuts and set aside.
Cook rice as indicated on box.
Add cream of chicken soup and milk to rice and broccoli, then stir in Cheez Whiz.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
If adding chicken, parboil before adding to mixture.
Also cut up in small pieces.
Enjoy.

title: sand art cookies gift mix
directions: Mix together in separate bowls, the flour and salt and the flour and baking soda.

In a quart jar, layer the ingredients in the order given. Decorate the jar lid as desired. Include the following printed instructions: Combine dry ingredients with 3 eggs, 2/3 cup oil and 1 teaspoon vanilla. Pour into greased 9 x 9-inch pan and bake at 350° for 30-35 minutes.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients.
Put in greased and floured Bundt or angel food cake pan.
Cook for 1 hour or until golden brown and toothpick inserted into cake comes out clean.
Makes a great substitute for fruit cake.

title: ham loaf
directions: Mix thoroughly.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: valentine strawberry bavarian
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water and add ice water.
Chill until slightly congealed and beat until light and fluffy.
Drain berries, reserving juice for glaze.
Fold berries and whipped cream to jello mixture. Rub brown from angel food cake and tear cake into pieces.
Alternate cake and gelatin mixture in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Chill until firm.
Drizzle glaze over all.

title: mock turkey
directions: Mix all ingredients well and place in buttered baking dish. Bake in a moderate 350° oven until done.

title: chocolate cheese cake
directions: Mix flour, butter and nuts until crumbly.
Pat into 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool.
Whip powdered sugar, Cool Whip and cream cheese.
Mix thoroughly; spread over crust.
Mix puddings and milk.
Beat until thick and creamy.
Pour over cream cheese mixture.
Top with remaining Cool Whip.
May be made the day before.

title: baked pork chops and beans
directions: Fry pork chops and remove from skillet.
Add all ingredients to fat in skillet and saute.
Stir well, then place pork chops on top and simmer or place in oven for 30 minutes.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, beating after each is added.
Add sour cream and mix thoroughly.
Add flavorings.
Mix in one cup of flour.

title: quick barbecue sauce
directions: Cook for 15 minutes on low heat; ready to use.

title: baked ham-new orleans
directions: Combine sugar and seasonings. Spread on ham. Place fat side up on rack in shallow roasting pan.
Sprinkle with lemon juice. Bake in slow 325° oven for 1 hour.
Serves 8 to 10 people.

title: sandy's special fruit salad
directions: Drain pineapple and save juice in a jar.
Add 2 tablespoons Tang instant drink and 1 (3 ounce) package vanilla instant pudding to juice.
Shake well and refrigerate for 1 hour.
Have fruit cut up in a large bowl and pour dressing over fruit at serving time.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: In a medium bowl, mix flour, salt and baking soda.
Set aside. In a large bowl, add eggs and beat.
Add vanilla, sugars and butter.
Then gradually add flour mixture and then add chips.
Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° to 375° for 6 to 10 minutes or until slightly brown on bottom.

title: grilled flank steak
directions: Combine oil and remaining ingredients, stirring well.
Pour over steak.
Cover.
Marinate in refrigerator 8 hours. Drain steak, reserving marinade.
Grill to desired doneness, basting twice with marinade.
Discard remaining marinade.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain fruit cocktail well.
Mix all ingredients except cherries.
Chill.
Garnish with cherries.

title: fudge sundae cake
directions: Mix together flour, margarine and chopped nuts and spread in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes until golden brown.
Mix cream cheese, half Cool Whip and sugar and spread over cooled nut mixture.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Combine ingredients and pour into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes.
Yields 24 (2-inch) squares.
I melt oleo in baking pan and saute chopped onion in it before adding to mixture, retaining 1/3 oleo in pan. Heat oleo before pouring into mixture.
Spread excess oleo over bread.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Boil potatoes.
Fry ground beef with any of the following: onion, celery or green peppers.
After browned, lay in small casserole dish.
Add soup and mix.
Add peas, green beans or corn. Add pats of butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour or until golden brown.

title: dill dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill.
Serve with raw veggies.

title: onion spread
directions: Combine all ingredients and stir well. Chill.
Spoon in container and chill.

title: cheese pudding
directions: (You can add Shoe Peg corn to this.
Make sure kernels are dry.)

title: stove top stuffing casserole
directions: Prepare the Stove Top stuffing mix per instructions on the box. Drain cans of mushrooms. In a deep baking dish, put a layer of stuffing (1/2), a layer of onions (1/2), a layer of mushrooms (1/2) and a layer of Velveeta cheese (slice thickness of cheese per taste). Repeat the layers again and then pour 1/4 cup of milk over the top. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes (until cheese is thoroughly melted).

title: snack mix
directions: In a 2-gallon Ziploc bag, mix cereal, crackers, nuts and pretzels.
Add oil and toss until well coated.
Add dressing mix and toss until well coated.
Pour onto cookie sheet and bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: swedish kol dolma
directions: Heat the butter or oil and fry the beef and onion until the beef is well browned.
Add the cooked potatoes, salt and pepper. Add enough water to make a pliable mixture and stir, breaking up the potatoes.
Form the mixture into balls and flatten to an inch thick.
Fry the rounds on both sides until golden brown.

title: sauteed frog legs
directions: Wash legs and let dry in air.
Dust generously with salt and pepper and roll in cracker crumbs.
Melt butter over high heat. Brown and add frog legs.
Saute 1 1/2 minutes and turn.
When legs curl, remove from heat and serve at once.
If a crisp joint is preferred, pour butter from pan and saute legs another minute, shaking them to prevent burning.

title: grasshopper pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour in two 9-inch unbaked pie shells. Bake at 325° for 50 minutes or longer, until brown.

title: chocolate pudding graham cracker layer cake
directions: Cook pudding according to directions.
Add Amaretto.
Stir awhile to cool pudding; set aside with plastic wrap on top to prevent a skin from forming (about 10 minutes).

title: macaroni and cheese casserole
directions: Boil macaroni and salt according to package. Drain.
Use 10-inch casserole dish, buttered or sprayed.
Put layer of macaroni and layer of grated cheese until all is used.
Beat eggs and milk together and pour over mixture.
Be sure it is juicy, if you have to add more milk.
Dot with oleo and cook until bubbly on top.
Save some cheese to put on top of casserole when it's done while hot.

title: cilantro chicken
directions: Begin preparing yellow saffron rice, following package directions.
Saute chicken, oil and jalapeno in a large frying pan or wok.
When chicken is about 1/2 way cooked through, add lemon juice, onion and water chestnuts.
Stir frequently as you allow most of the juices to cook away.
Once chicken is totally cooked through, add cilantro, salt and pepper.
Stir and allow to cook for 2 minutes.

title: sweet watermelon pickles
directions: Soak watermelon overnight in weak brine made by dissolving salt in 1 gallon cold water.
Rinse with cold water and let stand in ice water for 1 hour; drain.
Cover with boiling water and simmer until tender enough to be pierced with a toothpick.
Drain and drop into hot syrup made by cooking together vinegar and sugar.
Add spice bag holding cloves and cinnamon sticks.
Cook gently until rind is clear and transparent.
Remove spice bag and let rind stand in syrup 24 hours.
Pack attractively in hot, sterilized jars, adding a few spices for each jar.
Heat syrup to boiling.
Pour over pickles in jars and seal.
Eight pounds yields about 8 pints.

title: aunt patty's rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast and sugar in hot water.
Mix in order given. Let rise.
Make rolls; let rise again.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Slice and bake cookies (overlap on pizza pan).
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 375° unti slightly brown.
Mix next 4 ingredients and spread over cooled cookies.
Arrange fruit on top.

title: carol's mother's brownies
directions: Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: sweet potatoes
directions: Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: hot and sour soup
directions: *All vegetables 1/4 to 1/2 cup, sliced.

title: crab dip
directions: Mix crab, onions, red onion, tomato, parsley and lime juice and refrigerate overnight.
Cream the cream cheese and mayonnaise. Spread over bottom of platter, then avocados.
Drain crab mixture and spread over avocados.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Combine flour, sugar, cocoa, milk and egg yolks and cook until it begins to thicken.
Remove from heat and add vanilla and margarine.
Beat egg white for meringue.
Brown in a 450 degree oven until egg whites are beginning to brown.

title: sputniks
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix until well mixed with wooden spoon.
Drop by 1/2 teaspoons of mixture in hot oil (375°).
Brown; drain.
Roll in cinnamon and sugar mixture.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Mix soups, onions, black olives and chilies together.
Spray 9 x 13-inch dish with Pam.
On bottom of pan, put a layer of chips. Spread half of soup mixture over chips.
Sprinkle with half of chicken and half of cheese.
Repeat layers.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Mix flour with sugar; add other ingredients and cook until thick.
Pour in baked crust.
Beat egg whites until stiff and put on top.
Bake until whites are done.

title: scampi-style shrimp
directions: In large skillet, over medium heat, cook and stir green onion and garlic in butter and oil for 1 minute.
Add shrimp, cook and stir until shrimp are pink.
Add lemon juice and salt.
Heat through and garnish if desired.
Serves 4.

title: no cook banana pudding
directions: Blend pudding mix into milk.
Stir in condensed milk.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Put a layer of wafers in the bottom of a glass bowl and cover with a layer of sliced bananas.
Cover with a generous layer of pudding mix.
Continue to layer until all of the pudding is used.
Crush some of the wafers and put on the top.
Refrigerate. This recipe is from my mother, Ernestine Weems.

title: old fashioned peach ice cream
directions: Mash peaches well and blend thoroughly with 1 1/2 cups sugar; set aside.
Put ice cream can in freezer tub.
Pour tub 2/3 full of crushed ice around can, using 4 parts ice to 1 part ice cream salt.
Pour milk and cream into can.
Stir in remaining sugar, salt, flavorings and eggs.
Add sweetened mashed peaches; stir. Adjust lid and freeze according to your individual freezer instructions.
Usually takes about 15 minutes.

title: butterscotch noodle clusters
directions: Melt butterscotch over hot water; gently stir in noodles and nuts until well coated.
