Drop by tablespoon onto wax paper.
Place in refrigerator or cool place until set.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: 7 layer cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Melt butter.
Put layer of crumbs, then add layer of coconut, layer of morsels and chips and layer of nuts.
Pour can of Eagle Brand milk over this evenly.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Just brown lightly.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Add and mix pineapple, oranges, cottage cheese and nuts. Prepare pudding mix as directed on box.
Mix Cool Whip to pudding, then add other ingredients.

title: pie surprise
directions: Cook all ingredients over medium flame until it thickens. Pour into pie shell and let cool.
Serve topped with Cool Whip or whip cream.

title: strawberry surprise salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add strawberries and stir until thawed.
Add pineapple tidbits and juice; slice bananas into gelatin.
Add nuts.
Pour half of gelatin mixture into 8-inch square baking dish.
Chill until firm.
Spread sour cream over chilled gelatin and pour remaining gelatin over sour cream.
Chill until firm and cut into squares; serve on lettuce leaf.
Serves 9.

title: barbecue chuck roast
directions: Cook chuck roast until it falls apart (not dry).
Mix ingredients, except roast; bring to a boil.
Add meat and simmer. (Add canned tomatoes or tomato juice if too dry.)

title: streamlined bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Add sugar and salt.
Add shortening and half of the flour.
Beat 2 minutes.
Add remaining flour. Blend with a wooden spoon.
Cover.
Let rise - 30 minutes or until doubled.
Stir down by beating 25 strokes.
Spread batter in a greased loaf pan.
Batter will be sticky.
Let rise 40 minutes. Heat oven to 375 degrees.
Bake 45-50 minutes until brown.
Brush with butter.

title: pecan sticks
directions: Cream
butter
and
add sugar while beating constantly. Add all
remaining
ingredients and blend carefully.
Roll in pencil like
sticks
4-inches
long
or shape into crescents. Bake on cookie
sheet
in moderate oven at 350° until lightly browned, about 20 minutes.
Roll in confectioners sugar while still warm.

title: crazy cake(no eggs!)
directions: Mix together.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mini meat loaf supper
directions: Combine onion, ground beef, evaporated milk, bread crumbs, egg, garlic salt, salt and mustard.
Mix lightly but thoroughly. Shape mixture into 4 to 6 loaves. Brown meat loaves in oil, top and bottom. Add potatoes, onion and carrots. Add wine. Season with salt and pepper.
Cover and simmer about 1 hour. Add peas, if desired. Cover and simmer 10 minutes.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook spaghetti, rinse and drain well.
Add other ingredients and mix well.
Chill before serving.

title: tropical shrimp salad
directions: Amounts used will depend on number of people served.
A great tropical blend tossed with 3 types of lettuce and sprinkled with toasted coconut. Toss with your secret house dressing! (Kraft's Creamy Italian Dressing with real sour cream.)

title: white sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter, Crisco and both sugars.
Add eggs and beat well. Add flour sifted with cream of tartar and baking soda.
Add vanilla.
Chill several hours.
Roll dough in small balls and then in granulated sugar.
Place balls on greased cookie sheet. Flatten with a glass dipped in granulated sugar.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes or until light tan.
Place cookies on cooling rack.
This recipe makes quite a few.
It can easily be cut in half.

title: snack mix
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Makes a good trial mix.

title: spanish omelette
directions: Peel potatoes and cut into slices.
Fry the potatoes in very hot oil until they are medium golden and soft.
Drain the potatoes.
Beat the eggs with some salt.
Add the potatoes and mix.

title: microwave hershey bar mousse
directions: Combine chocolate bar pieces and water in medium micro-proof bowl.
Microwave on High (100%) for 1 1/2 to 2 minutes or until mixture is melted and smooth when stirred.
Stir in eggs. Microwave on Medium (50%) for 1 1/2 to 2 1/2 minutes or until mixture is hot; do not boil.
Cool slightly.
Whip cream until stiff; fold into cooled chocolate mixture.
Pour into 8-inch square pan.
Cover and freeze until firm.
Cut into squares. Makes 4 servings.

title: pita triangles
directions: Cut pita bread into triangles; leave out overnight to stale. Cook bacon very crispy.
Chop bacon, green pepper and onion and mix with Cheddar cheese and mayonnaise.
Put small amount of mixture on pita bread triangles.
Broil for a few minutes or until cheese melts and bread browns.

title: chocolate dessert
directions: Bake cake and cool.
Then in a large bowl, layer cake, Skors bits, chocolate syrup and Cool Whip.
Repeat each layer until finished, ending with the Cool Whip.
Garnish with Skors bits or chocolate curls.
Refrigerate.

title: creamy mashed potatoes
directions: Wash potatoes.
Leave skins on.
Quarter potatoes.
Heat 1 inch water to boiling.
Add potatoes.
Cover and bring to boil, cook 20 to 30 minutes until potatoes are soft with fork prick.
Remove from stove.
Slowly beat in milk and butter.
Add salt.
Sprinkle prepared potatoes with paprika and chopped parsley or chives for added flavor and color.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs and then bananas; add vanilla.
Mix dry ingredients together and add banana mixture. Add nuts, if desired.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: sausage and rice skillet dinner
directions: Cook sausage in 12-inch skillet.
Add onion; cook until tender.
Add rice.
Stir in remaining ingredients, except pepper. Bring to a boil, reduce heat, cover and simmer 20 minutes, or until liquid is absorbed.
Stir in pepper.
Remove from heat, cover and let stand for 5 minutes.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Sift flour with soda, salt and spices; set aside.
Cream butter with sugar until light.
Add vanilla and pumpkin.
Mix well.
Slowly add dry ingredients, then stir in raisins and nuts.
Drop by rounded teaspoons, 2-inches apart, on a greased baking sheet.
Bake for 15 minutes, until lightly browned. Transfer to a wire rack to cool.

title: sharon jarrels bacon-cheese snacks
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Spread generously on rye rounds. Sprinkle with bacon bits and bake at 300° for 20 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: low calorie vegetable soup
directions: *Carrots, broccoli, spinach, turnips, cauliflower, cabbage, beans, legumes, onions, mushrooms, corn, etc., may be used.

title: beer bread
directions: Flour, baking powder and salt makes self-rising flour.

title: corn scallop
directions: Do not drain corn.
Mix all ingredients together thoroughly. Bake at 350°
for 35 to 40 minutes.
Puffs up and gets a crusty top.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as directed; drain.
Mix with all other ingredients and place in a baking dish.
Top with crushed Ritz crackers or potato chips.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: easy potato bake
directions: Put Tater Tots into pan; add onion flakes and salt to your taste.
Mix soup, cheese and milk together and pour on top of taters.
Bake in 350° oven until done or microwave 15 minutes on High.
(Adjust milk to your preference.)

title: macaroni salad
directions: Boil vinegar and sugar.
Add to the rest of the ingredients with mayonnaise.
Refrigerate.

title: low-fat breakfast loaf
directions: Follow the directions for your bread machine.
This makes a good toast for breakfast.
It does not hold up well for sandwiches.

title: lemon jello salad
directions: Bring jello, marshmallows and pineapple to a boil.
Cool. Blend Cool Whip and cream cheese.
Add to jello mixture.
Chill until solid.

title: m&m's pie
directions: Grease a 9-inch pie plate.
In a medium sized mixing bowl, combine ground peanuts, oleo and sugar.
Press mixture firmly onto the bottom and up the sides of the pie plate.
Place in refrigerator for about 15 minutes.
Now mix coconut, Karo, peanut butter and the 3 tablespoons chopped peanuts.
Put the ice cream in a large chilled bowl and gently blend in the mixture.
Put into the chilled crust.
Sprinkle the top with chopped M&M's. Cover and freeze.
Make a day ahead.

title: taco dip
directions: In 1 1/2-quart casserole or pie plate, layer: 1/2 pound Velveeta (cut into cubes), 1/2 can stewed tomatoes (chopped), sprinkle with chili powder, 1/2 pound shredded Cheddar, 1/2 can chopped chilies and sprinkle with garlic powder.
Repeat layers. Bake at 350° until cheese is bubbly.

title: hungarian nut rolls
directions: Combine flour, margarine, sugar and salt until fine.
Dissolve yeast in milk.
Add to beaten eggs.
Add this to flour mixture. Knead until smooth.
Place in refrigerator overnight.
Roll out in sugar.
Fill with nut mixture.

title: the best apple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix first 8 ingredients by hand until smooth.
Mix cinnamon and sugar.
Grease and flour tube pan. Layer into pan: batter, apple, sugar/cinnamon mixture, batter, apple.
Finish with sugar/cinnamon mixture.

title: hershey fudge delicious brownies and icing
directions: Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cream together butter, sugar and eggs.
Add chocolate syrup, flour and nuts.
Pour evenly into pan and smooth top of mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Allow to cool completely.

title: lemon thyme sauce
directions: In a blender whip the cottage cheese.
Combine all of the ingredients in a small bowl.
Serve with fish or vegetables such as baked potatoes.
Or add 2 tablespoons more skim milk and serve as a salad dressing.
Yields 1/2 cup.

title: mom's cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.

title: cheese rolls
directions: Mix
cheese
and
butter.
Split
rolls horizontally in half. Spread
each
half
with
tablespoon cheese mixture. Replace tops.
Bake at 375° on ungreased baking sheet for 8 to 10 minutes or until cheese has melted and rolls are brown.

title: corn pudding
directions: Melt butter; stir in flour, salt and sugar.
Cook until bubbly.
Add milk and cook until thick.
Stir in the corn.
Stir in the eggs that have been beaten until frothy.
Pour into a well-buttered casserole and bake in a hot water bath at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: crabmeat dip
directions: Add all other ingredients to whipped cream cheese. Bake in small casserole for 30 minutes at 350°. Sprinkle with paprika. Serve hot with crackers or crunchy bread sticks for dipping.

title: spaghetti casserole
directions: Cook spaghetti; drain.
Toss with oil and black olives.
Brown hamburg; drain.
Add remaining ingredients; bring to boil for 10 minutes.
Layer spaghetti, then hamburg mixture times 2 layers. Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Remove foil; sprinkle with cheese and bake 10 minutes longer.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Bake crust for approximately 10 minutes.
Cook sausage and hash browns.
After crust is done, spread a layer of cheese, sausage and then hash browns (alternate each layer until ingredients have been used).
Top layer should be cheese.
Pour the egg mixture over the top.
Bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes or until the egg has stiffened.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Brown
hamburger
in skillet with onion.
Drain fat, if necessary.	 Add tomato soup and green beans.
Mix well.
Then put in	baking	dish
or pan.
Spread mashed potatoes over top and bake for about 45 minutes at 350°.

title: foolproof chocolate frosting
directions: Put first three ingredients in top of double boiler. Stir frequently and cook over (not in) boiling water for 8 to 10 minutes or until chocolate melts and mixture is smooth and thick. Remove from heat.

title: cake mix cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix ingredients well.
You can add nuts, raisins or chocolate chips.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix meat, 1 1/3 cups instant dry potatoes, egg, salt, pepper, onion, ketchup and milk.
Spread in an ungreased pie pan, 9 x 1 1/2-inch.
Bake uncovered 35 to 40 minutes.
Prepare remaining potatoes as directed on package for 4 servings.
Top baked meat with mashed potatoes.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake 3 to 4 minutes longer or until cheese melts.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: marinated tomatoes
directions: Peel the tomatoes and cut into wedges.
Put in a large bowl along with onion and green pepper.
Sprinkle on salt and pepper. Mix together the vinegar, water, sugar and salad oil.
Stir to dissolve sugar.
Pour over vegetables and chill.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake according to directions on box.
Pour one half the batter into greased, floured 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes (until set).
Melt caramels in heavy pan in 2 tablespoons milk.
Pour mixture over baked cake; sprinkle with chips and nuts. Pour remaining batter overall. Return to oven for about 15 minutes more.

title: ribbon jello salad
directions: You will need a 3-quart glass baking dish.

title: double buns
directions: Tips: If you wish, you can brush rolls with mixture of egg yolk, mixed with 1 tablespoon water before baking.

title: quick cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 2 cups of hot water, stir in cranberry sauce.
Cool.
Then drain pineapple and add to mixture.
Stir in the mashed bananas.
Top with whipped topping, cover and refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: quick caramel frosting
directions: Mix butter, dark sugar and water in saucepan.
Place over low heat and stir constantly until mixture comes to a boil; boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Add milk and vanilla.
Gradually add sugar, stirring until smooth.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Soak raisins in water.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Drain raisins and save 1/2 cup water.
Mix ingredients with raisins and reserved water.
Bake at 350° to 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Place on greased cookie sheet.

title: wake-up shakes
directions: The six most important words in the English language:
I admit I made a mistake.

title: date nut appetizer
directions: Make sure dates are pitted, then push a pecan half into each date.
Press together and roll in powdered sugar.
Arrange on tray and serve.

title: meat-rice casserole
directions: Prepare one pound of hamburger meat as for meat loaf with onions, bread crumbs, egg, tomato sauce, salt, pepper and green pepper, if desired.
Press into pie plate for crust.

title: benny's gumbo
directions: Cook white rice and set aside for later. Combine everything except pepper in a stock pot; simmer until chicken is done. Remove and discard celery, bay leaf and onion. Skin and bone chicken, dice meat into large chunks and place back into the stock.
Add ground peppers and salt to stock and bring back to a simmer.

title: fruity macaroon cookies
directions: In large bowl, combine all ingredients.
Mix thoroughly, making sure gelatin is blended evenly.
Cover and refrigerate at least 2 hours.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Shape into 1-inch balls and place on well greased baking sheets.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly brown around edges.
Remove from oven; cool on baking sheet 5 minutes before placing on wire rack to cool. Yields 4 dozen.

title: scandinavian salad
directions: Drain vegetables.
Mix together and add salt.
Stir well and chill for 1 hour.
Remove from refrigerator and drain.
Add remaining ingredients and stir until sugar is dissolved.
Pour into large dish; cover and refrigerate several hours.

title: ground beef "stroganoff"(weight watchers)
directions: In small saucepan heat 1 tablespoon margarine over medium heat until bubbly and hot; add flour and mix well.
Using wire whisk, gradually stir in milk and cook, stirring constantly, until mixture is smooth.
Stir in Worcestershire sauce, 1/2 teaspoon salt and the pepper.
Reduce heat to low and let simmer, stirring frequently, until sauce is thick, 10 to 15 minutes.

title: coquilles maison
directions: Melt butter; add garlic.
Pour into 1-quart casserole.
Add tomatoes and mash lightly; stir in wine and mushrooms.
If scallops are large, cut into bite-size pieces; add to casserole and mix.
Sprinkle with breadcrumbs and bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes, or until scallops break easily with a fork. Serve over a bed of rice or pasta.
Yields 4 servings.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together except Cheddar cheese.
Put in a greased 10-inch black skillet and sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix the pudding as directed using the 2 1/2 cups milk.
Add the 1/2 carton Cool Whip and sour cream.
Layer pudding, bananas and vanilla wafers. Cover with remaining Cool Whip.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients well. Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 1 hour.

title: surprise balls
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients in a large bowl; roll into balls. Place in refrigerator to cool overnight.
In the morning, melt paraffin and chocolate chips in a double boiler.
Spear balls with a toothpick, dip in chocolate and cool to dry on wax paper.

title: mashed potato soup
directions: Brown bacon until crisp.
Remove and let drain.
Add onions to drippings and saute for 2 to 3 minutes.
Drain fat off. Meanwhile, in saucepan, mix cold masted potatoes and soup until smooth.
Add milk gradually to desired consistency, stirring constantly.
Add bacon and onions; season with salt, pepper and parsley.
Heat through.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift all dry ingredients together, set aside.
Cream together margarine and sugar.
Blend in egg, milk and flavorings.
Blend in dry ingredients and chill for 2 hours. Roll out dough to approximately 1/8 inch thick.
Cut with cookie cutters, sprinkle with colored sugar and bake on ungreased cookie sheet for 6 to 8 minutes or until outer edge begins to brown.

title: potato casserole
directions: Shred cooked potatoes.
Melt butter in pan.
Add sour cream, soup, onions and cheese.
Stir until the cheese is melted and mix well with potatoes.
Put in baking dish.
Sprinkle with paprika. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 10.

title: mama's lovers knots
directions: Cut butter into flour, baking powder and salt mixture.
Add 3 eggs (beaten), sour cream and vanilla.
Mix together to a smooth dough.
Roll out on floured board.
Cut into 2 x 4-inch strips and make a cut in the middle; flip one end through.
Fry in deep oil, then dust with powdered sugar.
Good.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and beat for 10 minutes.
Grease and flour a Bundt pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pork roast
directions: Make slits in pork roast.
Slice garlic into 3 pieces each. Chop up pickled peppers.
Stuff a piece of garlic, pepper and onion into roast slits.
Sprinkle salt and pepper all over roast and rub in.
Sprinkle Texjoy
steak seasoning and rub in.

title: salmon steaks with mushroom stuffing
directions: Sprinkle salmon steaks with 1/4 tsp. salt.
Melt butter in skillet.
Saute onion in the butter until tender.
Combine onion with the crumbs, mushrooms, parsley, lemon juice (1/4 tsp.), salt and dash pepper.

title: vinegar salad
directions: Mix salad dressing, vinegar and sugar.
Toss other ingredients and pour dressing over.

title: corn salad
directions: Combine all ingredients. Chill, then serve.

title: apple pie in a jar
directions: Peel and slice apples, enough to pack into quart jars. Pack solid. Cover with syrup. Should be enough for at least 8 quarts. Cook syrup until thick and bubbly. Add lemon juice. Pour syrup over apples. Seal with lid and ring. Process 20 minutes in hot water bath.

title: buttermilk hot cakes
directions: Combine eggs, buttermilk and soda in a bowl; mix well. Sift dry ingredients together. Add flour mixture and shortening to buttermilk mixture; mix well. Pour onto hot griddle. Brown on both sides.

title: sugar balls
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Roll into balls (about a teaspoon each). Bake 20 minutes in a 350° oven.
Roll in powdered sugar after cooled.

title: easy beef jambalaya
directions: Heat oil to medium in heavy skillet.
Add beef, onion and garlic.
Cook until beef is evenly browned and drain.
Return to skillet and add tomatoes, field peas, salt and pepper to taste. Cook over low to medium heat until thoroughly heated and meat is completely done.
Serve over cooked rice.
Top with a sprinkling of green onions.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: cheese soup
directions: Dissolve bouillon in water.
Add potatoes, onion and mixed vegetables.
Cover and simmer 15 to 20 minutes or until vegetables and potatoes are tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Heat until Cheez Whiz is melted and soup is hot.
Good served with hot biscuits.

title: chicken and dressing casserole
directions: Put chicken pieces in bottom of 9 x 13-inch casserole dish. Spread soup over chicken.
Prepare dressing using broth and margarine.
(Add water if you don't have the necessary amount of broth.)
Spread dressing over soup and chicken.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: creamy au gratin potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease 1-quart casserole dish.
In 1-quart saucepan, over medium heat, cook frozen onion until tender.
Stir in undiluted soup and cream cheese cubes; cook stirring constantly, until smooth and hot.
In casserole dish, alternate a layer of frozen potatoes, then sauce ending with layer of sauce.
Cover and bake 45 minutes or until sauce is bubbly. Remove from oven and sprinkle with shredded Cheddar cheese.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream the shortening, peanut butter, brown sugar and white sugar.
Add 2 eggs and beat well.
Add flour, soda and vanilla and blend well.
Make into rolls and freeze.
Cook as needed.
Bake at 350° to 375° for 8 minutes.

title: caitlin's favorite pizza
directions: Heat oven to 375°. Spread dough on pizza pan. Spread garlic on dough. Sprinkle 1 cup Mozzarella and 1 ounce Romano on dough. Place sliced tomatoes on top of cheese, then cover with remaining cheese. Bake for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: texas pepper steak
directions: Slice beef across grain into thin strips.
Cook 1/2 beef in 1 tablespoon hot oil until browned.
Remove.
Set aside.
In same skillet with 1 tablespoon hot oil, cook sweet peppers, onion, oregano, garlic powder and pepper until vegetables are tender, stirring often.
Stir in soup and water.
Heat to boiling.
Return beef to skillet.
Heat thoroughly.
Serve over rice or spaghetti with garlic bread.
Serves 4.

title: coke salad
directions: Heat Coke and dissolve jello in hot Coke.
Add chopped cherries and nuts; chill.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Mix the plain flour, butter and nuts together.
Press into bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish and bake 20 minutes at 350°. Let cool.
Mix softened cream cheese, sugar and 1/2 of the Cool Whip.
Spread over crust. Mix chocolate and vanilla pudding with milk.
Spread over cheese mixture.
Top with remaining Cool Whip.

title: taco lasagna
directions: Brown meat and onion; drain.
Add taco seasoning, sauce, garlic powder and chili powder.
Add 1 to 1 1/2 cans water.

title: spinach supreme
directions: Cook spinach according to package.
Saute mushrooms in 1/4 cup butter.
Combine mayonnaise, sour cream and 2/3 cup Parmesan cheese.
Stir in spinach, mushrooms and artichokes.
Put into buttered 13 x 9-inch pan.
Put tomato slices on top.
Melt the remaining 1/2 cup butter.
Stir in bread crumbs and remaining 1/3 cup Parmesan cheese.
Sprinkle crumb mixture on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: apricot jello mold
directions: Mix Jell-O, sugar, boiling water and pineapple.
Refrigerate until thickened.
Mix cream cheese with reserved pineapple juice and Cool Whip.
Mix all together and refrigerate.

title: chicken parmesan(geppetto's favorite)
directions: Mix bread crumbs and 3 tablespoons Parmesan cheese together. Dip chicken pieces in eggs, then in crumb mixture.
Fry until golden brown.
Put pieces in baking dish and spread tomato sauce over all.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella and Parmesan cheeses.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 4.

title: monkey bread
directions: Coat each biscuit piece with mix of first sugar and cinnamon. Drop in Bundt pan.
Sprinkle top with nuts.
Boil last 3 ingredients.
Pour over biscuits and bake 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: pistachio jello salad
directions: Mix pudding and pineapple (using syrup).
Add cottage cheese, then Cool Whip.
Chill and serve.
Makes 5 to 7 servings.

title: cafe borgia
directions: Pour equal parts coffee and hot chocolate into cups.
Top with sweetened whipped cream and sprinkle with grated orange peel and shaved sweet chocolate.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Blend together margarine and Crisco.
Sift together flour, sugar, cocoa, salt and baking soda.
Add sifted ingredients alternately with the milk, eggs, one at a time, and vanilla.
Mix well and pour into greased and lightly floured tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: chicken curry
directions: Melt butter over low heat in heavy saucepan.
Saute onion and curry in melted butter.
Blend in flour and seasonings.
Cook over low heat until mixture is smooth and bubbly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in chicken broth and milk.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Boil 1 minute.
Add chicken and lemon juice.
Pour over rice and serve.

title: sausage balls
directions: Scramble sausage in pan and slightly brown.
Pour off all grease.
Add Bisquick, cheese and water.
Make in small balls. Put on slightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° to 450°
for 12 to 15 minutes, or until brown.

title: cake cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients well. You can add other ingredients, such as nuts, raisins or chocolate chips.
Drop teaspoons of dough onto an ungreased cookie sheet about 2-inches apart.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.

title: strawberry shortcake
directions: Mix first four ingredients well.
Add shortening; cut into pea size balls.
Add buttermilk; mix well.
Divide into 4 or 5 balls and roll out about 1/4 inch.
Then turn dough over a pie plate. Cook at 425° until golden brown.

title: dijon-tarragon chicken
directions: Dredge chicken in flour mixed with black pepper and a tiny bit of salt.
Add oil to pan with dash of sesame oil, dash of tarragon vinegar and touch of garlic.
Saute chicken hot and fast, 2 to 3 minutes on each side.
Remove chicken and set aside.

title: butterscotch haystacks
directions: Melt butterscotch bits in top of double boiler, stirring occasionally to blend.
Meanwhile, combine nuts and chow mein noodles; place in preheated low oven (200°).
Add warmed nuts and noodles to melted butterscotch and stir until all are coated. Quickly drop with a dessert spoon onto waxed paper-lined baking sheet to form little haystacks.
If nuts and noodles are warmed, butterscotch will not set until all the stacks are spooned out. Makes 48 haystacks or about 1 pound.
You can substitute 1 1/2 cups salted peanuts for the cashews, if you wish.

title: crab on english muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Spread on English muffins.
Put in freezer until firm.
When firm, cut into 4 wedges.
Then broil until golden brown.

title: ryan's pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Mix cake mix following directions on the box.
Melt the butter and pour into cake pan (10-inch cake pan).
Sprinkle brown sugar onto the bottom of the pan.
Put cherry in middle of pan.
Arrange pineapple on the bottom.
Pour the cake mix into pan and bake according to directions on the box.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Layer 1/3 of potatoes in buttered 8-cup baking dish.
Combine flour, salt and pepper.
Sprinkle 1/2 over potatoes; repeat layers, ending with potatoes on top; dot with oleo.

title: ricotta cake
directions: Mix cake mix according to directions. Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Mix remaining ingredients and pour over cake mixture. (When baked, the cheese mixture will drop and the cake will rise to the top.) Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: hazel's chili sauce
directions: Wrap pickling spices, seed and cinnamon in cheesecloth. Combine sugar, salt, tomatoes, onions, peppers and hot pepper. Cook
gently
minutes.	Add
spice
bag.
Cook	until very thick.
As	mixture thickens, stir good to prevent from sticking. Add
vinegar and water; boil until thick as you want it. Add to sterilized jars and seal with lids.

title: whipping cream pound cake
directions: Put all ingredients into mixing bowl at once and beat.
Grease and flour tube pan; pour batter into it and put into cold oven. Set oven at 325° and bake for 1 1/2 hours.

title: orange sweet potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook and cut potatoes in pieces or can be mashed.
Mix and simmer over low heat until slightly thickened. Place potatoes in casserole dish and cover with sauce.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: deer burger or salami
directions: Mix and form into rolls.
Wrap in wax paper and refrigerate for 24 hours.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 to 1 3/4 hours.

title: hot apple cranberry wassail
directions: Mix in a large container.
Bring to a boil and serve.

title: greek ziti salad
directions: In small bowl combine vinegar, dijon, basil, oil, and salt. Mix well and set aside. Cook ziti according to package directions. Drain, rinse with cold water and drain again. Place in large bowl. Toss pasta with dressing. Tear lettuce into bite sized pieces and arrange on four plates. Mound pasta on lettuce and top with tomatoes. Sprinkle with cheese and olives. Drizzle with remains dressing. Season with pepper.

title: christmas rock candy
directions: Stir first 3 ingredients over medium heat until dissolved. Boil without stirring until 310° is reached.
Cook at same temperature until you can drop some in cold water and it forms a hard crack.
Remove from heat and add cinnamon and food coloring.

title: crabmeat treats
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Water chestnuts are optional.
Bake in a 400° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.
(By just adding some bread crumbs, it makes wonderful stuffed mushrooms.)

title: triple chocolate fudge cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease a 9 x 3-inch spring-form pan. Line bottom with waxed paper; grease paper and dust with cocoa. Wrap outside and bottom of pan with heavy-duty foil.

title: grilled swordfish a la cancun
directions: Marinate fillets in oil, garlic and pepper for 1 1/2 hours.

title: chinese casserole
directions: Fry sausage; drain and set aside.
Saute vegetables, then add sausage and vegetables together.
Bring water to a boil.
Add soup mix to water and dissolve.
Add uncooked rice to vegetables and sausage.
Cover and cook 45 minutes at 350°.
Remove cover and cook an additional 15 minutes.
Makes 12 to 14 servings.

title: corn relish topping
directions: Mix all ingredients in medium bowl.
Chill.
Serve as topping for hot dogs, hamburgers or as a side condiment.

title: pineapple cake and topping
directions: Mix flour, 2 cups sugar, eggs and pineapple together; pour into well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Cool slightly.

title: tropical punch
directions: Mix together.
Makes 2 1/2 to 3 gallons.

title: overnight casserole
directions: Pour boiling water over rice.
Let stand for 10 minutes. Drain.
Brown hamburger and onion; drain.
Dissolve bouillon cubes in 1 cup boiling water.
Stir in rice, almonds, mushrooms, meat and soup.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake 2 hours at 350°, covered.
Remove cover last 30 minutes.

title: squash dressing(servings:  8)
directions: Mix all ingredients together in casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: shrimp mold
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 1/4 cup water.
Boil soup, gelatine and cream cheese on low until melted.
(If any lumps, beat with beater.)
Cool.
Add remaining ingredients and pour into greased mold.
Best if made the day before.

title: spiced peaches
directions: Drain peaches, reserving syrup.
Combine syrup, vinegar, cinnamon sticks and cloves in a saucepan.
Bring mixture to a boil and lower heat.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Pour this hot mixture over peach halves and let cool.
Chill thoroughly before serving. Store in refrigerator.

title: topsy-turvy coffee ring
directions: Dissolve yeast in the water.
Combine shortening, milk, sugar and salt.
Blend in eggs and the dissolved yeast.
Add flour; mix well.
Place in greased bowl and cover.
Let rise in warm place until double in bulk, 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: chocolate banana pops
directions: You will also need 6 wooden sticks.

title: apricot cheese fruitcake
directions: Grease and flour a 10-inch fluted tube pan.
Set aside.
In saucepan, combine water, apricots, raisins and the 1/4 cup sugar. Bring to boil.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 15 to 20 minutes. Drain well.
Set aside.

title: banana loaf
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder, soda and salt. Stir in oats.
Add shortening, eggs, milk and banana, stirring only until dry ingredients are blended.
Fill a greased loaf pan 1/2 full or put in small muffin tins.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 50 to 60 minutes.
Remove from pan immediately; cool. For ease in slicing, wrap cooled bread and store one day.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook and drain noodles.
Add tuna, onion and milk.
Place in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Spread cheese over top and spread potato chips over cheese.
Bake at 350° until bubbling, about 15 minutes.

title: better than ------ cake
directions: Bake Duncan Hines cake mix according to directions.
Cook pineapple and sugar, bringing to a boil.
Boil for 5 minutes. Cover baked cake with pineapple-sugar mixture.
Next layer the prepared instant vanilla pudding mix over the pineapple mixture. Next layer with sliced bananas.
Next layer with Cool Whip.
Next layer with coconut.
Next layer with chopped pecans.
Keep refrigerated.

title: sour cream chicken enchiladas
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Saute onion in butter until tender. Stir in chicken and add 1/2 cup sour cream, 1 can chicken soup, mushrooms, green chilies and seasonings.
Cook over low heat and stir until well heated.
Soften tortillas by frying each side in oil in large skillet.

Fill tortillas with a scant 1/4 cup mixture and top with Monterey Jack cheese.	Roll up and place seam side down in 9 x 13 dish that has been spread with 1 cup sour cream. Combine remaining can chicken soup with remaining sour cream and Cheddar cheese.
Spoon over tortillas and bake uncovered for 35 minutes.

title: party ball cheese
directions: Place cheese in small mixing bowl.
Let stand at room temperature until softened.
Add onion and Worcestershire sauce. Blend on low speed.
Beat on medium speed until fluffy, scraping sides and bottom of bowl.
Cover and chill at least 8 hours. Shape mixture into 1 large bowl or into 30 to 36 (1-inch) balls. Chill for 2 hours.

title: asparagus almondine
directions: Lay asparagus in oblong baking dish.
Dilute soup with asparagus juice, salt and pepper and pour over asparagus. Sprinkle bread crumbs over soup, then sprinkle with grated cheese. Saute almonds in butter and sprinkle over cheese.
Bake 35 minutes in 300° oven.

title: grandma kate's green bean casserole
directions: Mix all together and bake at 375°.

title: oatmeal muffins with raisins
directions: Combine the first 7 ingredients in a large bowl.
Make a well in the center of mixture.
Stir in raisins.
Combine buttermilk and next 4 ingredients; stir well.
Add to dry ingredients, stirring just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Divide batter evenly among 12 muffin cups coated with cooking spray.
Bake at 400° for 18 minutes or until wooden pick inserted comes out clean. Remove from pans immediately.
Cool on wire rack.

title: delicious scalloped potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes and slice 1/4-inch thick.
Layer in a greased casserole in order given.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes uncovered, then 15 minutes covered.

title: bet's peanut butter candy
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa and butter. Add enough milk to make a dough. Roll out on wax paper dusted with powdered sugar (from another box). Spread peanut butter over this. Roll up like jelly roll. Cut into slices. Place onto plate in single layer. Refrigerate until hard. Store in closed container with wax paper between layers. Store in refrigerator. YUMMY!!!!!!!! Makes 60 servings. Preparation time: 0:45.

title: dump cake
directions: Dump cherry pie filling in the bottom of 13 x 9 pan. Spread can of crushed pineapple over cherries. Sprinkle cake mix evenly over mixture. Pour melted butter over cake mix. Sprinkle coconut and nuts over top. Bake at 350°
for one hour or until golden brown. Serves 12.

title: cauliflower cheese soup
directions: Combine onion and 3 tablespoons of chicken broth.
Cook, stirring occasionally, 4 or 5 minutes.
Add a bit more broth.
Add remainder of broth, potatoes, cauliflower, mustard, celery seed and pepper.
Bring to a boil over high heat.
Lower heat, cover and simmer 11 to 14 minutes.
Remove pot from heat.
Puree three quarters of vegetables and liquid in blender.
Return puree to pot with remaining vegetables and liquid.
Add milk and stir to mix well.
Heat soup to a gentle simmer.
Add cheese to soup.
Stir well.
Cook additional minutes, but not to boil.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: white batter bread
directions: Sprinkle yeast on warm water.
Stir until dissolved.
Add shortening, salt, sugar and 1 1/2 cups of the flour.
Beat 2 minutes, using medium speed on electric mixer or 300 vigorous strokes by hand.
Scrape sides and bottom of bowl frequently.
Add remaining flour; blend in with spoon until smooth.
Scrape batter from sides of bowl.
Cover; let rise in warm place, free from draft, until doubled, about 30 minutes.
Spread batter evenly in greased loaf pan.
Batter will be sticky.
Let rise in warm place until batter reaches within 1-inch of top of pan, about 40 minutes.
Bake in moderate oven (375°) for 45 to 50 minutes, or until brown.
Test to see if it's done by tapping top of crust; it should sound hollow.
Remove from pan at once.
Brush top with melted butter or margarine.
Cool on rack.

title: how to make friends
directions: Mix all together and go around making as many friends as possible.

title: dream pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour, salt, pineapple and cherries in a large saucepan.
Stir well.
Cook over medium heat until thick and bubbly.
Remove from heat.
Add Jell-O, stirring well.
Allow mixture to cool.
Thinly slice bananas and arrange in each graham cracker shell.
Pour fruit mixture evenly into pastry shells. Refrigerate a couple hours.
Prepare Cool Whip and spread over pies and top with nuts.
Makes 2 pies.

title: spinach balls
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl.
Refrigerate 1 hour. Form into balls.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: sonora chicken
directions: Cut chicken into 1-inch pieces.
Mix together both soups, chili beans, taco sauce, onion and milk.

title: old-fashioned lemon pie
directions: Mix sugar, salt, cornstarch, 2 tablespoons of milk and egg yolks until it makes a paste.
Add scalded milk; stir into paste. Cook until thick.
Take off heat; add lemon juice, peel and oleo. Beat with mixer until very creamy and pour into baked shell.
Top with meringue and brown.
Makes a 9-inch pie.

title: chalupa delicious
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large 6 qt. pot and cover with water.
Cook on high until boiling.
Reduce heat and cook 6 hours. Remove bones and fat and tear meat.
Cook 2 hours longer.
Serve with corn chips, grated cheese, shredded lettuce, chopped onions, diced tomatoes and drizzle taco sauce on top.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients together in large bowl.
In another bowl, mix the remaining ingredients.
Beat slightly and pour over the flour mixture; beat until smooth.
Add raisins and nuts, if desired.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: truly delicious baked apples
directions: Place apples in 2-quart round covered casserole.
Spoon juice over apples.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and nutmeg.
Cover and bake in microwave on High for 9 to 11 minutes, or in conventional oven at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cream cheese and jam turnovers
directions: Measure warm water into large bowl.
Sprinkle in yeast; stir until dissolved.
Add warm milk, brown sugar, salt, margarine, egg and 2 cups flour; beat until smooth.
Stir in enough remaining flour to make stiff dough.
On floured surface, knead 8 to 10 minutes.
Set in greased bowl; turn to grease top.
Cover; let rise in warm draft-free place until doubled, about 1 hour.
Punch dough down.
Roll to 24 x 12-inch rectangle.
Cut into 4 inch squares. Beat cream cheese to soften.
Add sugar, flour, vanilla and egg; mix thoroughly.
Spoon 1 tablespoon on center of squares.
Top with 1 to 1 1/2 teaspoons of jam.
Overlap 2 opposite corners; seal. Set on greased baking sheets.
Cover and let rise until doubled. Bake at 375° for 15 minutes or until browned.
Cool.
Frost with confectioners sugar glaze.

title: german lentil soup
directions: In a 5-quart Dutch oven over medium-high heat, fry bacon until lightly browned; push to side of pan.
Add onions, carrots and celery.

Cook over medium heat until onions are tender, about 5 minutes. Add ham bone, lentils, pepper, thyme, bay leaves, hot water and 2 teaspoons salt. Cover and simmer over low heat 1 hour or until lentils are tender. Discard bay leaves.
Remove ham bone to cutting board and cut off any meat. Cut into small pieces. Stir meat into soup.
Add lemon juice and salt to taste.

title: cottage cheese casserole
directions: Saute diced onion in margarine.
Beat eggs.
Mix all ingredients together.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes until browned.

title: tabouleh (salad)
directions: Mix lemon juice, olive oil and bulgur; set aside.
The bulgur will absorb the liquid.
Finely chop parsley and scallions, red onions and pepper.
Mix together with bulgur mixture.
Finely chop and add tomatoes.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Refrigerate.
You can use more or less of the different vegetables to suit your taste.

title: fresh rhubarb betty
directions: Mix all together but bread crumbs.
Layer mixture and bread crumbs in baking dish.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes, covered. Uncover; bake for 10 minutes longer and brown.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Cook beans; drain and put in casserole dish.
Cover with soup, croutons, onions and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: zesty chicken wings
directions: In a saucepan, combine the first 8 ingredients. Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, for 15 to 20 minutes or until thickened.

title: potato casserole
directions: Peel and thinly slice potatoes and parboil for 5 minutes in water to cover with salt added.
Heat cream of chicken soup mixed with milk.
Add cheese and onion.
Layer the drained potatoes and soup mixture in a greased 2-quart casserole, starting with potatoes.
Top with a ring of potato slices and a little cheese and paprika.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: sharon's dip
directions: Cook hamburger and sausage until all pink is gone from meat. Drain off excess fat.
Put cheese and picante sauce in pan.
Cook until cheese melts.
Add to meat and serve with chips.
Serve warm.

title: cinnamon cookies
directions: Cream margarine until light and fluffy.
Mix artificial sweetener with vanilla and milk or one of the other liquids.
Stir into flour mixture (flour, baking powder and salt) and mix well. Shape dough into 30 even-sized balls and place on cookie sheet. Flatten balls with fork dipped in cold water.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: fairy pudding
directions: Dissolve sugar in 1/4 cup milk and add 2 egg yolks; beat. Add 3/4 cup milk and cook in double boiler until spoon is coated. Dissolve 1 envelope gelatin in a little water.
Add this to the custard and cook 1-2 minutes; let cool.
Add vanilla.
Fold in (do not stir) 1 beaten egg white and the Cool Whip.
Line flat baking dish with graham cracker crumbs.
Place crushed pineapple over crumbs, pour in pudding and cover top with graham cracker crumbs.

title: sherried beef
directions: Place in casserole in order listed.
Cover tightly and bake at 325° for 3 hours.
Serve with fine noodles or rice.
Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: overnight coffee cake
directions: Mix sugar with cinnamon.
Coat Bundt pan with Pam.
Put frozen rolls in bottom.
Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon mixture. Sprinkle with brown sugar, then nuts, then pudding mix.
Cut margarine on top.
Cover with wax paper, then kitchen towel.
Let rise overnight.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
After 5 minutes, invert.

title: shaving cream salad
directions: Mix together the cream cheese, mayonnaise and pineapple.
Let stand overnight or at least 3 to 4 hours.
Then mix in marshmallows and cherries.

title: icebox cake
directions: Make the vanilla pudding according to manufacturer's directions.
Follow the manufacturer's directions for the chocolate, but use 2 1/2 cups milk.
Line the bottom of an 8 x 8-inch square inch pan with graham crackers.
Pour 1/2 of the chocolate pudding in the pan.
Place a second layer of graham crackers on top of pudding.
Pour the entire vanilla pudding over the crackers.
Repeat with crackers and the remainder of the chocolate pudding.
Chill.
Top with whipped cream and serve.

title: taco casserole
directions: Note:
Amount in parentheses is for two 1 1/2-quart casseroles.

title: the best salsa(servings:  4)
directions: Mix all together and refrigerate.
Great on your roast beef tacos!

title: stir-fry beef or chicken
directions: Brown meat in large skillet.
Slice the vegetables into pieces.
(Add the amount of vegetables you need according to the amount you're serving.)
Add the remaining ingredients to the meat.
Simmer over medium heat until tender.
Serve over rice if you desire.

title: pumpkin dump cake
directions: Mix eggs, pumpkin, sugar, milnot, cinnamon, salt and pumpkin pie spice together.
Pour into ungreased 13 x 9 inch cake pan. Crumble cake mix on top.
Drizzle melted oleo over cake mix.
Top with pecans.
Bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Real good with Cool Whip.

title: no crust green chili pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine cheeses and distribute in a buttered deep dish pie plate.
Beat eggs with flour, mustard and cream until thick and well blended.
Stir in chilies.
Pour over cheeses.
Bake about 40 minutes, until set and lightly browned. Drizzle salsa over the top and top with jalapeno slices, if desired.
Cut into wedges after letting sit 10 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: macaroni hamburger hot dish
directions: Mix macaroni and tomato soup. Mix taco seasoning into browned beef. Add to the macaroni. Mix well. Top with cheese. Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: marshmallow cream(no refrigeration needed)
directions: Whip first 2 ingredients at low speed.
Heat next 2 ingredients to approximately 210°.
Add heated mixture to the beaten egg whites and whip again on high speed until light and fluffy.
Add vanilla.
Store in covered container.
Use in any recipe calling for Marshmallow Cream.

title: fajitas
directions: Cook chicken in a skillet for 7 minutes.
Add Miracle Whip, peppers and garlic.
Stir them together and add lime juice, cumin, cilantro and hot peppers.
Warm flour tortillas in microwave about 20 seconds, then place some of the chicken mixture in the center of the tortilla.
Place lettuce and sour cream on top of chicken, wrap and eat.
Salsa can be added for extra flavor.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Grease casserole dish and add raw meat. Blend soups and pour over meat.
Top with Tater Tots. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: meat loaf everybody loves!
directions: Set oven at 350°.
Mix beef, crumbs, cheese, onion, green pepper and seasonings.
Combine eggs and tomato sauce.
Mix with meat combination.
Shape meat mixture into two loaves in buttered, shallow pan.
Bake about 1 hour or until browned and done through. Serve hot.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Grease a cookie sheet and spread out the crescent rolls. Press together.
Bake for 8 minutes at 375°.
Combine the next 3 ingredients; spread on cooled crust.
Top with chopped vegetables and cheese.

title: mama lucy's pound cake
directions: *Do not change to low fat, or oleo.
It just isn't the same.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Spray baking dish with Pam.
Cover bottom dish with sliced bread.
Brown sausage and crumble over bread.
Beat eggs; add salt and pepper.
Pour over sausage.
Sprinkle grated cheese on top. Cover with plastic wrap.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake next morning at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: french toast
directions: Beat egg, milk, salt and nutmeg together with a fork in a small bowl.
Melt the butter in a skillet until it sizzles.
Pour the egg mixture into a shallow dish large enough for bread to lay flat, one slice at a time.
Put a slice of bread into the egg mixture and gently turn it to cover both sides.
Place bread gently into the hot skillet.
Turn heat down to medium.
Cook until the bread turns light brown.
You can check by lifting up edge of bread with a turner, then turn bread over to cook other side.
Coat second slice with egg mixture and cook like the first piece.
Serve immediately with your choice of syrup, jam, jelly or powdered sugar.

title: okra fritters
directions: Mix well and fry in hot oil.
Drain on paper towel.

title: sweet and tangy barbecue sauce
directions: This sauce is good when baking or grilling chicken or pork.

title: baked scallops
directions: Dip scallops in oil, then roll in crumbs.
Spread out on cookie sheet.
Bake at 450° for 12 minutes.
Serve with slice of lemon.

title: chicken cheese ball
directions: Combine chicken, dressing mix and cream cheese in a mixing bowl.
Beat on medium speed of electric mixer until blended. Shape into ball and roll in pecans.

title: veal parmesan
directions: Saute
onion and garlic in oil.
Add remaining ingredients (except
cheese
and
veal)
and simmer 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
Pound
thin the veal.
Dip into egg, then bread crumbs.
Fry
until brown on both sides.
Place veal in baking dish.
Cover
each	with
generous	slice
of cheese and spoon sauce over	each
piece.
Bake at 350° to 400° for 20 minutes. Serve with garlic bread and salad.

title: easy margaritas
directions: Mix all in large pitcher.

title: lazy man's dessert
directions: Melt margarine in casserole dish.
Combine flour, sugar, baking powder and milk.
Pour evenly over melted margarine but do not stir.
Add 2 1/2 cups fruit, rhubarb sauce or 1/2 cup strawberries.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve with ice cream, half and half, milk or Cool Whip.

title: pork chop supreme
directions: Put in a slow cooker at 8 a.m.
Have supper at 5 p. m.

title: rice and chicken casserole
directions: Mix together the rice and soups.
Put 3 to 4 pieces of chicken on top.
Cover with lid or foil and bake 1 hour at 350° or until chicken is tender.
Uncover part of time to brown chicken.

title: broccoli delight
directions: Finely chop the broccoli tops and tender parts of top stems. Slice and dice the red onion.
Mix well and refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Saute onions and celery in 2 tablespoons butter.
Spread half of the stuffing mix in the bottom of an oiled baking dish.
Heat 1/2 cup butter and broth; pour over crumbs in a large bowl.
Mix chicken, onions, celery, mayonnaise, salt and pepper; spread over crumbs.
Blend eggs and milk; pour over mixture.
Cover. Refrigerate overnight.
Remove 1 hour before baking.
Spread remaining crumbs over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: rocks
directions: Cream butter and sugar; beat with eggs.
Add soda, dissolved with hot water, then add flour.
Stir in dates and nuts.
Drop in very small dabs (size of walnuts) on greased cookie sheet.
Allow for spreading.
Bake in hot oven.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: quick garden cheese soup
directions: In large kettle or Dutch oven, cook celery and onion in margarine until tender.
Stir in flour until smooth.
Gradually add water, then bouillon, pepper and vegetables.
Bring to a boil. Reduce heat; cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Add milk and cheese. Cook and stir until cheese melts and soup is hot (do not boil). Garnish, as desired.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: orange syrup
directions: Cook until butter is melted.
Remove from heat and cool 10 minutes.
Beat until slightly thickened.
Serve warm.

title: spinach balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together; let set in refrigerator for 2 hours.
Shape into small balls and place on cookie sheet in freezer.
When ready to serve, bake for 20 minutes at 375°.

title: microwave oven fried chicken
directions: Mix baking mix, paprika, salt and pepper.
Coat chicken. Arrange chicken pieces, skin sides up, in rectangular, microwavable dish, 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inches with thickest parts toward edges.
Cover with waxed paper and microwave on High (100%) 10 minutes.
Rotate dish 1/2 turn.
Microwave until done, 8 to 10 minutes longer.
Makes 6 servings.

title: baked stew beef
directions: Mix all ingredients in a Dutch oven.
Cover and bake at 300° for 5 hours, stirring once or twice.

title: cheese grits souffle
directions: Cook grits as directed on package.
Add eggs and Cheez Whiz; mix well.
Pour in a greased Pyrex dish and bake at 350° for about 1 hour (put Pyrex on cookie sheet with water in it so it will not burn grits on the bottom).
Check often 45 minutes.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: Dice all vegetables.
I put through my food processor.
Add all vegetables to the can of chicken broth. Simmer until vegetables are tender.
Mix milk with flour slowly.
Combine with broth and vegetables.
Boil and let thicken for 5 to 10 minutes. Add cheese.
Simmer for 10 minutes.

title: new perry hotel style yams
directions: Shred potatoes.
Soak
in salted water (1/2 cup salt to 2 quarts water).
Soak
for
to 1 1/2 hours;
wash.
Drain. Place in uncovered
pan.	Pour syrup over (3 cups sugar, 1 1/2 cups water
and	1
cup	Karo)
potatoes.
Boil 5 minutes over medium heat.
Add orange juice, grated orange rind and butter. Bake in 350° oven 35 minutes or until potatoes are transparent and syrup is lightly thickened.

title: egg mcmuffins
directions: Cook scrambled eggs.
Use bacon or ham for the McMuffins.
Use hamburger buns.
Flatten with your hand and put in the toaster. Put on a paper plate 1/2 of the bun, then eggs, ham and top with a piece of cheese.
Microwave just until the cheese melts over the eggs.
Top with the other bun slice.

title: butterfingers delight
directions: Take 9 x 13-inch pan, layer with little pieces of sponge cake, then crumble Butterfinger candy bars on top (saving about 1/2 a bar for the top).
Mix 1 large box of instant vanilla pudding; spread over top of Butterfinger and cake.
Then spread Cool Whip on top, sprinkled with crumbled 1/2 Butterfinger bar.

title: jalapeno and rice casserole
directions: Mix peppers and sour cream.
Butter large casserole pan.
Pour in 1/3 rice, 1/2 cheese, then peppers/sour cream; continue, ending with rice.

title: red punch
directions: In a large punch bowl pour all three ingredients. I freeze a jello mold ring full of this to keep punch cold.

title: chess (egg) pie
directions: Cream the oleo and sugar. Add beaten whole eggs, vanilla and vinegar. Pour into 2 unbaked pie shells (8-inch). Start at 350° for 10 minutes; turn down to 300° for 45 minutes.

title: sugared pecans
directions: Whip the egg white and 1 tablespoon water until frothy.
Add pecans.
In another bowl, mix sugar, cinnamon and salt together. Add dry mixture to frothy mixture and stir.
Pour
onto greased (with margarine) cookie sheet.
Cook for 1 hour at 250°.
Turn every 15 minutes until done.

title: crawfish bisque
directions: First you make a roux using flour and oil (to be just "wet" enough).
Have oil hot, then add flour.
Keep on medium heat, not hot.
Cook to color of caramel.
Have water ready in a big pot (8-quart) and put roux in so it doesn't continue to brown.
Add the chopped vegetables and cook down until thickened.
Add crawfish with their fat and cook 15 minutes.
Add salt and pepper.

title: hush puppies
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Add onion.
Beat egg and add milk.
Then add dry ingredients.
Drop by teaspoons in hot oil (375°) and fry for 5 minutes or until brown.
Yield: 1 1/2 dozen.

title: mile-high biscuits
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Mix well.
Cut in shortening until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Combine egg and milk.
Add to flour.
Knead mixture 8 to 10 times.
Roll dough to 1 inch thickness.
Cut with 2 1/2-inch biscuit cutter.
Place biscuits on an ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Yields 15 biscuits.

title: gooeys
directions: Put egg and vanilla in bowl; mix and add dry ingredients. Stir in nuts.
Spoon into 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes.
Done when still soft in middle.

title: towboat gumbo
directions: Boil chicken and set aside.
In a large pot mix flour and cooking oil and cook over low to medium heat until color of chocolate.
Turn off heat and add onions, bell pepper, and celery. Cook this until soft, stirring constantly.
When soft, add water 1 cup at a time very slow.
When everything is mixed, add chicken and bay leaf, salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer for 2 hours.
15 minutes before serving, add fil.
Serve over freshly cooked rice.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Press crescent rolls in 11 x 15-inch pan and bake at 350° for 13 minutes.
Mix together next six ingredients.
Chop vegetables. Let crust cool before putting mixture and vegetables on.

title: baked lima beans
directions: Soak beans overnight in cold water with 2 tablespoons baking soda.
Next day, rinse and cook until tender, about 1 hour.
Keep 2 cups of broth.
Mix ingredients with beans.
Line baking dish with bacon strips.
Pour in bean mixture; using only 1 cup broth. Add bacon strips to top.
Bake at 350° for 2 to 3 hours.
Add remaining broth if necessary.

title: apple coffee cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients and set aside.
In a large bowl, add oil, vanilla, orange juice and eggs. Beat at medium speed for 2 minutes. Mix dry ingredients with rest, except apples.
Grease a Bundt pan or tube pan.
Layer batter and apples. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: raspberry oatmeal bars
directions: Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
In a large bowl, combine dry cake mix and oats.
Stir in melted butter until mixture is crumbly.
Place 1/2 of crumb mixture (about 3 cups) into pan. Press firmly to cover bottom.
Combine preserves and water.
Spoon over crumb mixture in pan and spread evenly.
Cover with remaining crumb mixture.
Pat firmly to make top even.
Bake in preheated oven at 375° for 20 minutes.
Top should be light brown.
Cool completely.
Cut into bars.
Makes 3 dozen bars.

title: quick fruit-flavored sherbet
directions: Dissolve soft drink and sugar in milk (mixture may appear curdled).
Pour into bowl.
Freeze until partially firm.
Spoon into chilled bowl and beat until smooth, but not melted.
Freeze until firm.

title: mother's meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients except tomato sauce.
Mold into loaf in shallow baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Drain excess fat from pan.
Pour tomato over loaf.
Bake 30 minutes longer, basting occasionally.
Serves 4.

title: garlic string beans
directions: Heat oil.
Saute garlic and beans.
Add thyme, salt and pepper. Add water and vegetable bouillon.
Bring to boil.
Simmer 20 to 30 minutes until beans are tender.
Add dash of lemon and serve. Serves 4.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Beat cream cheese; add powdered sugar.
Beat until fluffy.
Mix peanut butter and milk until smooth.
Add to cream cheese mixture. Add Cool Whip.
Mix well.
Pour into crust.
Refrigerate.

title: cranberry chicken
directions: Mix together the first 3 ingredients and pour over the chicken breasts.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour uncovered.

title: turkey tetrazzini
directions: Cook linguini per directions; drain.
Keep warm.
In a 2-quart saucepan over medium heat, in 3 tablespoons hot margarine or butter, cook onion until tender, stirring occasionally.
Stir in flour until blended.
Gradually stir in milk, mushrooms with their liquid, bouillon, salt and pepper.
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture is slightly thickened.
Remove saucepan from heat; stir in cheese.
Tear bread into small pieces to make 2 cups coarse bread crumbs.

title: easy healthy microwave chicken
directions: Place chicken in casserole dish.
Cover with vegetables. Cover with Saran Wrap.
Microwave on High for 15 minutes.
Turn chicken over and microwave for another 15 minutes.
Serve with juice, over cooked rice.

title: french toast
directions: Arrange bread in single layer in 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish. Beat eggs with milk, sugar, vanilla and salt until well blended. Pour over bread.
Turn slices to coat evenly.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Cook vegetables and drain.
Pour in greased baking dish. Layer cheese slices on top and cover with crackers.
Drizzle butter on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: christmas cookies
directions: Mix well. cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and beat well. Alternate flour and water.
Add to cream mixture.
Add nuts, dates or raisins and cherries.
Let mixture set for 2 hours.
Cover with towel.
Spoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 12 minutes at 350°.

title: cucumber dill salad
directions: Completely dissolve gelatin and salt in boiling water. Add lemon juice. Combine cold water and ice cubes to make 1 1/4 cups. Add to gelatin, stirring until slightly thickened. If necessary, remove unmelted ice. Blend in sour cream, add remaining ingredients. Pour into bowl and chill until set, about 2 hours. Makes three cups.

title: original meat loaf
directions: Bake in loaf pan at 300° for 2 hours.
Last half hour, uncover and brown.

title: good chicken
directions: Place chicken in pan.
Combine other ingredients.
Pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until done.

title: sugar-free orange oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream together butter and egg until well mixed.
Gradually beat in juice concentrate.
Combine flour, salt, baking powder, oats, walnuts and raisins in large bowl; stir well.
Mix dry ingredients and creamed mixture together.
Drop by large teaspoonfuls 2 inches apart onto greased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 17 minutes, until lightly browned.
Cool on wire rack.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: parmesan tuna spread
directions: Drain tuna, place in small bowl and flake with a fork.
Blend Parmesan cheese in blender until powder fine.
Mix cheese and mayonnaise into tuna with a fork.
Mixture should be almost smooth.
Yield: 4 servings.
Carbohydrate 1 g, protein 22 g, fat 11 g, calories 201.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Empty cans, barbecue sauce and chopped onion and pour into a crock-pot.
Stir and simmer 2 to 6 hours.

title: apple stuffed chicken breasts
directions: Sprinkle breasts lightly with thyme, Mrs. Dash and pepper. Peel, core and dice apples.
In large, nonstick skillet over medium heat, melt 1 tablespoon margarine.
Add apples and onion and saute until soft, about 5 minutes.
Stir in bread crumbs and moisten with 3 tablespoons cider.
Add currants and sherry. Remove from pan and cool.

title: green tomato bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar; beat in eggs, one at a time.
Stir in tomatoes, flour, nuts, raisins, milk and dry ingredients.
Pour into greased and floured bread pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Makes 3 loaves.
Cool in pans.

title: creamed turkey with biscuits
directions: Strain and heat broth.
Mix the turkey fat or butter with flour.
Add hot broth gradually and cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Add other ingredients.
Pour in flat casserole. Cover with rich biscuit dough, cut with very small cutter.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 450°.
Yields 10 servings.

title: rotelle with basil and parsley ricotta
directions: Whisk the Ricotta cheese, egg, parsley, basil, Parmesan and nutmeg in large bowl.
Cook pasta in large pot of boiling salted water until firm (about 12 minutes).
Drain.
Add immediately to bowl of Ricotta.
Toss to coat hot pasta.
Serve at once.
A very good, low-fat, yet creamy sauce.

title: spanakopita spanish pie
directions: Wash spinach and remove stems.
Cut into 1/2-inch lengths. Mix in salt.
Let stand 15 minutes.
Squeeze liquid from spinach. Beat eggs.
Add parsley, dill, onions and cheese.
Combine spinach with egg mixture.

title: strawberry mousse
directions: Put in blender and freeze.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine sugar and cocoa; add cream.
Bring to a boil and cook for 3 minutes.
Remove from heat; add vanilla flavoring and peanut butter.
Beat until stiff.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased pan. Cool.

title: (georgia) peach seafoam salad
directions: Heat peach juice to boiling; add gelatin and stir to dissolve. Place gelatin and softened cream cheese in blender container. Blend until smooth; add mashed peaches.
Refrigerate until cool and thick.
Fold in whipped topping.
Refrigerate in 8 x 12-inch dish until set.
Serves 6.

title: nut peach pie
directions: Mix and beat first 5 ingredients until egg whites look dry; place in a large pie dish, rounding sides up.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until dry and light brown.
Add fresh peaches or any other fruit desired sliced, sweetened and drained.
Cover with whipping cream or Cool Whip.
Let set a few hours in refrigerator or can be refrigerated overnight.

title: fresh apple date cake
directions: Mix together the flour, salt, soda, baking powder and cinnamon. Mix together eggs, sugar, Wesson oil and vanilla.
Add flour mixture.
Mix together and add the chopped pecans, apples and dates.
Put in Bundt pan and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: chicken in a pan
directions: Lay chicken in a pan.
Pour red wine vinegar over.
Sprinkle each piece with Italian seasonings.
Then sprinkle each piece with dry Lipton soup.
Then put catsup on top of each piece of chicken, cover and bake.

title: spicy grits and sausage casserole
directions: Cook grits according to package directions; set aside.
Cook sausage and onion over medium heat until browned, stirring to crumble sausage; drain.
Combine grits, sausage and remaining ingredients.
Pour into a greased shallow 2-quart baking dish. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: potato soup
directions: Boil potatoes and onion in small amount of water until soft. If desired potatoes may be mashed slightly.
Add milk, salt and pepper and reheat.
Just before serving, add hard-cooked eggs and sprinkle with parsley.

title: bacon water chestnuts
directions: Cut bacon into
thirds. Wrap each chestnut with strip of bacon and secure with toothpick. Bake in glass pan 1/2 hour at 350°. Drain grease.
Mix ketchup
and sugar well. Pour over water chestnuts.
Sprinkle with Worcestershire sauce.
Bake 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: lemon chicken
directions: Coat chicken in flour and salt.
Brown chicken on all sides in hot oil.
Transfer meat to cooker.
Stir together remaining ingredients and pour over chicken.
Cook on high heat setting for 3 to 4 hours.
Thicken liquid.
Serve chicken and gravy over hot rice.

title: raisin and nut sandwich spread
directions: Grind lemon.
Combine lemon, sugar and egg in small saucepan. Cook for a few minutes, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Add raisins and cook for a few minutes.
Let stand until cool.
Stir in mayonnaise and nuts.
Chill until ready to use.
Yields 3 cups.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix Cool Whip and pudding.
Add the rest of the ingredients. Chill for 3 hours or overnight.
Great for picnics or parties. Very easy to make and can be made in advance.

title: tex-mex dip
directions: Combine tomatoes, basil, minced garlic, salt and pepper.
Let stand for 20 to 30 minutes or cover and refrigerate for up to 4 hours.
Slice bread in 1-inch slices and put on baking sheet. Broil until lightly browned on each side.

title: barbecued spareribs
directions: In large pan, cover spareribs with water.
Simmer 1 hour; drain.
Then arrange in single layer in 2 1/2-quart baking dish.

title: marinade for ribs
directions: Pour boiling water over ribs; drain.
Boil mixture.
Pour over meat.
Marinate for 3 hours or longer.
Cook at 250° for 3 hours or longer.

title: burger patties with oatmeal
directions: Mix all ingredients, except tomato juice.
Drop by spoonfuls into hot oil and fry on both sides until well browned.
Pour tomato juice or mushroom soup over top and steam on low heat for 25 minutes.

title: peanut butter oatmeal cookies
directions: Melt butter or margarine.
Beat together with the sugars, vanilla, peanut butter and eggs.
In a separate bowl, combine the flour, bran, oats and baking soda.
Stir into butter mixture. Drop by teaspoons onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes.

title: clam fritters
directions: Clean clams and grind clams and onion until fine. Beat eggs and add to clams and onions. Pour in flour and stir until mixture is well blended. Add salt and pepper to taste. Add oil to skillet and fry until brown.

title: chess squares
directions: In a large bowl, mix cake mix, egg and butter together and pat into pan with edges slightly pushed up; set aside.
In another bowl, mix cream cheese, sugar and 3 eggs together, blend well. Pour into cake mix.
Spread evenly.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes or until desired brown.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: no bake cheesecake
directions: Soften cream cheese; mix with Eagle Brand milk.
Mix until smooth and add lemon juice and vanilla.
Pour into graham cracker crust and chill.
Top with cherries and serve.
Also good with fresh strawberries or plain.

title: baked green beans
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Drain beans; pour into a greased casserole.
Blend soup and milk; pour over the beans.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Pour butter over bread crumbs and pour crumbs on top of beans.
Bake for 15 minutes longer.

title: pumpkin dip with fresh fruit and cookies
directions: In small mixing bowl, beat cream cheese and sugar until well blended.
Add pumpkin, syrup and cinnamon.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Serve as dip with fruit and cookies. (Preparation time:
10 minutes.)

title: stromboli
directions: Let dough rise overnight.
Roll out 1 loaf of dough and put in the bottom of a deep dished pizza pan.
Let dough hang over the edges of the pan.
Put layer of cheese over dough (reserve 1/4 of cheese for top).
Layer rest of the ingredients over cheese.
Roll out other loaf of dough, crimp edges like a pie.
Pour tomato sauce on top and the rest of the cheese.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour. Serves at least 6 to 8 people.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Cook beef until gray.
Add onion, pepper, salt and black pepper.
Mix tomato paste and pizza sauce.
Simmer for a few minutes.
Mix with macaroni in casserole and sprinkle with cheese. Bake until brown at 375°.
Can freeze.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Combine cheese, macaroni, margarine and seasoning.
Mix well. Spoon macaroni into greased 8-inch square baking dish.
Combine with milk and eggs; pour over macaroni mixture.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes or until set.
Yields 5 to 6 servings.

title: best ever deer stew
directions: Roll meat cubes in flour and brown on all sides in oil in a large Dutch oven.
Remove meat and set aside.
Add onion, garlic, and celery to oil remaining in the pot and cook until lightly browned.
Add all seasonings to pot.
Return meat to pot and add consomme and non-alcoholic beer.
Cover and bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer 60 - 90 minutes or until meat is almost tender.
Add vegetables and simmer on low heat for 30 minutes. Remove bay leaf.
Add salt or pepper to taste.
Thicken with flour, if desired.

title: apple blossom cake
directions: Mix first 9 ingredients thoroughly; add 3 cups flour and stir. Pour into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Combine remaining ingredients and sprinkle over batter.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: buttermilk corn bread loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease a 8 1/2 x 4 1/2-inch loaf pan.

title: six cup salad
directions: Drain pineapple and fruit cocktail.
Mix all ingredients together.
Let set overnight in refrigerator to blend.

title: grilled greek chicken
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients in a plastic bag and mix.
Add chicken.
Marinate 2 hours in refrigerator.
Heat grill (we have portable gas grill).
Grill chicken 5 minutes on each side, more if breasts are large.
If desired, sprinkle with Feta cheese and ripe olives.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni in boiling water for 7 minutes.
Drain and rinse with cold water.
Make sauce of butter, flour and milk.
Grease baking dish.
Add macaroni and sauce.
May top with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Serves 2 or 3.

title: blackberry cobbler
directions: Wash berries; drain well.
In a large saucepan, combine berries, water and 1/2 to 1 cup sugar (to taste).
Cook until mixture is hot and sugar is dissolved.
Remove from heat and add lemon juice.

title: fudge brownies
directions: Melt butter.
Stir all ingredients together.
Pour into 8-inch greased square pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: angel flake rolls
directions: Put sugar, salt and yeast in bowl with 1 cup warm water.
Let dissolve.
Melt Crisco and cool.
Add buttermilk and yeast water to flour and knead until smooth.
More flour will be needed. Store in flour covered containers in the refrigerator to be used as desired.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: monkey bread
directions: Combine 1/2 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon.
Quarter biscuits; roll in sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Place in greased Bundt pan.
Combine 1 teaspoon cinnamon and 1 cup sugar; melt this with the stick of butter.
Drizzle over biscuit pieces.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter squares
directions: Mix peanut butter, butter, crumbs and sugar.
Spread in well-greased 10 x 15-inch pan.
Pour melted chips over all.
Chill and slice.
These are always a hit!

title: chocolate surprise cake
directions: Mix sugar, butter and eggs well.

title: ham loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: hot fudge(for hot fudge cake or ice cream)
directions: Mix together and cook for 8 minutes.

title: spinach balls
directions: Cook and drain spinach well.
Mix eggs, stuffing mix, onion, cheese, butter, thyme and garlic salt together.
Chill.
Roll into balls.
Freeze on cookie sheet.
Store in Ziploc bags in freezer.
Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes.

title: cheese cake
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Cream together cheese, sugar and vanilla.
Add gelatin and lemon juice and blend well.
Fold in stiffly whipped Milnot. Mix graham cracker crumbs and oleo.
Pack 2/3 of mixture on bottom and side of 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Add filling and sprinkle with remaining crumbs.
Chill several hours or overnight.
Can be frozen.
Use only Milnot.

title: caramel covered pecans
directions: Beat egg white until stiff.
Dip pecan halves into egg mixture, making sure each is covered well.
Place on a greased pan.
Preheat oven to 250°.
Bake 30 minutes.
Do not open oven door.
Turn oven off and leave in oven 30 more minutes.
Do not open oven door until time has lapsed.

title: beginner biscuits
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt together. Cream sugar and shortening. Cut creamed mixture into flour. Add milk until dough holds together. Turn dough onto floured surface. Roll out to 1/2 to 3/4-inch thickness. Cut with biscuit cutter. Dip biscuits in melted butter. Place in ungreased pan. Bake at 400° or until golden.

title: maple nut pie
directions: Beat eggs "real good"; add milk and syrup.
Boil until this mixture forms a thick custard.
Add pecans and pour into a baked pie crust.
Chill.
Top with whipped cream.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt milk chocolate chips and peanut butter over low heat. Stir in cereal.
Layer mix and powdered sugar in several layers in a brown grocery bag.
Shake bag until cereal is coated with powdered sugar.
Store in sealed container.

title: german noodle bake
directions: Mix all and bake for 1 hour at 350° in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch casserole.

title: lemon cream sherbet
directions: Add 1/4 cup sugar to milk and stir until thoroughly dissolved. Add lemon rind and juice.
Turn mixture into cold freezer tray and freeze.
Beat egg whites until stiff but not dry; add remaining sugar and beat well.
Whip cream to a custard consistency.
Combine mixtures and return sherbet to freezer tray.
Freeze 2 to 3 hours without stirring.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Cook noodles.
In a large saucepan, melt butter.
Combine soups, sour cream and chicken.
Mix in spaghetti.
Add cheese to taste.
Place in a large baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: You will need a potato peeler.

title: old fashioned pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add egg yolks one at a time.
Add flour.
Whip egg whites until soft peaks form.
Fold into batter. Bake in tube pan in cold oven at 325° for one hour and 15 minutes. Add glaze (powdered sugar and milk) while still hot.

title: colonel muncy's oven-fried chicken
directions: Cut chicken in half.
Wipe dry; remove skin and fat.
In a large bowl, combine all ingredients except margarine and corn flakes.
Stir well.
Add chicken.
Make sure each piece is covered well.
Let stand overnight in refrigerator.
Remove chicken pieces from mixture; blot off excess moisture with a dry towel.
Dip each piece in melted margarine, then roll in cornflakes.
Place chicken in a single layer on a shallow baking pan.
Sprinkle with parsley. Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: holiday crescents
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Beat butter and almond extract until fluffy.
Beat sugar, add flour gradually.
Stir oats and almonds. Shape into crescent shapes.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 15 to 18 minutes, until light brown.
Sift powdered sugar over warm crescents.
Yield: 3 dozen.

title: dump salad
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Add cool whip and chill for 1 hour.

title: wassail
directions: Tie spices in cheesecloth.
Drop into hot simmering cider. Stir in sugar.
Simmer over low heat for 30 minutes.
Do not boil. Makes 20 servings.

title: vegetarian chili
directions: Combine all ingredients in a crock-pot and cook on high for 4 hours or on low for 8 to 10 hours.
Can also be simmered on stove top for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: zucchini cake
directions: Heat
oven to 325°.
Grease and flour pan.
Blend all ingredients on low speed 1 minute.
Beat on medium for 1 minute. Pour into pan.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool 10 minutes and remove from pan and cool completely.

title: cinnamon topped oatmeal muffins
directions: Bake 15 minutes at 425°.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: asparagus patties
directions: Put first 3 ingredients through a coarse food grinder. Liquefy remaining ingredients in blender.
Mix everything together and drop by spoonfuls onto an oiled baking sheet.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Serve over lettuce with a mild mustard on the side.

title: fruited tea
directions: Mix together first 4 ingredients. Add water. Makes 3 gallons of tea.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix vanilla pudding as directed.
Add sour cream.
Then add Cool Whip.
Add sliced bananas to mixture, layering alternately with mixture and vanilla wafers.

title: slushie punch
directions: Mix sugar, jello, water and juice. Stir until dissolved.
Add enough water to make 1 gallon.
Freeze.
Chop and put in punch bowl.
Pour 7-Up over to taste!

title: 3 bean salad
directions: Drain corn and beans.
Mix all ingredients and marinate at least overnight.
Will keep well in refrigerator.

title: appetizer pie
directions: Mix cream cheese and milk until well mixed. Add sour cream, beef, green pepper, and onion. Mix until well blended. Spread into a glass pie plate. Top with chopped nuts. Bake until bubbly. Serve with crackers as a dip.

title: lotsa party mix
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Use top and bottom of large roaster. Must have side handles or 2 large cake pans.

title: tuna with curried almond rice
directions: Melt 6 tablespoons of the margarine.
